nagement, measurement & reporting) in order to effectively advocate for operational excellence of those workflows with key stakeholders (e.g., Product, Engineering, Legal, and other cross-functional teams) Investigate & define clear business problems and prioritize solutions using data-driven analytics, developing success metrics to measure project performance and alignment with team mission and goals Effectively plan and manage complex projects from the initial ideation phase through final execution to further our mission Be on the front lines of the workflow and proactively communicate regular updates, concerns, trends and the impact of changes to all internal stakeholders Develop and deliver measurement and reporting to quantify the impact of all launches, and monitor and analyze product and operational health metrics Drive internal and external process improvements, consulting with cross-functional teams to understand needs and pain points related to tools support, solve workflow problems, and ensure internal tools and automation systems are fully leveraged Communicate clearly the progress of monthly initiatives to internal and external stakeholders, including the ability to synthesize feedback and adjust plans accordingly MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS degree Experience in a role involving strategic/analytical initiatives (ie: operations, project management, consulting experience, data analysis or technical systems) Ability to communicate with a variety of audiences Critical thinking and problem solving experience Fluent in Arabic & English PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working and communicating with global teams Ability to source both internal and external data sets Experience with or exposure to SQL Experience working with or in support of diverse communities Experience in the business analysis of processes, metrics, workflows, or operations"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MolC9UAJ/", "title": "Signal Integrity Engineer", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Driven by our rapid growth, Facebook is looking to take advantage of the efficiency gained by optimizing our network hardware for our data centers. Our network platform is industry-leading for its efficiency, throughput, scalability, reliability and intelligence. Facebook is looking for a Signal Integrity Engineer to support the development of the overall network equipment of Facebook and shape the next generation of network that goes into our massively scalable data centers. RESPONSIBILITIES Establish framework of a Signal Integrity Team supporting development of next generation hardware platforms. Drive leading edge SerDes design, SerDes validation and SerDes test methodologies with our silicon and our manufacturing partners. Lead signal integrity work on ASIC, PHY, FPGA and system level. Assist in developing systems for Facebook\u2019s next generation network across a broad range of technologies including switch, router, and transport. Collaborate on new designs/solutions for Facebook data center networking, bringing them from concept to operations. Design the next generation of open on- and off-chip interconnect technologies and integrate these into highly scalable, deplorable and maintainable systems. Support the hardware design, debug, validation and optimization of the products. Work in a collaborative environment across Facebook and with ODM's & OEM's and suppliers to drive Facebook's requirements for development, planning, operation and deployment. Work with ODM and CM suppliers to evaluate existing designs and work towards developing cost-effective and innovate custom designs that meet Facebook networking requirements. Involvement in projects from concept through production, perform the design review across different cross-functional teams, gaining exposure to the complete design life cycle. Support the engineering builds with high volume manufacturing. Support production operation of Facebook's network platform across our data center, develop efficient automation tools to improve operation efficiency. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 7+ years of experience with signal integrity analysis. 7+ years of experience with PCB board level design and layout, high speed interconnect and switching using merchant silicon ASICs. 7+ years of hardware development experience, with emphasis in network equipment field, such as switch, router, or transport. Proven track record of conceptualizing and delivering engineering solutions to customers. 7+ years of experience working with ODM and CM suppliers. 7+ years of experience with environmental testing and electrical certifications. 7+ years of programming experience in test/measurement automation and/or simulation. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Strong knowledge in signal integrity and high-speed design with 25Gbps+ signals. Strong experience with signal integrity modeling and simulation tools (HFSS, ADS, etc.). Strong experience with signal integrity analysis tools including (HSPICE, Sigrity, etc.). Hands-on lab experience on TDR, VNA, logic analyzers and scopes. Advanced knowledge of data center switching, routing, and network protocols. Knowledge or experience in semiconductor devices, VLSI design, microelectronic device. Programming experience in test/measurement automation and/or simulation. Experience with open-source software tools. Linux knowledge or other embedded environments."}
