{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCYaAUAX/", "title": "Program Manager, Business Integrity", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Business Integrity's mission is to ensure safe and trusted connections between people, businesses, and Facebook. Our team works together to anticipate and predict potential threats to our platform, design and build tools to protect against these threats, and then implement and enforce these systems at scale. We leverage data analysis, machine learning and a robust infrastructure to review the quality of promoted content on our platform. We partner closely with several cross-functional teams, including product, engineering, and data science, to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and businesses across the Facebook family of apps.\n\nSuccessful candidates for this team are adaptable, creative, have a bias toward action, aren't afraid of being wrong, and can successfully work across various teams & countries. Opportunities are available in Singapore. RESPONSIBILITIES Partner with cross-functional teams such as Product, Engineering, and outsourced vendors to lead or contribute to large scale strategic projects as well as solve ongoing operational problems at scale. Inform, influence, and execute new strategies and tactics using sound analysis and impact metrics to support your positions Leverage data informed insights to drive new products and initiatives Work with data and measurement partners to identify and track key program performance indicators, and ensure the results contribute to overall company, product, customer, and community experience goals Identify trends to enhance the support and detection processes and improve team efficiency Manage, coordinate, and/or support policy enforcement projects as needed MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS or Advanced Degree 4+ years of professional experience in product/program management or related field Analytical skills, with experience solving problems using data and providing practical business insights/cases Ability to influence data, business, and engineering teams through an understanding of business and ecosystem needs Experience working with international or cross-functional teams Experience resolving and communicating about issues with both technical and non-technical audiences Experience being a \u201cconnector\u201d across teams and managing a program/project against KPIs through to completion PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience performing analytics work or manipulating data sets Experience with SQL Understanding of relevant landscapes including ad tech, outsourcing, policy, and spam/fraud Advanced degree"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoxTsUAJ/", "title": "Manager, Business Integrity", "location": "Mumbai, India", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Business Integrity's mission is to ensure safe and trusted connections between people, businesses, and Facebook. Our team works together to anticipate and predict potential threats to our platform, design and build tools to protect against these threats, and then implement and enforce these systems at scale. We leverage data analysis, machine learning and a robust infrastructure to review the quality of promoted content on our platform. We partner closely with several cross-functional teams, including product, engineering, and data science, to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and businesses across the Facebook family of apps.\n\nSuccessful candidates for this team are adaptable, creative, have a bias toward action, aren't afraid of being wrong, and can successfully work across various teams & countries. This is a full-time position based in our Singapore office. RESPONSIBILITIES Manage a high-performance team in a technical operations organization covering a wide variety of workflows including content review, policy creation & enforcement, fraud/spam research & investigation, reporting & analytics, tool & infrastructure development, new product testing & support, and vendor management Identify and assess risks & opportunities develop goals & metrics to assess impact Develop and drive operations to enable and maintain quality in the ecosystem, across multiple teams, ensuring timely and thoughtful response, and scalable processes Develop - in partnership with multiple functions in multiple geographies - principles for policy development and enforcement, and decisions Use insights gleaned from investigations and other inputs to proactively mitigate risk to advertisers and users and to inform and improve operations and execution Interface and consult regularly with cross-functional groups and leaders both internally and externally Develop domain expertise across Business Integrity, informed by trends in business and technology including knowledge of current/potential Facebook business models and customer needs Staff and manage dynamic and technical teams, including managing other people managers Develop, coach, mentor, and ensure high performance without burnout MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS degree, preferably in a analytical field such as Math, Statistics, Computer Science, Econ, or Information Systems 10+ years of experience in strategic and operational roles Experience in leading other people managers Experience leading cross-functional projects and ability to work with people at all levels both inside and outside of Facebook Experience leading & working with global teams and customers Experience managing with ambiguity and principles in a high-pressure environment Ability to shape strategy and execute against that strategy, with appropriate prioritization of people and resources Ability to communicate the results of analyses, along with the ability to compile briefing materials and other communications Ability to juggle priorities and tasks Organizational skills, with ability to identify opportunities for efficiency improvements PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Advanced degree (MS/MA/MBA) Experience managing and/or working with high-performance teams focused on Analytics (including developing data pipeline architecture, organizational metrics, and insights into problems) and Engineering (infrastructure, tool development, and system design) Analytical ability with experience with data tools and SQL abilities Ability to set and drive operational metrics, do staffing ROI analyses and drive data for OPEX conversations Demonstrated success presenting complex research data (qualitative and quantitative) in a clear and compelling manner that inspires action Experience utilizing both qualitative analysis (e.g. content analysis, phenomenology, hypothesis testing) and quantitative analysis techniques (e.g. cluster analysis, descriptive and inferential statistics) Experience managing remotely, across global regions Experience working with or in support of diverse communities and global teams"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MomL1UAJ/", "title": "Business Integrity Associate, Spanish", "location": "New York, NY", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Business Integrity's mission is to ensure safe and trusted connections between people, businesses, and Facebook. Our team works together to anticipate and predict potential threats to our platform, design and build tools to protect against these threats, and then implement and enforce these systems at scale. We leverage data analysis, machine learning and a robust infrastructure to review the quality of promoted content on our platform. We partner closely with several cross-functional teams, including product, engineering, and data science, to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and businesses across the Facebook family of apps. Successful candidates for this team are adaptable, creative, have a bias toward action, aren't afraid of being wrong, and can successfully work across various teams & countries. This role is based in New York City or Seattle, WA.  RESPONSIBILITIES Become a subject matter expert in workflows spanning a variety of business integrity disciplines (policy creation & enforcement, content review, process optimization, spam research & mitigation, advertiser experience, vendor management, measurement & reporting) in order to effectively advocate for operational excellence of those workflows with key stakeholders (e.g., Product, Engineering, Legal, and other cross-functional teams) Investigate & define clear business problems and prioritize solutions using data-driven analytics, developing success metrics to measure project performance and alignment with team mission and goals Effectively plan and manage complex projects from the initial ideation phase through final execution to further our mission Be on the front lines of the workflow and proactively communicate regular updates, concerns, trends and the impact of changes to all internal stakeholders Develop and deliver measurement and reporting to quantify the impact of all launches, and monitor and analyze product and operational health metrics Drive internal and external process improvements, consulting with cross-functional teams to understand needs and pain points related to tools support, solve workflow problems, and ensure internal tools and automation systems are fully leveraged Communicate clearly the progress of monthly initiatives to internal and external stakeholders, including the ability to synthesize feedback and adjust plans accordingly MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS degree Fluent in Spanish & English (read, write and speak) Experience in a role involving strategic/analytical initiatives (i.e.: operations, project management, consulting experience, data analysis or technical systems) Experience communicating with a variety of audiences Critical thinking and problem-solving experience PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working and communicating with global teams Ability to source both internal and external data sets Experience with or exposure to SQL Experience working with or in support of diverse communities Experience in the business analysis of processes, metrics, workflows, or operations"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MonGEUAZ/", "title": "Finance Manager \u2013 Community Integrity", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The FP&A team manages Facebook\u2019s revenue and expense budget. We focus on using our unique view into the numbers to see trends and opportunities that are developing within Facebook and within related industries. Successful candidates for this team have a bias toward action, have exceptional partnership and communication skills, and know how to balance getting the details right while still moving fast. \n \nIn this role, you\u2019ll join a team that manages the finances for Facebook\u2019s research and tech development groups that focus on key efforts like safety, security, growth and monetization across all our products. The groups you\u2019ll support build and design products and tools aimed at keeping the community safe and secure while minimizing bad experiences for our users \u2013 one of Facebook\u2019s key focus areas. You will gain invaluable experience in a position that offers significant responsibility and interaction with business partners as well as considerable opportunity to have a large impact working cross-functionally within a growing Finance organization. Our ideal candidate is a well-rounded top performer who can be a key contributor in a high-energy growth environment. The position is full-time and located in Menlo Park, CA. RESPONSIBILITIES Create strong business partnerships with leaders of all levels and functions within Facebook\u2019s Integrity product groups Provide financial leadership across headcount planning, budgeting, forecasting, and long-range planning Help business partners gain key insights into spend with meaningful and actionable analyses Build thoughtful resource allocation analyses to drive better investment decisions Collaborate cross-functionally with other FP&A teams to be the lead finance partner for consolidating the Integrity effort across all Tech groups companywide Partner with operations including purchasing, accounting, corporate finance to support the R&D groups Identify and lead initiatives to continuously improve, automate, and scale forecasting and reporting tools, processes, and methodologies MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 6+ years of financial planning and analysis experience BA/BS in Business, Economics, or equivalent Experience in accounting concepts and financial planning Experience in Excel Features and PowerPoint PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working at a leading technology company or high growth company Experience with Hyperion Essbase and Oracle Financials Experience building cross-functional relationships and partnering with organizational leaders Analytical skills and experience with building business cases Communication skills and ability to tailor messaging as required for audiences of varying level of expertise Self-driven, organized, detail-oriented, and able to multi-task in a fast-paced environment"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCTDgUAP/", "title": "Manager, Hardware Product Integrity", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is looking for an engineering leader for our Hardware Product Integrity team. In this role, you will be responsible for managing a team of experienced quality, reliability, failure analysis, and compliance engineers who support Facebook's data center and connectivity hardware development. The Hardware Product Integrity team owns building scalable platforms for failure analysis and reliability as well as developing and implementing the compliance strategy for the Facebook Infrastructure team. As Manager of the team, you will be responsible for developing and executing on the team's mission and vision as well as giving technical guidance to core team members and partners. RESPONSIBILITIES Hire, develop, and lead a team of quality, reliability, failure analysis, and compliance engineers that are responsible for ensuring the hardware integrity of Facebook's data centers. Develop analytics, metrics, tools, risk assessment and mitigation plans for key strategic initiatives. Partner with hardware engineering, data center operations, and supply chain teams to build scalable platforms to measure and improve the hardware health of the data center fleet. Partner with legal, hardware engineering, and sustainability teams to build EMC, safety, and environmental compliance policies and strategies for Facebook's world wide data center deployments. Establish and foster strong working relationships with internal and external stakeholders and find creative ways to overcome obstacles to ensure delivery of quality, schedule, and technical goals. Highlight and drive opportunities for significant technical and operational improvements and drive high impact initiatives with measurable results. Help engineers develop their careers by providing them technical guidance to develop their long term skills. Hold your own in a technical discussion, be a subject matter expert, and have strategic influence. Up to 25% travel required to review and coordinate various initiatives with onsite personnel and vendors. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree in electrical, mechanical, or equivalent engineering field. 15+ years experience in hardware quality, reliability, failure analysis, and/or compliance engineering. 5+ years of direct management experience in an engineering or technical field. Experience moving from strategy to execution and delivering results while managing multiple tasks. Experience balancing multiple priorities and influencing cross-functional teams. Interpersonal and communication experience. Analytical, problem-solving, and organizational experience. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Master's degree or PhD. Action-orientated with the ability to get things done and overcome obstacles. Ability to thrive in a fast-paced and dynamic team environment."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000ModXuUAJ/", "title": "Product Manager, Community Integrity", "location": "Seattle, WA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Community Integrity builds a safe, inclusive community by minimizing and removing the bad experiences for people on Facebook. Community Integrity encompasses a number of teams responsible for preventing real-world harm where Facebook is used as a means to attack victims. The team is responsible for globally preventing and mitigating abuse including keeping bad actors, behaviors, and content off our platform. It also includes a responsibility to help users through some of life\u2019s more sensitive moments. We protect people by analyzing behavior, leveraging our community of users and utilizing technologies like natural language processing (NLP), Machine Learning (ML) and Artificial Intelligence (AI). At a scale of two billion+ people, this certainly has its challenges and we\u2019re looking for a number of Product Managers to drive our efforts to solve these problems. \n \nFacebook Product Managers work with teams of engineers and designers to build products. We are looking for extremely entrepreneurial Product Managers to help innovate and execute product initiatives across the company. This position is full-time and based at our Seattle office. RESPONSIBILITIES Understanding the different problems and prioritizing between them Helping to define our policies Identifying opportunities that will reduce the prevalence of abuse Building systems to proactively detect or to help people report these issues Reviewing tools used by community operations to investigate potential abuse Building end-to-end flows for handling abuse including referring severe cases to law enforcement MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years product management experience, including delivery of entire products from start to finish Communication and presentation experience Organizational and analytical experience Knowledge in technical architecture of scalable web applications and/or media products Experience designing user interfaces and creating examples through wire frames and mock ups PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience developing social products, technologies and platforms Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, start-up environment"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCGR4UAP/", "title": "Director, Pages Integrity", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a leader to manage our Pages Integrity team within the Business Integrity Organization. Business Integrity's mission is to ensure safe and trusted connections between people, businesses, and Facebook. Our team works together to anticipate and predict potential threats to our platform, design and build tools to protect against these threats, and then implement and enforce these systems at scale. We leverage data analysis, machine learning and a robust infrastructure to review the quality of promoted content on our platform. We partner closely with several cross-functional teams, including product, engineering, and data science, to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and businesses across the Facebook family of apps.\n \nThis person will build a team that will develop, implement, and iterate on the operational strategy needed to ensure the integrity of our Pages ecosystem. Candidates will be data-driven, collaborative, and comfortable in a fast-paced environment. This leader will be expected to think creatively about nebulous issues and solve complex problems impacting our business. This person will be a strong people leader who can demonstrate a sustained ability to hire and develop strong talent. They will also be able to work successfully across teams and countries. This role is based in Austin or Menlo Park and reports to the Global Business Integrity Director. RESPONSIBILITIES Shape strategy and operations of our Pages Integrity team, identify and assess risks and opportunities, develop review workflows to minimize and manage risk, to ensure trust and safety on our platforms Develop and drive operations to enable and maintain quality in the ecosystem, across multiple teams, ensuring timely and thoughtful response, and scalable processes Develop in partnership with multiple functions in multiple geographies, principles for Page policy development and enforcement, and decisions Use insights gleaned from investigations and other inputs to proactively mitigate risk to advertisers and users and to inform and improve operations and execution Interface and consult regularly with cross-functional groups and leaders both internally and externally Develop domain expertise across Business Integrity, informed by trends in business and technology including knowledge of current/potential Facebook business models and customer needs Build and manage a team with domain expertise and agility Develop, coach, mentor, and ensure high performance without burnout MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree in an analytical field (such as Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Finance, or similar) 12+ years of experience in strategic and operational roles, within the online advertising domain or related space Experience working with global teams and customers PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 10+ years management experience in a role involving policy, strategy or operations Experience managing with ambiguity and principles in a high-pressure environment Ability to work with people at all levels both inside and outside of Facebook"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MopoEUAR/", "title": "Data Scientist, Analytics (Integrity)", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  We're looking for Data Scientists to work on measuring, detecting, reducing, and preventing  negative experiences such as Hate Speech and Fake News in order to ensure that Facebook is a safe and welcoming community. RESPONSIBILITIES The Data Scientist, Analytics (Integrity) role has work across the following four areas: Data Infrastructure -Working in Hadoop and Hive primarily, sometimes MySQL, Oracle, and Vertica -Automating analyses and authoring pipelines via SQL and python based ETL framework Product Operations -Forecasting and setting product team goals -Designing and evaluating experiments -Monitoring key product metrics, understanding root causes of changes in metrics -Building and analyzing dashboards and reports -Building key data sets to empower operational and exploratory analysis -Evaluating and defining metrics Exploratory Analysis -Proposing what to build in the next roadmap -Understanding ecosystems, user behaviors, and long-term trends -Identifying new  levers to help move key metrics -Building models of user behaviors for analysis or to power production systems Product Leadership -Influencing product teams through presentation of data-based recommendations -Communicating state of business, experiment results, etc. to product teams -Spreading best practices to analytics and product teams MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 2+ years experience doing quantitative analysis BA/BS in Computer Science, Math, Physics, Engineering, Statistics or other technical field Experience in SQL or other programming languages Experience initiating and driving projects to completion with minimal guidance Experience communicating the results of analyses Knowledge of statistical analysis PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience with a statistical package such as R, MATLAB, SPSS, SAS, Stata, etc. Experience with an Internet-based company"}
