ng analysis to execute data-informed initiatives that help improve our support channels, improve the quality of our ad products and drive great service Apply expertise in quantitative analysis, data mining, and data visualization to see beyond the numbers and pull insights to help identify trends and opportunities to drive growth of our products and business Conduct in-depth investigations leveraging large and complex data sets Partner with Data Science, Product and Engineering teams to solve problems at scale Inform, influence, and execute new strategies and tactics using analysis and impact metrics to support your positions MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS in an analytical field such as Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Finance, or similar 9+ years experience doing quantitative analysis, operational analyses or general leadership in a risk, tech, analytics, operations field 2+ years people management experience 4+ years of analytics experience with large data sets to formulate insights and drive solutions 3+ years of advanced SQL experience Development experience in at least one scripting language (Python, JavaScript, PHP, C++, Perl) Experience with data visualization tools such as Tableau or packages in R/Python Experience in leading teams that develop data pipeline architecture, organizational metrics, insights into problems and sharing levers Track record of operating independently, being detail-oriented, and delivering results Cross-functional experience, including experience leading or influencing change through data driven insights Communication skills with an ability to articulate issues to both technical and non-technical audiences PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working with or in support of diverse communities"}
