{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCDJcUAP/", "title": "Technical Program Manager, Integrity", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Our mission is to prevent people from having negative experiences on Facebook due to product or platform abuse. We build large scale, complex systems and operate an infrastructure to enable detection and remediation of content and behaviors that violate our Community Standards. We do this on a global scale across the full suite of Facebook products. \nWe are looking for a Technical Program Manager who will become a subject matter expert in specific areas of our integrity work, and will provide support to a largely cross-functional team in reducing negative impact on the platform. Our team is comprised of varying levels of experience and backgrounds, from new grads to industry veterans. Relevant experience is important, but ultimately less so than your demonstrated abilities and attitude. \nAre you passionate about helping those around you be more effective? Do you think about technology as a way to increase efficiency and change how we combat abuse? Our team is looking for candidates that share our passion for tackling complexity head-on, to help build tools and processes that can scale through multiple orders of magnitude. This is a full-time position based in Menlo Park and will report to the Group Technical Program Manager. Our team is global so some travel is expected. RESPONSIBILITIES Manage cross-functional platform programs by working with development teams, data teams and operations. Develop and manage end-to-end project plans and ensure on-time delivery Communicate status and big picture to the project team and management Provide hands-on program management during analysis, design, development, testing, implementation, and post implementation phases Provide day-to-day coordination and quality assurance for projects and tasks Drive internal process improvements, remove gaps across multiple teams and ensure teams are working on high impact projects that align with company mission and goals Interface with Engineering and Product teams for project requirements and scope Understand and be able to communicate well in regards to backend infrastructure MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS B.S. in a technical or science discipline or equivalent experience 3+ years of tech industry experience and 3+ years of program management experience Communication, organization, and coordination skills along with multi-tasking capabilities to get things done in a fast-paced environment Analytical and problem-solving skills, experience to large-scale systems and writing queries Ability to communicate and translate non-technical to technical (and vice versa) requirements and discussions. Ability to work cross-functionally with multiple partners in different time zones. Experience working with external technology vendors and partners Proven ability to establish work relationships across multi-disciplinary teams PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in using technology to detect and action online integrity related issues Experience with manual labeling and measuring labeling quality"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCGLxUAP/", "title": "Business Integrity Analyst, Technical", "location": "Dublin, Ireland", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Business Integrity's mission is to ensure safe and trusted connections between people, businesses, and Facebook. Our team works together to anticipate and predict potential threats to our platform, design and build tools to protect against these threats, and then implement and enforce these systems at scale. We leverage data analysis, machine learning and a robust infrastructure to review the quality of promoted content on our platform. We partner closely with several cross-functional teams, including product, engineering, and data science, to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and businesses across the Facebook family of apps.\n\nSuccessful candidates for this team are adaptable, creative, have a bias toward action, aren't afraid of being wrong, and can successfully work across various teams & countries. This role is based in Dublin, Ireland. RESPONSIBILITIES Develop compelling analyses to execute data-informed initiatives that helps improve our support channels, improve the quality of our ad products and drive great service Apply expertise in quantitative analysis, data mining, and data visualisation to see beyond the numbers and pull insights to help identify trends & opportunities to drive growth of our product & business Be a thought leader for data-informed initiatives and guide the team\u2019s direction overall Conduct in-depth investigations leveraging large and complex data sets Partner with Data Science, Product and Engineering teams to solve problems at scale Inform, influence, and execute new strategies and tactics using analysis and impact metrics to support your positions MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS in Computer Science, Engineering, Math/Finance, Physics, Economics, Statistics or other technical discipline with professional experience in a quantitative field Experience with SQL Experience with reporting systems and data pipeline architecture Experience leveraging data to make decisions and solve problems Experience resolving, communicating, and presenting issues & insights to both technical and non-technical audiences Critical thinking and problem solving experience in a professional setting Ability to assess, analyze and resolve complicated issues, and distill that complexity into simple and concise communication PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working and communicating with global teams Experience with statistical analysis, and a statistical package such as R, MATLAB, SPSS, SAS, or Stata Development experience in at least one scripting language (PHP, Python, Perl) Advanced technical degree"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoUntUAF/", "title": "IP Integrity Analyst", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  We\u2019re the team that\u2019s responsible for managing reports surrounding Facebook\u2019s policies and procedures, complex legal issues and the changing landscape of free speech on the Internet. We are passionate about building trust and giving the most voice to the most people. We are constantly balancing mitigating legal risk with making the world more open and connected while scaling our operations to support Facebook\u2019s 1.8 billion users. \n \nOur Integrity team focuses on bringing innovative and scalable technical solutions to enhance the notice-and-takedown process by enforcing our policies against bad actors in the intellectual property space, through automation, abuse detection, and operational excellence.\n \nSuccessful candidates for this team have a bias toward action and enjoy finding patterns amid chaos, making quick decisions, and aren't afraid of being wrong. The perfect candidate will have a background in a quantitative or technical field, experience working with large data sets and data-driven decision making, and some coding experience. You are focused on results, a self-starter, and have demonstrated success in using analytics to reduce abuse and negative user experiences across the platform. This position is located in our Menlo Park office. \n RESPONSIBILITIES Apply your expertise in quantitative business analysis, data mining, and the presentation of data to identify trends and opportunities to combat abuse in the IP space Implement and scale effective countermeasures to eliminate IP abuse Deliver insights from data that drive business prioritization and automation efforts Collaborate with our Legal team and act as the voice of IP operations to solve problems at scale Be a thought leader for data-informed initiatives Partner with Data Science, Product, Engineering and Operations teams to solve problems at scale MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS in Computer Science, Math/Finance, Physics, Applied Economics, Statistics or equivalent experience in end-to-end project management, product, technical, and/or operations 2+ years of programming experience with SQL, Python, PHP 2+ years of experience of quantitative analysis 2+ years of SQL experience Experience with data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau) PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in machine learning, predictive or descriptive analytics Experience in an adversarial space such as IP, fraud, spam, risk, or ad policy"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCJKMUA5/", "title": "Business Integrity Associate", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Business Integrity's mission is to ensure safe and trusted connections between people, businesses, and Facebook. Our team works together to anticipate and predict potential threats to our platform, design and build tools to protect against these threats, and then implement and enforce these systems at scale. We leverage data analysis, machine learning and a robust infrastructure to review the quality of promoted content on our platform. We partner closely with several cross-functional teams, including product, engineering, and data science, to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and businesses across the Facebook family of apps.\n \nSuccessful candidates for this team are adaptable, creative, have a bias toward action, aren't afraid of being wrong, and can successfully work across various teams & countries. Opportunities are available in our Singapore office. RESPONSIBILITIES Become a subject matter expert in workflows spanning a variety of business integrity disciplines (policy creation & enforcement, content review, process optimization, spam research & mitigation, advertiser experience, vendor management, measurement & reporting) in order to effectively advocate for operational excellence of those workflows with key stakeholders (e.g., Product, Engineering, Legal, and other cross-functional teams) Investigate & define clear business problems and prioritize solutions using data-driven analytics, developing success metrics to measure project performance and alignment with team mission and goals Effectively plan and manage complex projects from the initial ideation phase through final execution to further our mission Be on the front lines of the workflow and proactively communicate regular updates, concerns, trends and the impact of changes to all internal stakeholders Develop and deliver measurement and reporting to quantify the impact of all launches, and monitor and analyze product and operational health metrics Drive internal and external process improvements, consulting with cross-functional teams to understand needs and pain points related to tools support, solve workflow problems, and ensure internal tools and automation systems are fully leveraged Communicate clearly the progress of monthly initiatives to internal and external stakeholders, including the ability to synthesize feedback and adjust plans accordingly MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS degree 4+ year(s) of work experience in a role involving strategic/analytical initiatives (ie: operations, project management, consulting experience, data analysis or technical systems) Ability to communicate with a variety of audiences Critical thinking and problem solving experience PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working and communicating with global teams Ability to source and manipulate both internal and external data sets Experience with or exposure to SQL Experience working with or in support of diverse communities Experience in the business analysis of processes, metrics, workflows, or operations"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCJtxUAH/", "title": "Manager, Business Integrity", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Business Integrity's mission is to ensure safe and trusted connections between people, businesses, and Facebook. Our team works together to anticipate and predict potential threats to our platform, design and build tools to protect against these threats, and then implement and enforce these systems at scale. We leverage data analysis, machine learning and a robust infrastructure to review the quality of promoted content on our platform. We partner closely with several cross-functional teams, including product, engineering, and data science, to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and businesses across the Facebook family of apps.\n\nSuccessful candidates for this team are adaptable, creative, have a bias toward action, aren't afraid of being wrong, and can successfully work across various teams & countries. This is a full-time position based in our Singapore office. RESPONSIBILITIES Manage a high-performance team in a technical operations organization covering a wide variety of workflows including content review, policy creation & enforcement, fraud/spam research & investigation, reporting & analytics, tool & infrastructure development, new product testing & support, and vendor management Identify and assess risks & opportunities develop goals & metrics to assess impact Develop and drive operations to enable and maintain quality in the ecosystem, across multiple teams, ensuring timely and thoughtful response, and scalable processes Develop - in partnership with multiple functions in multiple geographies - principles for policy development and enforcement, and decisions Use insights gleaned from investigations and other inputs to proactively mitigate risk to advertisers and users and to inform and improve operations and execution Interface and consult regularly with cross-functional groups and leaders both internally and externally Develop domain expertise across Business Integrity, informed by trends in business and technology including knowledge of current/potential Facebook business models and customer needs Staff and manage dynamic and technical teams, including managing other people managers Develop, coach, mentor, and ensure high performance without burnout MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS degree, preferably in a analytical field such as Math, Statistics, Computer Science, Econ, or Information Systems 10+ years of experience in strategic and operational roles 3+ years' experience leading global teams Experience leading cross-functional projects and ability to work with people at all levels both inside and outside of Facebook Experience leading & working with global teams and customers Experience managing with ambiguity and principles in a high-pressure environment Ability to shape strategy and execute against that strategy, with appropriate prioritization of people and resources Ability to communicate the results of analyses, along with the ability to compile briefing materials and other communications Ability to juggle priorities and tasks Organizational skills, with ability to identify opportunities for efficiency improvements PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Advanced degree (MS/MA/MBA) Experience managing and/or working with high-performance teams focused on Analytics (including developing data pipeline architecture, organizational metrics, and insights into problems) and Engineering (infrastructure, tool development, and system design) Analytical ability with experience with data tools and SQL abilities Ability to set and drive operational metrics, do staffing ROI analyses and drive data for OPEX conversations Demonstrated success presenting complex research data (qualitative and quantitative) in a clear and compelling manner that inspires action Experience utilizing both qualitative analysis (e.g. content analysis, phenomenology, hypothesis testing) and quantitative analysis techniques (e.g. cluster analysis, descriptive and inferential statistics) Experience managing remotely, across global regions Experience working with or in support of diverse communities and global teams"}
