 is full-time and based in Menlo Park.\n \n RESPONSIBILITIES Building systems to proactively detect, mitigate, and help people report these issues Helping build tools used by community operations to investigate potential abuse Building end-to-end flows for handling abuse including working with law enforcement Define and own key metrics and key performance indicators Articulate the technology, requirements, goals and milestones of your team Work with Engineering and Product Management to define your team's strategy Reduce surprises during execution and own project management and progress reporting Bring a strong sense of execution and ownership to the team Identifying opportunities that will reduce the prevalence of abuse MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS B.S. in a technical discipline or equivalent experience 5+ years of software engineering, systems engineering or similar experience, in addition to project/program management experience Communication and presentation experience Organizational and analytical experience Experience working on abuse problems PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS B.S. or M.S. degree with focus in computer science, computer engineering 7+ years of software engineering, systems engineering or similar experience, in addition to project/program management experience Web or Internet start-up environment and technical infrastructure management experience Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, start-up environment Passionate about preventing abuse, can rally groups with strong conflicting views and execute well Communication skills and experience working with highly technical management teams Experience organizing and coordinating large-scale tutorials/demos/training sessions for Machine Learning platforms and algorithms Strong organizational and coordination skills along with multi-tasking capabilities to get things done in a fast-paced environment Ability to motivate and focus a large collaboration to reach challenging goals Interpersonal skills, including relationship building and collaboration within a diverse, cross-functional team Analytical and problem-solving skills, exposure to large-scale systems"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LJm45UAD/", "title": "Intellectual Property Integrity, Program Manager", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  We\u2019re the team that\u2019s responsible for managing reports surrounding Facebook\u2019s policies and procedures, complex legal issues and the changing landscape of free speech on the Internet. We are passionate about building trust and giving the most voice to the most people. We are constantly balancing mitigating legal risk with making the world more open and connected while scaling our operations to support Facebook\u2019s 1.8 billion users.  Passionate about diving into the world of big data and trends analyses? Interested in solving complex problems that are geared towards improving Facebook? Excited about learning how to scale and automate processes? Come join the Digital Rights Operations! We focus on bringing innovative and scalable technical solutions to enhance the notice-and-takedown process by enforcing our policies against bad actors in the intellectual property operations space (e.g., repeat infringers and recidivism), through automation, abuse detection, and operational excellence.  Successful candidates for this team have a bias toward action and enjoy finding patterns amid chaos, making quick decisions, and aren't afraid of being wrong. The perfect candidate will have a background in a quantitative or technical field, will have experience working with large data sets, and will have in-depth experience in data-driven decision making. You are scrappy, focused on results, a self-starter, and have demonstrated success in using analytics to reduce abuse and negative user experiences across the platform. This position is located in our Menlo Park office.  RESPONSIBILITIES Articulate the technology, requirements, goals and milestones of your team Manage cross-functional programs in a matrix organization covering a range of areas (Integrity, Trust, Fraud) Develop and manage end-to-end project plans and ensure on-time delivery Provide hands-on program management during analysis, design, development, testing, implementation, and post implementation phases Perform risk management and change management on projects Provide day-to-day coordination and quality assurance for projects and tasks Drive internal process improvements across multiple teams and functions Interface with Engineering, Product, Marketing, Legal, Policy and Operations for program requirements, scope and implementation Help define  metrics and key performance indicators MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS B.S. degree or equivalent experience in technical program management 4+ years of experience in program management, systems or software engineering Communication and interpersonal experience, including relationship building and collaboration within cross-functional team Organizational, coordination and multi-tasking experience Analytical and problem-solving experience and experience in building scalable solutions Experience understanding product requirements and translating needs into plans PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience dealing with projects that cut across legal, policy, trust or fraud Exposure to machine-learning and data modeling"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mp4yhUAB/", "title": "Integrity Project Manager, Media Operations", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Media Operations team develops solutions for public figures on Facebook and Instagram by creating scaled systems to address issues impacting their experiences with the suite of Facebook products. The Media Integrity team protects users and ensures safe connections between users and Media constituents. This individual will focus on establishing our integrity support operations by working to anticipate and predict potential threats and abuse in the media ecosystem, create policies and tools to fight against these threats, and implement and enforce scaled solutions. We partner closely with several cross-functional teams, including product, infrastructure, and data to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and Media partners. \n \nCandidates are expected to think creatively about nebulous issues and are passionate about problem solving. They will also be able to work successfully across teams and countries, and use their technical and analytical expertise to proactively drive solutions for change and ensure safe and meaningful interactions across the Facebook family of apps. This role is based in Singapore. RESPONSIBILITIES Become a subject matter expert in workflows spanning a variety of media integrity disciplines (e.g., policy creation & enforcement, process optimization, measurement & reporting) in order to effectively advocate for operational excellence Build scalable solutions to address market segment, constituent, and legal concerns Identify automation opportunities as we take down malicious actors at scale Develop strong cross-functional partnerships with partnerships, policy, legal, engineering, data science, sales, product management and other operational teams at Facebook in order to implement optimal integrity solutions Improve integrity operations by understanding global challenges and needs, build scalable solutions to address industry segments and constituent pain-points Identify trends and key insights to drive impact to team goals including product, user experience, and operational efficiency MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA or BS Degree 3+ years of experience in online operations, consultancy, analytics or related industries Experience communicating the results of analyses 1+ years of SQL experience Experience working with global teams PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in a fast-paced start-up environment MBA or consultancy work experience"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LJrbyUAD/", "title": "Technical Program Manager, Video Integrity", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a Technical Program Manager, for the Video Integrity team within the Video Platform Team. As a TPM in Video Integrity, you will play a key role, working on various initiatives to ensure that people watching videos on Facebook have a great experience.  This is a constantly evolving space, so the TPM needs to be flexible and be able to pivot based on the problems we are trying to solve. A Technical Program Manager operates within the Engineering and Product organization and has technical knowledge that enables them to influence and drive cross-team projects and roadmaps. Video Platform TPMs work horizontally to create long term value for Facebook by promoting the right technologies for productivity, stability, and growth. This is a full-time position based in our Menlo Park or Seattle offices. RESPONSIBILITIES Manage cross-functional software engineering programs in a matrix organization covering a range of areas. Interface with product teams to gather requirements, and work with engineering teams to define, evaluate, and prioritize. Build common requirements into a roadmap and drive this roadmap through the engineering and cross-functional teams. Develop and manage end-to-end project plans and ensure on-time delivery. Provide hands-on program management during analysis, design, development, testing, implementation, and post implementation phases. Perform risk management and change management on projects. Provide day-to-day coordination and quality assurance for projects and tasks. Interface with Engineering, Product, Marketing, Legal, Policy and Operations for program requirements, scope and implementation. Help drive product decisions to align with higher company initiatives. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS B.S. in a Computer Science or equivalent experience. 5+ years of software engineering, systems engineering, or similar tech experience including 5+ years of program/product management experience. Experience in backend reliability, efficiency, quality and/or performance work. Experience with communication and working with technical management teams. Organizational, coordination and multi-tasking experience. Analytical and problem-solving experience including experience working with large-scale systems and experience writing code/queries. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience with video quality measurements, video integrity, or related areas. Experience with computer vision, machine learning techniques, natural language processing, or related areas. Experience with projects that cut across legal, policy, trust, and fraud. Experience working with large-scale distributed data systems."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MozgBUAR/", "title": "Product Marketing Manager, Business Integrity", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook seeks a leader who is passionate about helping to ensure that Facebook remains a safe and trusted environment for businesses and people. Traits in a successful leader will be maturity and good judgment, technical acuity, and accountability and follow-through. This Product Marketing Manager will partner closely with Product Management, Operations, Policy and other Integrity teams. She or he must thrive as a leader within cross-functional teams, exhibit excellent analytical and communication skills, and have a track record of influencing product strategy and managing complex, fast-paced projects. This is a full-time position based at Facebook headquarters in Menlo Park. RESPONSIBILITIES This team informs product strategy in partnership with product management and engineering across multiple product areas and establishes and drives both in-bound as well as the go-to-market plan for every product in the portfolio through the following skills: -Identify long-term opportunities for business integrity and trust based on regional understanding, analysis and a strategic view of the direction of 