the direction of the market both for businesses and consumers -Market assessment and requirements including impact analysis and competitive benchmarking -Represent voice of the market including qualitative and quantitative feedback on product from clients and partners -Manage product alphas and betas to direct product refinements and identify critical client needs that must be met by the product in order to launch -Lead comprehensive go-to-market strategy including sales and partner materials -Manage high priority, fast-moving decisions and communications regarding policy changes or enforcement MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years experience in marketing, consulting, communications, or internet technology 4+ years experience in the advertising or communications sector and experience contributing at both strategic and operational levels Analytical, data-driven decision-maker Communicator with experience simplifying concepts BA/BS degree PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 3+ years in client facing roles working with large and small advertisers Product Marketing experience"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCa0KUAT/", "title": "UX Researcher, News Feed Integrity", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Come join a diverse and collaborative team of researchers who work directly with product designers and engineers to make the best social platform for Facebook's billion users. Our work ranges from the foundational to the evaluative, from ethnography to experimentation, and allows for collaboration between qualitative and quantitative researchers across the company. For this position, we are looking for a mixed-methods researcher with a history of product research on journalism, media, politics, news consumption and algorithmic curation. \n \nThe ideal candidate is passionate about the power of technology to inform people about their world. Successful candidates are strong communicators, knowledgeable about UI design, passionate about social platforms, comfortable in a fast-moving organization, excited to collaborate and focused squarely on bringing compelling and relevant online experiences to as many people as possible around the world. RESPONSIBILITIES Develop and maintain expertise in politics/polarization/civil discourse, news/journalism/misinformation, and related media/social science research (both academic and market insights) Work closely with product teams to identify research topics that will drive short- and long-term product development Design studies that address both user behavior and attitudes Generate actionable insights that both fuel ideation and evaluate designs Work collaboratively with researchers in other disciplines and teams Work cross-functionally with design, product management, content strategy, engineering and marketing Partner with engineers, analysts, and other technical roles to create and share research Communicate results and illustrate suggestions in compelling and creative ways Collaborate with researchers across the company to elevate research findings on related topics MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 3+ years' experience in political science or journalism/media research or MS/PhD in political science, communication, information science, journalism, human-computer interaction, psychology, media studies, linguistics, anthropology, sociology, market research or a related field Experience with start-to-finish ownership and execution of large-scale research projects Experience with mixed methods research, particularly the design and analysis of research projects that combine surveys, experiments, interviews, and behavioral/server log data Experience with SQL, R or Python Experience conducting international/cross-cultural research Experience communicating theory, analysis and results to a lay audience"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoqByUAJ/", "title": "Product Counsel, Ads \u2013 Business Integrity", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook seeks a highly motivated and experienced team player to serve as Product Counsel on Facebook's product legal team. The position will focus on providing strategic and tactical legal counseling to the product and business teams that build tools for Facebook\u2019s business integrity efforts. This is a great opportunity to join a growing legal team and to work on novel issues in an exciting, fast-paced environment.  RESPONSIBILITIES Review products, features and initiatives to assess legal compliance across multiple jurisdictions Counsel product, marketing, engineering, and other business teams on legal issues related to the provision of online advertising products to help ensure compliance with consumer protection laws, privacy laws and regulations, and other legal requirements Coordinate with legal, public policy and communications colleagues on multi-disciplinary issues Coordinate with content policy, operations, legal and product teams to implement and enforce content standards Support escalations on advertising content assessment and takedown requests MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS J.D. degree and membership in at least one U.S. state bar 4+ years of legal experience, including at a law firm or in-house experience (including applicable litigation, regulatory or product counseling experience) Experience working on multiple different projects simultaneously and building consensus across cross-functional stakeholders PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience advising clients on risk mitigation across technology product platforms Content liability counseling experience related to CDA Sec. 230 or related international frameworks Experience with online advertising industry, including from the perspective of social media or other internet companies, ad agencies, advertisers or publishers, or political advertising Experience with international legal requirements, including those related to data privacy, and how to work effectively across multiple jurisdictions"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MonGYUAZ/", "title": "Automation Specialist, Media Operations Integrity", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook's mission is to give people the power to share, and make the world more open and connected. Through our growing family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that helps billions of people around the world connect and share what matters most to them. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to make the world more open and accessible. Connecting the world takes every one of us\u2014and we're just getting started.\n \nThe Media Operations team develops solutions for partners by creating scaled systems to address issues impacting their experiences with the suite of Facebook products. Within Media Operations, the Media Integrity team protects users and ensures safe connections between Media constituents and their followers. We do so by understanding the landscape, identifying and analyzing problems and trends, and executing scalable solutions. We partner with engineering and other integrity teams to drive solutions. RESPONSIBILITIES Develop a deep understanding of issues facing our constituents and how it affects Facebook, Instagram and our communities Implement effective anti-fraud automation to eliminate abuse based on identified risks Analyze and interpret data in order to devise hypotheses on how fraudulent and other nefarious activity is proliferating Requires contributing to Facebook\u2019s anti-abuse codebase Be a thought leader for data-informed initiatives and guide the team\u2019s direction overall Proactively  investigate, troubleshoot, and resolve sensitive escalations Work collaboratively with cross-functional stakeholders including but not limited to Policy, Communications, Escalations, Spam and other operations teams to solve problems at scale. Please note that some weekend and holiday work will be required on a shift basis MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree in Business, Science, Engineering, Economics or equivalent practical experience. Experience manipulating large data sets in SQL or equivalent. Experience in at least one scripting language (PHP, Python, Perl), statistical software (R, SAS, SPSS), or data visualization tool (Tableau). 2+ years of work experience in an abuse, investigations, consulting, or online operations environment"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MovbWUAR/", "title": "Technical Analytics Associate, Business Integrity", "location": "Dublin, Ireland", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Business Integrity's mission is to ensure safe and trusted connections between people, businesses, and Facebook. Our team works together to anticipate and predict potential threats to our platform, design and build tools to protect against these threats, and then implement and enforce these systems at scale. We leverage data analysis, machine learning and a robust infrastructure to review the quality of promoted content on our platform. We partner closely with several cross-functional teams, including product, engineering, and data science, to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and businesses across the Facebook family of apps.\n\nSuccessful candidates for this team are adaptable, creative, have a bias toward action, aren't afraid of being wrong, and can successfully work across various teams & countries. This role is based in Dublin, Ireland. RESPONSIBILITIES Develop compelling analyses to execute data-informed initiatives that helps improve our support channels, improve the quality of our ad products and drive great service Apply expertise in quantitative analysis, data mining, and data visualisation to see beyond the numbers and pull insights to help identify trends & opportunities to drive growth of our product & business Be a thought leader for data-informed initiatives and guide the team\u2019s direction overall Conduct in-depth investigations leveraging large and complex data sets Partner with Data Science, Product and Engineering teams to solve problems at scale Inform, influence, and execute new strategies and tactics using analysis and impact metrics to support your positions MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS in Computer Science, Engineering, Math/Finance, Physics, Economics, Statistics or other technical discipline with professional experience in a quantitative field Experience with SQL Experience with reporting systems and data pipeline architecture Experience leveraging data to make decisions and solve problems Experience resolving, communicating, and presenting issues & insights to both technical and non-technical audiences Critical thinking and problem solving experience in a professional setting Ability to assess, analyze and resolve complicated issues, and distill that complexity into simple and concise communication PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working and communicating with global teams Experience with statistical analysis, and a statistical package such as R, MATLAB, SPSS, SAS, or Stata Development experience in at least one scripting language (PHP, Python, Perl) Advanced technical degree"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MotVtUAJ/", "title": "Data Integrity Manager, Partnership Analytics", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Partnerships team at Facebook works with leading content creators, publishers, and businesses in entertainment, sports, news, and many other verticals. This role is a unique opportunity to work with one of the most important datasets in the world. In this role you will oversee the process that creates, iterates, enforces and coordinates the policies and processes on which we base the internal and external usage/access of data for the Partnerships Organization.   Your primary responsibility will be to create and manage a process for lots of product teams to plug into to ensure proper use of data and metrics across Partnerships.    RESPONSIBILITIES Develop the philosophies and corresponding policies we use to govern access and use of data (internal & external). Manage a process across stakeholders to review metrics (new and old) and data use permissions. Run cross-functional process to ensure we have efficient and definitive answer on metric/data to maintain the integrity of our policies while enabling speed of execution. Work cross-functionally to define problems and organize data stakeholders to drive to resolution and decisions. From time to time, oversee completion or project manage until resolved. Be a representative to other data teams and educate them about our work & to unify policies to create a 1 FB data approach. Develop training and work across regions and teams to educate the entire partnerships org on Data usage best practices to up-level data integrity for everyone. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 12+ years experience in data policies Experience running cross-functional, cross product initiatives 5+ years\u2019 experience in data related projects, education and/or execution Executive experience, including experience with VP/C level to educate and progress data policy related initiatives PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Strong communication skills Ability to work independently and specific ability to problem solve with little direction"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LJyAEUA1/", "title": "Technical Program Manager, Business Integrity", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a Technical Program Manager, for the Integrity team within Core Ads. As a TPM in Integrity, you will play a key role, working on various initiatives to ensure trustworthy connections between people and businesses. This is a constantly evolving space, so the TPM needs to be flexible and be able to pivot based on the problems we are trying to solve. An Ads Technical Program Manager operates within the Engineering and Product organization and has technical knowledge that enables them to influence and drive cross-team projects and roadmaps. Ads TPMs work horizontally to create long term value for Facebook by promoting the right technologies for productivity, stability, and growth. This is a full-time position based in our Menlo Park, CA office. RESPONSIBILITIES Articulate the technology, requirements, goals and milestones of your team. Manage cross-functional programs in a matrix organization covering a range of areas. Develop and manage end-to-end project plans and ensure on-time delivery. Provide hands-on program management during analysis, design, development, testing, implementation, and post implementation phases. Perform risk management and change management on projects. Provide day-to-day coordination and quality assurance for projects and tasks. Drive internal process improvements across multiple teams and functions. Interface with Engineering, Product, Marketing, Legal, Policy and Operations for program requirements, scope and implementation. Define and own metrics and key performance indicators. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS B.S. in a technical discipline or equivalent experience At least 5 years of technical program management, systems or software engineering experience Communication and interpersonal experience including relationship building and collaboration within cross-functional team Organizational and coordination experience Analytical and problem-solving experience, and experience to large-scale systems Experience understanding product requirements and translating needs into plans PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience dealing with projects that cuts across legal, policy, trust and fraud. PMP Certification (PMI)."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MotQ5UAJ/", "title": "Technical Analytics Lead, Business Integrity", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Passionate about diving into the world of big data and trends analyses? Interested in solving complex problems that are geared towards improving Facebook and its community\u2019s experiences? Excited about learning how to scale and automate processes? Come join the Business Integrity Technical Analytics team at Facebook! \n \nThe Technical Analytics team reports into the Analytics organization at Facebook and specifically supports Business Integrity, which is a cross-functional group across Engineering, Operations, Product Management, and Analytics. The Business Integrity group protects users and ensures safe connections between users and businesses.\n \nOur focus on data analysis, machine learning, and a robust infrastructure of back-end systems allows us to work effectively with our engineering, operations, and product teams to build proprietary tools and techniques to enforce the quality of all promoted content at scale. \n \nSuccessful candidates for this team have a bias toward action and enjoy finding patterns amid chaos, making quick decisions, and aren't afraid of being wrong. The perfect candidate will have a background in a quantitative or technical field, will have experience working with large data sets, and will have in-depth experience in data-driven decision making. You are scrappy, focused on results, a self-starter, and have demonstrated success in using analytics to drive the growth and success of a business. This position is located in our Austin, TX office.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Develop compelling analyses to execute data-informed initiatives that helps improve our support channels, improve the quality of our ad products and drive great service Apply expertise in quantitative analysis, data mining, and data visualization to see beyond the numbers and pull insights to help identify trends & opportunities to drive growth of our product & business Be a thought leader for data-informed initiatives and guide the team\u2019s direction overall Conduct in-depth investigations leveraging large and complex data sets Partner with Data Science, Operations, Product, and Engineering teams to solve problems at scale Inform, influence, and execute new strategies and tactics using analysis and impact metrics to support your positions MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 4+ years experience doing quantitative analysis BA/BS in Computer Science, Math/Finance, Physics, Applied Economics, Statistics or other technical field 4+ years of Excel and SQL experience Development experience in at least one scripting language (PHP, Python, Perl) Experience with reporting systems and data pipeline architecture 4+ years of experience initiating and driving projects to completion with minimal guidance Communication and problem-solving experience Experience resolving and communicating about issues with both technical and non-technical audiences PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Advanced degree Experience with statistical analysis, and a statistical package such as R, MATLAB, SPSS, SAS, or Stata"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LC5EfUAL/", "title": "Product Marketing Manager, Business Integrity", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook seeks a leader who is knowledgeable and passionate about online advertising to ensure that Facebook remains a safe and trusted environment for businesses and people. Traits in a successful leader will be technical acuity, maturity and good judgment, and accountability and follow-through. This Product Marketing Manager will partner closely with Regional Product Marketing, Product Management, Operations, and Sales. She or he must thrive as a leader within cross-functional teams, exhibit excellent analytical and communication skills, and have a track record of shaping product strategy and growing product adoption. This is a full-time position based at Facebook headquarters in Menlo Park. RESPONSIBILITIES This team informs product strategy in partnership with product management and engineering across multiple product areas and establishes and drives both in-bound as well as the go-to-market plan for every product in the portfolio through the following skills: -Identify long-term opportunities for business integrity and trust based on regional understanding, analysis and a strategic view of the direction of the market both for businesses and consumers -Market assessment and requirements including impact analysis and competitive benchmarking -Represent voice of the market including qualitative and quantitative feedback on product from clients and partners -Manage product alphas and betas to direct product refinements and identify critical client needs that must be met by the product in order to launch -Lead comprehensive go-to-market strategy including sales and partner materials -Manage high priority, fast-moving decisions and communications regarding policy changes or enforcement MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years experience in marketing, consulting, communications, or internet technology 4+ years experience in the advertising or communications sector and the ability to contribute at both strategic and operational levels Analytical, data-driven decision-maker Communicator with an ability to simplify concepts BA/BS degree PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 3+ years in client facing roles working with large and small advertisers Product Marketing experience"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCFkWUAX/", "title": "Manager, Business Integrity Technical Solutions", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Business Integrity team ensures safe connections between users and businesses. We ensure our platform is a high quality ecosystem for users, developers, page admins, advertisers and businesses to create and promote digital content. The Technical Solutions team within Business Integrity is an applications engineering team focused on solving for tools development or back-end infrastructure problems as well as implementing business rules through statistical analyses and investigations. We partner closely with product and software engineering teams to enforce the quality of all promoted content at scale.\n \nSuccessful candidates for this team have a bias toward action and enjoy finding patterns amid chaos, making quick decisions, and aren't afraid of being wrong. This position is located in our Austin, Texas office. RESPONSIBILITIES Manage a small to medium-sized team of technical individuals Mentor the team in data analysis, optimization strategy and technical investigations Understand business needs and context to identify gaps and derive solutions leveraging tools and infrastructure knowledge Advocate for the team and align closely with cross-functional partners, driving towards common business and company goals Large scale data analysis, applying statistical methods and writing code for enforcement Use technical expertise to design scalable solutions that impact audience and advertiser behavior while balancing the effect of policy on our communities Partner with cross-functional teams such as Product and Software Engineering to lead or contribute to large scale strategic projects as well as solve ongoing operational problems at scale Self-identify gaps, problems, needs, and come up with robust solutions with relative independence MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 7+ years work experience including at least 4 years of direct people management with a focus on mentoring and coaching Programming experience with a modern language (PHP, Python, C++, Java or Haskell) Experience in SQL and data analysis with statistical focus Communication skills and proven experience as a leader Results-oriented, with prioritization skills Critical thinking and problem solving skills Ability to communicate with technical and non-technical audiences Experience working with or in support of global communities Experience managing concurrent projects and driving initiatives in a cross-functional environment BA or BS in Engineering or quantitative disciplines such as Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science, Information"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCR12UAH/", "title": "Director, Business Integrity Research Operations", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Business Integrity's mission is to ensure safe and trusted connections between people, businesses, and Facebook. Our team works together to anticipate and predict potential threats to our platform, design and build tools to protect against these threats, and then implement and enforce these systems at scale. We leverage data analysis, machine learning and a robust infrastructure to review the quality of promoted content on our platform. We partner closely with several cross-functional teams, including product, engineering, and data science, to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and businesses across the Facebook family of apps.\n \nThe Director of Business Integrity Research Operations will lead a global team of employees who are focused on proactive risk assessment and management. They will operate as a key leader and stakeholder within the Business Integrity team and across Facebook\u2019s key cross-functional partner ecosystem, responsible for driving Research Operations efforts globally. Business Integrity\u2019s \u201cIntegrity Research Operations team\u201d is responsible for driving changes to Facebook\u2019s platform as we protect our users and ensure safe connections between businesses, users and Facebook. \n \nCandidates should have a background and passion for leading a team that is testing our platforms, researching the intersection of how global affairs and trans-national threats affect technology platforms and helping us proactively plan for the future. The successful candidate will effectively manage and develop a team that translates these trends and developments into clear analysis focused on how technology can be abused for unintended purposes, testing the threats against our own platform and experience in methodically identifying solutions for risk mitigation. The candidate will serve as an excellent people manager and partner to relevant teams to provide remediation guidance, build better detection and prevention systems, and close out vulnerabilities. RESPONSIBILITIES Manage leaders and project managers with teams that conceptualize and produce impactful, data-driven, and compelling reports Provide career development opportunities for team members, including tenured managers, and create solutions that will allow the team to scale Develop an organization that scales with time and moves nimbly while driving short and long-term results Build strong relationships with internal partners including Operations, Engineering, Policy, Legal and third-party partners Communicate succinctly to various audiences MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor\u2019s degree in an analytical field (such as Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science, Economics, Information Systems or similar) 15+ years of experience in online operations/consultancy/analytics or related industries People management experience with experience recruiting and managing operations or investigation teams, including performance management Experience managing other people managers Experience developing and communicating research progress, findings, and recommendations Experience translating concepts into language that is understood by audiences, including software engineers, business and technical leaders and external security community members and press PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Advanced degree (MS/MA/MBA) Experience managing and/or working with high-performance teams focused on Analytics (including developing data pipeline architecture, organizational metrics, and insights into problems) and Engineering (infrastructure, tool development, and system design) Understanding of the online ecosystem, particularly tools and tactics used to accomplish specific objectives Analytical ability with experience with data tools and SQL abilities Ability to set and drive operational metrics, do staffing ROI analyses and drive data for OPEX conversations Demonstrated success presenting complex research data (qualitative and quantitative) in a clear and compelling manner that inspires action Experience managing remotely, across global regions Experience working with or in support of diverse communities and global teams"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LBfmgUAD/", "title": "Product Manager, Business Integrity (Ads)", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Ads team at FB helps providing meaningful connections between billions of users and millions of advertisers and ensures great ad experiences across the family of Facebook Apps (Facebook, Instagram, Messenger, Audience Network, and WhatsApp). As a Product Manager in the Business Integrity team you will lead an exciting cross-functional role helping us create an ecosystem that rewards high quality user experiences and advertiser value. \n\nWe are looking for an extremely entrepreneurial Product Manager with deep online advertising domain knowledge and trust/risk experience to manage quality and integrity work across Facebook\u2019s suite of apps. A deep understanding of Machine Learning is a plus. As a member of the Business Integrity product team you'll be responsible for ensuring trustworthy connections between people, publishers and advertisers. You'll be working with engineering teams on building solutions and systems that improve people's experiences with ads across the platform. The ideal candidate will have experience in building, launching, and scaling great products. You must thrive as a leader of highly cross-functional teams, exhibit excellent analytical and communication skills, and have a strong bias for action. This is a full time position based in Menlo Park, California. RESPONSIBILITIES Lead the ideation, technical development, and launch of innovative products Establish a shared quality/risk vision across the company Drive solution development with world-class engineers Brainstorm entirely novel ways to solve trust and risk problems Define and analyze metrics that inform the success of products Understand Facebook\u2019s strategic and competitive position and deliver products that are recognized best in the industry. Maximize efficiency in a constantly evolving environment where the process is fluid and creative solutions are the norm MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 8+ years product management experience, including management of end-to-end solutions related to content quality 4+ years of experience in online advertising in a trust- or risk-related product role Experience working cross-functionally with engineering, sales, legal, policy and external communications teams Communication, presentation, organizational and analytical skills Understanding of the technical architecture and highly scalable web applications and/or media products, including machine learning systems Experience designing user interfaces and process flows \u2013 ability to create examples through wire frames and mock ups Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, start-up environment PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working with both advertisers and publishers on products, technologies and platforms Experience developing social products, technologies and platforms BA/BS"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MonGYUAZ/", "title": "Automation Specialist, Media Operations Integrity", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook's mission is to give people the power to share, and make the world more open and connected. Through our growing family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that helps billions of people around the world connect and share what matters most to them. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to make the world more open and accessible. Connecting the world takes every one of us\u2014and we're just getting started.\n \nThe Media Operations team develops solutions for partners by creating scaled systems to address issues impacting their experiences with the suite of Facebook products. Within Media Operations, the Media Integrity team protects users and ensures safe connections between Media constituents and their followers. We do so by understanding the landscape, identifying and analyzing problems and trends, and executing scalable solutions. We partner with engineering and other integrity teams to drive solutions. RESPONSIBILITIES Develop a deep understanding of issues facing our constituents and how it affects Facebook, Instagram and our communities Implement effective anti-fraud automation to eliminate abuse based on identified risks Analyze and interpret data in order to devise hypotheses on how fraudulent and other nefarious activity is proliferating Requires contributing to Facebook\u2019s anti-abuse codebase Be a thought leader for data-informed initiatives and guide the team\u2019s direction overall Proactively  investigate, troubleshoot, and resolve sensitive escalations Work collaboratively with cross-functional stakeholders including but not limited to Policy, Communications, Escalations, Spam and other operations teams to solve problems at scale. Please note that some weekend and holiday work will be required on a shift basis MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree in Business, Science, Engineering, Economics or equivalent practical experience. Experience manipulating large data sets in SQL or equivalent. Experience in at least one scripting language (PHP, Python, Perl), statistical software (R, SAS, SPSS), or data visualization tool (Tableau). 2+ years of work experience in an abuse, investigations, consulting, or online operations environment"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MovbWUAR/", "title": "Technical Analytics Associate, Business Integrity", "location": "Dublin, Ireland", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Business Integrity's mission is to ensure safe and trusted connections between people, businesses, and Facebook. Our team works together to anticipate and predict potential threats to our platform, design and build tools to protect against these threats, and then implement and enforce these systems at scale. We leverage data analysis, machine learning and a robust infrastructure to review the quality of promoted content on our platform. We partner closely with several cross-functional teams, including product, engineering, and data science, to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and businesses across the Facebook family of apps.\n\nSuccessful candidates for this team are adaptable, creative, have a bias toward action, aren't afraid of being wrong, and can successfully work across various teams & countries. This role is based in Dublin, Ireland. RESPONSIBILITIES Develop compelling analyses to execute data-informed initiatives that helps improve our support channels, improve the quality of our ad products and drive great service Apply expertise in quantitative analysis, data mining, and data visualisation to see beyond the numbers and pull insights to help identify trends & opportunities to drive growth of our product & business Be a thought leader for data-informed initiatives and guide the team\u2019s direction overall Conduct in-depth investigations leveraging large and complex data sets Partner with Data Science, Product and Engineering teams to solve problems at scale Inform, influence, and execute new strategies and tactics using analysis and impact metrics to support your positions MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS in Computer Science, Engineering, Math/Finance, Physics, Economics, Statistics or other technical discipline with professional experience in a quantitative field Experience with SQL Experience with reporting systems and data pipeline architecture Experience leveraging data to make decisions and solve problems Experience resolving, communicating, and presenting issues & insights to both technical and non-technical audiences Critical thinking and problem solving experience in a professional setting Ability to assess, analyze and resolve complicated issues, and distill that complexity into simple and concise communication PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working and communicating with global teams Experience with statistical analysis, and a statistical package such as R, MATLAB, SPSS, SAS, or Stata Development experience in at least one scripting language (PHP, Python, Perl) Advanced technical degree"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MotVtUAJ/", "title": "Data Integrity Manager, Partnership Analytics", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Partnerships team at Facebook works with leading content creators, publishers, and businesses in entertainment, sports, news, and many other verticals. This role is a unique opportunity to work with one of the most important datasets in the world. In this role you will oversee the process that creates, iterates, enforces and coordinates the policies and processes on which we base the internal and external usage/access of data for the Partnerships Organization.   Your primary responsibility will be to create and manage a process for lots of product teams to plug into to ensure proper use of data and metrics across Partnerships.    RESPONSIBILITIES Develop the philosophies and corresponding policies we use to govern access and use of data (internal & external). Manage a process across stakeholders to review metrics (new and old) and data use permissions. Run cross-functional process to ensure we have efficient and definitive answer on metric/data to maintain the integrity of our policies while enabling speed of execution. Work cross-functionally to define problems and organize data stakeholders to drive to resolution and decisions. From time to time, oversee completion or project manage until resolved. Be a representative to other data teams and educate them about our work & to unify policies to create a 1 FB data approach. Develop training and work across regions and teams to educate the entire partnerships org on Data usage best practices to up-level data integrity for everyone. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 12+ years experience in data policies Experience running cross-functional, cross product initiatives 5+ years\u2019 experience in data related projects, education and/or execution Executive experience, including experience with VP/C level to educate and progress data policy related initiatives PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Strong communication skills Ability to work independently and specific ability to problem solve with little direction"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LJyAEUA1/", "title": "Technical Program Manager, Business Integrity", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a Technical Program Manager, for the Integrity team within Core Ads. As a TPM in Integrity, you will play a key role, working on various initiatives to ensure trustworthy connections between people and businesses. This is a constantly evolving space, so the TPM needs to be flexible and be able to pivot based on the problems we are trying to solve. An Ads Technical Program Manager operates within the Engineering and Product organization and has technical knowledge that enables them to influence and drive cross-team projects and roadmaps. Ads TPMs work horizontally to create long term value for Facebook by promoting the right technologies for productivity, stability, and growth. This is a full-time position based in our Menlo Park, CA office. RESPONSIBILITIES Articulate the technology, requirements, goals and milestones of your team. Manage cross-functional programs in a matrix organization covering a range of areas. Develop and manage end-to-end project plans and ensure on-time delivery. Provide hands-on program management during analysis, design, development, testing, implementation, and post implementation phases. Perform risk management and change management on projects. Provide day-to-day coordination and quality assurance for projects and tasks. Drive internal process improvements across multiple teams and functions. Interface with Engineering, Product, Marketing, Legal, Policy and Operations for program requirements, scope and implementation. Define and own metrics and key performance indicators. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS B.S. in a technical discipline or equivalent experience At least 5 years of technical program management, systems or software engineering experience Communication and interpersonal experience including relationship building and collaboration within cross-functional team Organizational and coordination experience Analytical and problem-solving experience, and experience to large-scale systems Experience understanding product requirements and translating needs into plans PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience dealing with projects that cuts across legal, policy, trust and fraud. PMP Certification (PMI)."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCRkPUAX/", "title": "Manager, Software Engineering - Community Integrity", "location": "London, United Kingdom", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is in search of the world\u2019s most creative and experienced engineering leaders. We embrace entrepreneurs as well as those who come from more established organisations. Software Engineering Managers are clearly characterised by progressive technical experience and demonstrated progression in management responsibility. You have also kept your coding skills sharp and bring an unwavering passion for managing the dynamics of a fast-paced environment.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Be both highly technical, hands-on coder and an effective people manager Communicate across functions and drive engineering initiatives Participate in technical design Be a subject matter expert in a product domain Define and influence product strategy MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Proven hands-on technical management. Exceptional coding skills in one of the following:  C++, Java, Javascript, or PHP. Demonstrated ability to manage technical teams. BS / MS in Computer Science (In lieu of degree, relevant work experience)."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LBwpHUAT/", "title": "Software Engineer, Integrity and Anti-Abuse", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking Software Engineers experienced in abuse detection to help keep our two billion users safe from negative experiences in a highly adversarial environment. The ideal candidate will have industry experience working and building scalable detection systems on a range of  problems that keep spam, fraud, deception, and abuse at bay, and are resistant to adversarial iterations. As a successful candidate, you will bring your passion and experience to designing novel anti-abuse measures and deploying them across Facebook's products. We are looking for someone who loves reimagining what's possible when it comes to detecting and disrupting attackers, and building software to realize those ideas to make the internet a safer place for all.\n\nThis position is full-time and based in our Menlo Park, CA office. RESPONSIBILITIES Develop situational awareness in a highly adversarial environment and keep Facebook's anti-abuse capabilities ahead of our attackers. Build highly scalable classifiers and tools leveraging machine learning and rule-based models. Analyze the latest attacker techniques and apply solutions to detect them holistically and stop them proactively. Take a leadership role in driving anti-abuse initiatives across the company. Collaborate with Facebook's leading Machine Learning & Artificial Intelligence teams and apply their innovations to fighting abuse. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS B.S. or M.S. in Computer Science or related field, or equivalent experience 3+ years of engineering experience in one or more of the following areas: abuse, spam or fraud detection, trust & safety Proven ability to perform rigorous data analysis and translate the results into business recommendations. Experience with programming and/or scripting languages such Java, C++, Perl, Python, PHP. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Contributions to the security community (open source, public research, blogging, presentations, etc.). Ph.D. degree in Computer Science or related quantitative field. Experience working with large datasets, using tools such as Hadoop/Hive/HBase/Pig or MapReduce/Sawzall/Bigtable. Experience with anomaly detection, machine learning, recommendation systems, pattern recognition, data mining, content understanding, or artificial intelligence."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LC5FGUA1/", "title": "Internal Solutions Engineer, Business Integrity - Infrastructure", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Business Integrity team ensures safe connections between users and businesses.  We ensure our platform is a high quality ecosystem for users, developers, page admins, advertisers and businesses to create and promote digital content.   The Internal Solutions team within Business Integrity is an applications engineering team focused on solving for tools development or back-end infrastructure problems.  We partner with product and software engineering teams to build proprietary tools and techniques to enforce the quality of all promoted content at scale.  \n \n Successful candidates for this team have a bias toward action and enjoy finding patterns amid chaos, making quick decisions, and aren't afraid of being wrong.  This position is located in our Austin, TX office. RESPONSIBILITIES Work on a global team of technical individuals leveraging technical skills such as PHP, Hack, Haskell + Haxl, JavaScript + React to successfully drive infrastructure & tool improvements for new products + existing processes and workflows Use engineering skill sets in a business organization to drive meaningful business impact by looking at problems through an operational lens Partner with cross-functional teams such as Product and Software Engineering to lead or contribute to large scale strategic projects as well as solve ongoing operational problems at scale Self-identify gaps, problems, needs, and come up with robust solutions with relative independence Be the gatekeeper of system integrity by deep-diving into stability issues and coming up with solutions as well as working to enhance overall code quality MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS B.A. or B.S. degree 3+ years of experience in software development Ability to write readable, and self-documented code Ability to assess, analyze and resolve issues using data, and distill that complexity into concise business insights Ability to communicate with technical and non-technical audiences Experience working with or in support of global communities Experience managing multiple concurrent projects and driving initiatives in a cross-functional environment PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Object oriented experience Quantitative backgrounds"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCBqWUAX/", "title": "Global Leader of Business Integrity, CoreOps", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a senior leader to manage our Business Integrity team\u2019s human review solutions.  This is a core process operations team for our overall Business Integrity organization.  The Business Integrity team protects users and ensures safe connections between users and businesses. This individual will assume management responsibilities in developing our talented team members globally, as well as drive cross-functional impact with our internal and external partners. Internal partners span everyone from planning and forecasting teams and product management to engineering as well as other sub-teams within Business Integrity, while external partners are our outsourcing vendors with a large core operational footprint globally. Candidates will be data driven, self-motivated, and flexible to frequent changes. They are expected to think creatively about nebulous issues and are passionate about problem solving. They will have led teams and will be able to demonstrate a sustained ability to hire and develop talent. They will also be able to work successfully across teams and countries. This role is based in Singapore and reports to the Global Director of Business Integrity. RESPONSIBILITIES Responsible for global teams across multiple locations that manage our core and outsourcing operations for Business Integrity Lead teams that improve Business Integrity\u2019s operations by understanding global and local challenges and needs, building scalable solutions to address business pain-points and identify automation opportunities as we take down malicious actors at scale Develop strong cross-functional partnerships with our global partners within Facebook Play an integral role as a thought leader across the global business integrity and APAC leadership teams to drive the business forward Provide mentorship, guidance and career development to members of their local and global team Identify trends and key insights to drive impact to team goals including user experience and operational efficiency Develop tenured managers to empower them and enable them to manage their teams successfully MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree in an analytical field preferred (such as Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Finance, or similar) 13+ years of experience in online operations/consultancy/analytics or related industries 10+ years management experience, ideally in a role involving strategy, risk management or operations Inspiring global people leader Appetite for intensity and working on some of the most challenging business problems Proven ability to make sound business decisions Ability to drive insight and communicate analyses clearly and effectively Passionate about problem solving and the potential for innovative solutions that online marketing has created Experience working with global teams PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Significant experience leading and developing high performing teams Experience in a fast-paced start-up environment a plus Vendor management experience preferred, but not a must"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoIyzUAF/", "title": "Platform Policy and Integrity Enforcement Specialist", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Our team ensures that applications integrated with our platforms are high-quality and trustworthy. Working closely with other Facebook teams, we investigate and detect apps not compliant with our Platform Policies. Depending on the nature of the violation and the best user experience, we may take a variety of actions; everything from helping the developer/publisher fix the problem, to permanently removing the developer/publisher and application from our platform. We work to improve the platform experience for users, publishers and developers through the use of automated detection tools, strategic manual review, data analysis, guidance, and coordination with product teams. \n \nOur team is looking for a strong team player to work with the external developer and publisher community, investigate and take action on violating apps, and ensure the best possible experience on our platform. In this position, you will interface with internal teams such as Partnerships, Policy, Legal, Marketing and Engineering, as well as with external developers and publishers. Successful candidates will have strong data skills and a bias toward action, enjoy finding patterns amid chaos, making quick decisions and are up for a challenge.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Keep our platforms clean of malicious and non-compliant apps Investigate suspicious developer and publisher behavior and take action where appropriate Identify trend characteristics that can enhance automation Conduct in-depth investigations leveraging large and complex data sets Partner with Product and Engineering teams to solve problems at scale Inform, influence, and execute new strategies and tactics using sound analysis and impact metrics Realize data informed insights to drive new products and initiatives Identify trends to enhance detection, enforcement and support processes and improve team efficiency Manage, coordinate, and/or support policy enforcement projects Proactively investigate and protect app users against malicious activities such as phishing, malware, and fake accounts MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS degree 2+ years analytical and problem-solving experience Experience sourcing and driving insights from internal and external data sets Communication experience Experience thinking both individually and in team environments Demonstrated experience developing and presenting business cases Experience assessing, analyzing and resolving issues Analytical experience, with experience solving problems using data and providing business insights Knowledge of statistical analysis and data tools PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS degree in physical sciences, information systems, or finance Experience coordinating contingent workforce/vendors"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoiqQUAR/", "title": "Director, Business Integrity Operations - Optimize & Scale", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Business Integrity's mission is to ensure safe and trusted connections between people, businesses, and Facebook. Our team works together to anticipate and predict potential threats to our platform, design and build tools to protect against these threats, and then implement and enforce these systems at scale. We leverage data analysis, machine learning and a robust infrastructure to review the quality of promoted content on our platform. We partner closely with several cross-functional teams, including product, engineering, and data science, to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and businesses across the Facebook family of apps. We focus on Ads Integrity, Pages and Commerce verticals and ensure our platform is a high quality ecosystem for users, developers, page admins, advertisers and businesses to create and promote digital content. We are an analytics-driven operations team that thinks upstream to constantly implement solutions at scale through better automation strategies.\n \nWe are seeking a leader to optimize and scale our global Business Integrity operations. Business Integrity is an area of significant investment, and this leader will be responsible for a complex set of workflows and enforcement processes. There is a significant global and cross-functional leadership aspect to this role; the solid-line team, internal partners and outsourced reviewers are based in many locations worldwide. Internal partners span functions such as product, public policy, engineering, legal, and other sub-teams within Business Integrity, while external partners are outsourcing vendors with a large core operational footprint globally. \n \nSuccessful candidates will be self-motivated, operationally rigorous with a high tolerance for nuance and ambiguity, and inspired by frequent changes. They will think creatively about nebulous issues and be passionate about problem solving. They will have led teams and demonstrated a sustained ability to hire and develop talent, with humility and appetite to learn. They will also be able to work across teams and countries. This role is based in either our Menlo Park, CA, Austin, TX, Seattle, WA, or New York, NY office and reports to the Global Director of Business Integrity. RESPONSIBILITIES Responsible for global teams across multiple locations that manage our core and outsourcing operations for Business Integrity Improve risk operations by understanding global and local challenges and needs, build scalable solutions to address user  and business pain-points and identify automation opportunities as we take down malicious actors at scale Develop strong cross-functional partnerships with our key internal stakeholders like global outsourcing, engineering, data science, product management and additional operational teams at Facebook in order to implement optimal solutions to policy related problems and outsourcing needs Lead the team that manages our Outsourcing partners and vendors globally and drive a forward-looking vision Provide mentorship, guidance and career development to members of their local and global team Identify trends and key insights to drive impact to team goals including user experience and operational efficiency MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS degree 14+ years of experience in online operations/consultancy/analytics or related industries 10+ years management experience Experience leading and developing teams Experience as a Global people leader Experience making complex business decisions Experience driving insight and communicate analyses PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree in an analytical field (such as Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Finance, or similar) Experience in a role involving strategy, risk management or operations Vendor management experience Experience working with global teams Experience in a fast-paced start-up environment Appetite for intensity and working on some of the most challenging business problems Passionate about problem solving and the potential for innovative solutions that online marketing has created"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Moj4cUAB/", "title": "Data Scientist, Analytics - Brand Safety & Integrity Lead", "location": "Seattle, WA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Protect the users and advertisers in the ecosystem by proactively identifying and enforcing against low-integrity behavior that ultimately creates poor user experiences, and to create a brand safe environment to increase advertiser trust and transparency.\n \nOne of the key roles of  Facebook monetization team is to support creators that publish great content with monetization products that allow them to build sustainable businesses. As we grow rapidly and connect people, creators, and advertisers, our platform also bears the responsibility to protect all players on the ecosystem from undesirable behaviors. In particular, we want to prevent bad creators from monetizing harmful viral content, game the distribution + auction that crowd out good creators from reaching their audience and full monetization potential. At the same time, we must protect the creators from overly conservative policies that risk negatively impacting their livelihood and our relationship with partner communities. This role will focus on proactively identifying undesirable behaviors and building detections to identify them, and work closely with product, policy, and other integrity teams to implement actions that reduce risk.\n \n RESPONSIBILITIES Provide technical and thought leadership on designing, prototyping, implementing and automating complex analyses Partner with cross-functional teams to identify new opportunities requiring the use of modern analytical and modeling techniques Have a proactive mindset to identify, detect, and mitigate risk to our ecosystem, and be able to clearly articulate a tactical and strategic plan to combat it Effectively communicate insights and recommendations to management in support of strategic decision-making Plan, and be able to conduct as needed, end-to-end analyses, from data requirement gathering, to data processing and modeling Own ongoing deliverables and communications Work with data engineers to architect, develop, and optimize data and modeling pipelines MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS MS degree in a quantitative discipline (e.g., statistics, operations research, econometrics, computer science, applied mathematics, physics, electrical engineering, industrial engineering) or equivalent practical experience 10+ years experience doing quantitative analysis or statistical modeling Working knowledge of at least one modeling framework (e.g., SciKit Learn, TensorFlow, SAS, R, MATLAB) Experience extracting and manipulating large datasets Development experience in any scripting language (PHP, Python, Perl, etc.) Experience in influencing product strategy through data-centric presentations (to product, business, and other stakeholders) Domain experience in the measurement and analysis of system performance PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years experience in technical leadership role Quantitative risk management and policy experience Experience with distributed computing (Hive/Hadoop)"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoRe2UAF/", "title": "Integrity Project Manager, Media Operations (LATAM)", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Media Operations team develops solutions for public figures on Facebook and Instagram by creating scaled systems to address issues impacting their experiences with the suite of Facebook products. The Media Integrity team protects users and ensures safe connections between users and Media constituents. This individual will focus on establishing our integrity support operations for the LATAM region by working to anticipate and predict potential threats and abuse in the media ecosystem, create policies and tools to fight against these threats, and  implement and enforce scaled solutions. We partner closely with several cross-functional teams, including product, infrastructure, and data to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and Media partners. \n \nCandidates are expected to think creatively about nebulous issues and are passionate about problem solving. They will also be able to work successfully across teams and countries, and use their technical and analytical expertise to proactively drive solutions for change and ensure safe and meaningful interactions  across the Facebook family of apps. This role is based in Menlo Park.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Become a subject matter expert in workflows spanning a variety of media integrity disciplines (e.g., policy creation & enforcement, process optimization, measurement & reporting) in order to effectively advocate for operational excellence Build scalable solutions to address market segment, constituent, and legal concerns Identify automation opportunities as we take down malicious actors at scale Develop strong cross-functional partnerships with partnerships, policy, legal, engineering, data science, sales, product management and other operational teams at Facebook in order to implement optimal integrity solutions Improve integrity operations by understanding global challenges and needs, build scalable solutions to address industry segments and constituent pain-points Identify trends and key insights to drive impact to team goals including product, user experience, and operational efficiency MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA or BS Degree 3+ years of experience in online operations, consultancy, analytics or related industries Experience communicating the results of analyses 1+ years of SQL experience Experience working with LATAM markets Fluency in Portuguese or Spanish PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in a fast-paced start-up environment MBA or consultancy work experience"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoNrSUAV/", "title": "Software Engineer, Integrity and Anti-Abuse (WhatsApp)", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": "WhatsApp is a fast, simple and reliable way to talk to anyone in the world. More than 1.5 billion people in over 180 countries use WhatsApp to stay in touch with friends and family, anytime and anywhere. WhatsApp is not only free but also available on multiple mobile devices and in low connectivity areas - making it accessible and reliable wherever you are. It's a simple and secure way to share your favorite moments, send important information or catch up with a friend. WhatsApp helps people connect and share no matter where they are in the world.  Join a world-class engineering-driven company, where you'll have instant impact from day one. WhatsApp has an open culture and flat organization. Every engineer is literally sitting a few steps away from the founders. As a member of our engineering team you will tackle challenging issues of scale, reliability and security while delivering a delightful, simple user experience to a global user base. If you love writing code, hate tons of meetings, then come talk to us. The ideal candidate will have industry experience working and building scalable detection systems on a range of problems that keep spam, fraud, deception, and abuse at bay, and are resistant to adversarial iterations. WhatsApp integrity faces unique problem of fitting abuse without having content. If you want to learn more about our team, you can see the video of a talk describing our main concepts: https://developers.facebook.com/videos/f8-2017/how-whatsapp-reduced-spam-for-over-1-billion-people/ RESPONSIBILITIES Develop situational awareness in a highly adversarial environment and keep WhatsApp anti-abuse capabilities ahead of our attacker Write clean, awesome and bug free code using Erlang, Haskell, PHP to build abuse detection systems Scale servers to handle millions of users Develop system monitoring and instrumentation tools Building ML models for abuse detection MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Experience building abuse detection systems 1+ years of experience in one or more of the following areas: abuse, spam or fraud detection, trust & safety 2 + years experience in either Erlang, Haskell, PHP, C++ Knowledge of Unix internals Experience working in a team BS in Computer Science or equivalent"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Lgnf1UAB/", "title": "Internal Solutions Engineer, Business Integrity - Optimization", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Business Integrity team ensures safe connections between users and businesses.  We ensure our platform is a high quality ecosystem for users, developers, page admins, advertisers and businesses to create and promote digital content.\nThe Technical Solutions - Optimization team within Business Integrity is an applications engineering team focused on developing, implementing and optimizing enforcement business logic through investigations, statistical analyses and modeling.  We partner closely with product and software engineering teams to continuously ensure the quality of all promoted content at scale.  \n \n \nSuccessful candidates for this team have a bias toward action and enjoy finding patterns amid chaos, making quick decisions, and aren't afraid of being wrong.  This position is located in our Singapore office.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Large scale data analysis, applying statistical methods and writing code for enforcement Work on a global team of technical individuals to successfully drive improvements for new products + existing processes and workflows Use analytic and/or engineering skill sets in a business organization to drive meaningful business impact by looking at problems through an operational lens Partner with cross-functional teams such as Product and Software Engineering to lead or contribute to large scale strategic projects as well as solve ongoing operational problems at scale Self-identify gaps, problems, needs, and come up with robust solutions with relative independence MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 6+ years of analytics experience Proficiency in SQL and data analysis Programming experience with a modern language (PHP, Python, C++, Java or Haskell) Critical thinking skills and creative problem solver Ability to communicate effectively with technical and non-technical audiences Experience working with or in support of global communities Experience managing multiple concurrent projects and driving initiatives in a cross-functional environment BA or BS in Engineering or quantitative disciplines such as Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science, Information Systems"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCL4gUAH/", "title": "Business Integrity Escalations Lead, Risk and Response", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  If you like helping people, Risk & Response is for you. The Escalations Manager for Business Integrity will be responsible for managing a high-performing team within Risk & Response's Global Escalations team, ensuring that we build a deep understanding of issues impacting our community, building strong strategic relationship with stakeholders across the business, and providing direction, coaching, and mentorship to a diverse, motivated team of individual contributors and leaders. The Manager will help shape the team's long-term vision, devise and drive global goals, and identify opportunities to drive change to help Facebook provide the best support for the community. The Manager will be responsible for driving relationships with senior partners within various cross-functional teams to drive priorities, anticipate challenges, and mitigate & prevent risk. The will lead a team that will be optimizing processes, solving challenging problems and most importantly, helping to prevent them in future. Helping people and solving challenging, global problems to strengthen and enrich our communities is core to the Risk & Response team. \n\n RESPONSIBILITIES Provide mentorship, guidance and career development to members of your team Lead and enable a high-performing team to deliver on goals by providing superb 1:1 support, and enabling deeper, more scalable solutions Help shape global team vision and establish team goals and work with direct reports and leaders across the organization on strategies for executing, measuring progress and sharing results Deliver projects involving quantitative analysis, industry research, and strategy development, working directly with global cross-functional teams to problem solve and develop solutions Identify actionable insights, suggest recommendations and influence team strategy through effective communication Lead strategic tools, systems, and data projects to help the team analyze trends and delivering insights to define goals and improve processes Build strategic relationships with global and cross-functional teams to understand and anticipate risks to the company, develop global solutions across operations and policy Regularly communicate and interface with senior leadership and global executives in crisis management situations MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Operations domain experience: 4+ years of experience working in large-scale operations, domains such as online operations, escalations, informational systems, compliance, risk management, policy, legal operations or management consulting. Leadership: 1+ years of people management experience Strategic thinker with proven track record of transforming operations to provide customer experience through innovation and continuous improvement Communication: Demonstrated experience influencing across functional boundaries and/or globally. Analytical and problem-solving experience BS/BA Degree PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Prior experience with analytical tools (like Excel, SQL, or R)"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mp4z6UAB/", "title": "Director of Business Integrity Policy Operations", "location": "Dublin, Ireland", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  \nBusiness Integrity's mission is to ensure safe and trusted connections between people, businesses, and Facebook. Our team works together to anticipate and predict potential threats to our platform, design and build tools to protect against these threats, and then implement and enforce these systems at scale. We leverage data analysis, machine learning and a robust infrastructure to review the quality of promoted content on our platform. We partner closely with several cross-functional teams, including product, engineering, and data science, to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and businesses across the Facebook family of apps. We focus on Ads Integrity, Pages and Commerce verticals and ensure our platform is a high quality ecosystem for users, developers, page admins, advertisers and businesses to create and promote digital content. We are an analytics-driven operations team that thinks upstream to constantly implement solutions at scale through better automation strategies. \n \nWe are seeking a leader to manage our Business Integrity team\u2019s policy operations. This person will operate as a key leader and stakeholder within the Business Integrity team and across Facebook\u2019s key cross-functional partner ecosystem, responsible for driving Policy Operations efforts globally. Successful candidates for this team have a bias toward action and enjoy finding patterns amid chaos, making quick decisions, and aren't afraid of being wrong. This position is located in our Dublin, New York, or Seattle offices. RESPONSIBILITIES Improve policy operations by understanding global and local challenges and needs, build scalable solutions to address user and business pain-points and identify automation opportunities as we take down malicious actors at scale Develop strong cross-functional partnerships with key internal stakeholders like policy, legal, engineering, data science, product management and additional operational teams at Facebook in order to implement optimal solutions to policy related problems Responsible for a global team situated across multiple locations Inform, influence, and execute new strategies and tactics as we think about the future of our business Provide mentorship, guidance and career development to members of their team MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS degree Extensive experience in quantitative or engineering disciplines Sihgnificant direct people management experience Communication & project management experience Experience thinking both individually and in a team environment Experience assessing, analyzing, and resolving issues through communication Experience executing and procuring resources to remove roadblocks for the team Analytical experience, with experience understanding and driving nuances with malicious activity, policy needs, new types of products and other needs for the business PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Risk, policy, or online fraud background"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MovaiUAB/", "title": "News Feed Integrity Data Specialist, Community Operations", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Community Operations' focus is on improving the health of our products and helping people understand how to use them through both direct support interactions as well as scalable solutions. Those who join our teams are very passionate about solving people\u2019s issues, and are strong advocates for the Facebook community. We need influencers who can align cross-functional partners to ensure the best possible experience for our platforms. If you like helping people, Community Operations is for you. \n \nThe News Feed Integrity Data Specialists help protect the integrity of Facebook News Feed by leveraging their strong data skills to analyze patterns of activity, investigate trends to help enforce Facebook policies, and build data based case for action. You will work alongside Product Managers, UX Researchers, Data Scientists, Data Engineers, and Engineering Leads to proactively identify and independently lead strategic projects geared towards reducing the spread of false news, misinformation, clickbait, engagement bait, sensationalism, and other types of spammy content. Successful candidates for this role have strong data analytics and stats skills, are efficient critical thinkers and problem-solvers, and are always looking for strategic opportunities to improve how systems and processes work.  RESPONSIBILITIES Cultivate relationships and collaborate with cross-functional partners to shape, support, and execute product goals Ensure product success through targeted product feature development and quality assurance Conduct investigations into integrity abuse to inform product direction or define new enforceable policies Identify and share insights and learnings to develop scalable solutions Manage multiple different work flows and execute on key long-term strategic  initiatives and projects Support new ideas experimentation through ad hoc analytics, framework development, and project structuring MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 2+ years experience doing quantitative analysis 2+ years experience in SQL or Python, R, C++ 2+ years of industry experience in product environment, consulting, analytics, or operations role Knowledge of statistics (e.g., hypothesis testing, regressions) Experience juggling multiple priorities Experience communicating the results of analyses to both technical and non-technical audiences to influence the strategy of the product PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS in Computer Science, Math, Physics, Engineering, Statistics or other technical fields Experience defining measurements and applying statistical analysis to evaluate process performance Ability to assess, analyze and resolve complicated issues, and distill that complexity into simple and concise concepts Threat intelligence, abuse detection and investigation experience Fluency in other languages, including French, Dutch, German, Bahasa, Burmese, Portuguese, Spanish, Hindi"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCF9kUAH/", "title": "Internal Solutions Engineer, Business Integrity - Infrastructure", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Business Integrity team ensures safe connections between users and businesses.  We ensure our platform is a high quality ecosystem for users, developers, page admins, advertisers and businesses to create and promote digital content.   The Internal Solutions team within Business Integrity is an applications engineering team focused on solving for tools development or back-end infrastructure problems.  We partner with product and software engineering teams to build proprietary tools and techniques to enforce the quality of all promoted content at scale. \n \nSuccessful candidates for this team have a bias toward action and enjoy finding patterns amid chaos, making quick decisions, and aren't afraid of being wrong.  This position is located in our Singapore office. RESPONSIBILITIES Work on a global team of technical individuals leveraging technical skills such as PHP + Hack, Haskell + Haxl, JavaScript + React to successfully drive infrastructure & tool improvements for new products + existing processes and workflows Use engineering skill sets in a business organization to drive meaningful business impact by looking at problems through an operational lens Partner with cross-functional teams such as Product and Software Engineering to lead or contribute to large scale strategic projects as well as solve ongoing operational problems at scale Self-identify gaps, problems, needs, and come up with robust solutions with relative independence Be the gatekeeper of system integrity by deep-diving into stability issues and coming up with solutions as well as working to enhance overall code quality MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 3+ years of experience in software development (object oriented experience preferred but not a must) Ability to write elegant, readable, and self-documented code Ability to rapidly assess, analyze and resolve complicated issues using data, and distill that complexity into concise business insights Ability to communicate effectively with technical and non-technical audiences Experience working with or in support of global communities Experience managing multiple concurrent projects and driving initiatives in a cross-functional environment B.A. or B.S. degree (quantitative backgrounds preferred but not a must)"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Moa71UAB/", "title": "Threat Analyst, Research Operations - Business Integrity", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Passionate about diving into the world of big data and trends analyses? If given a vast database, would you find useful information in it and organize it into beautiful charts that tell a compelling story? Interested in solving complex problems that are geared towards improving Facebook and it's community's experiences? Excited about learning how to scale and automate processes? Come join Business Integrity at Facebook! \n  \nThe Business Integrity organization ensures safe and fair connections between people, businesses and Facebook. We are hiring for the Integrity Research Operations team within Business Integrity. This is a team that proactively assesses risks and vulnerabilities on our platform (products and surfaces), policies, tools, and workflows, and helps deploy mitigation strategies. Threat Analysts should have a background and passion for understanding threat intelligence, researching potential exploit scenarios and investigating how global affairs and events affect communities, governments, companies, and technology. Threat Analysts effectively analyze patterns in everything ranging from complex geopolitical trends to business transactions, and effectively communicate them to any audience. Multiple openings are based in our Singapore office. RESPONSIBILITIES Engage with intelligence analyst counterparts around Facebook and work together to spot threat patterns Research and analyze emerging events to provide reports to share with relevant internal teams and senior leadership Develop and maintain a network of sources that will provide compelling insights and foresight into emerging news-worthy developments Collaborate with an internal staff of project managers and analysts to conceptualize and produce impactful, data-driven, and compelling reports MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 6+ years experience researching, investigating, and analyzing trends or developments in global politics, markets, and businesses Fluency in English language The following languages are required for market-specific roles: Burmese/Sinhalese/Bahasa Indonesia/Hindi/any Indian dialects Strong knowledge and experience in either of these markets are a must - Burmese, Sri Lankan, Indonesian or Indian markets Bachelor's degree or equivalent experience Resourceful, self-motivated, and independent with the ability to deal with people of all levels within and outside the company Ability to work productively and communicate with a variety of stakeholders, including organization leaders Ability to work collaboratively and to share knowledge within a fast-moving organization"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MohlKUAR/", "title": "Product Marketing Lead, Marketplace Integrity, Trust & Care", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook seeks a leader who is knowledgeable and passionate about marketplaces to ensure that Facebook remains a safe and trusted environment for businesses and people. This Product Marketing leader will partner closely with Product Management, Operations, and Sales. She or he must thrive as a leader within cross-functional teams, exhibit excellent analytical and communication skills, and have a track record of shaping product strategy and growing product adoption. This is a full-time position based at Facebook headquarters in Menlo Park or Seattle. RESPONSIBILITIES This team informs product strategy in partnership with product management and engineering across multiple product areas and establishes and drives both in-bound as well as the go-to-market plan for every product in the portfolio through the following skills: -Identify long-term opportunities for business integrity and trust based on regional understanding, analysis and a strategic view of the direction of the market both for businesses and consumers -Market assessment and requirements including impact analysis and competitive benchmarking -Represent voice of the market including qualitative and quantitative feedback on product from clients and partners -Lead comprehensive go-to-market strategy including sales and partner materials -Manage high priority, fast-moving decisions and communications regarding policy changes or enforcement MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years experience in marketing, consulting, communications, or internet technology 4+ years experience in the advertising or communications sector and experience contributing at both strategic and operational levels Analytical, data-driven decision-maker Communicator with experience simplifying concepts BA/BS degree PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 3+ years in client facing roles working in a marketplace Product Marketing experience"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LBjbbUAD/", "title": "Business Integrity Escalations Specialist, Risk and Response", "location": "Dublin, Ireland", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Risk & Response Escalations Team coordinates across different internal and external teams to help intelligently scale enforcement and application of Facebook's policies across products like Pages, Ads, & Marketplace. Our team focuses on identifying areas for improvement, optimizing processes, solving challenging problems, and most importantly, helping to prevent them in future. This is an exciting opportunity to help drive impact and strengthen user trust on Facebook and Instagram.\n \nThe Escalations Team is looking for a specialist with a focus on Business Integrity to help Facebook build a high-quality commerce ecosystem for people around the world. We are seeking a team-oriented problem solver who can build strong relationships and thrives in ambiguity. You work well in high pressure situations, and quickly implement solutions, activating partners and subject matter experts as needed. You communicate clearly to various stakeholders, and provide key updates and findings as high priority escalations unfold. RESPONSIBILITIES Investigate reported escalations across multiple channels on Facebook and Instagram Respond to escalated user/press/partner inquiries with high quality, speed, and accuracy Ability to identify gray areas in policies and gaps in processes, and use excellent judgment to resolve those issues Interpret and enforce relevant Facebook/Instagram Community standards and policies Develop and implement scalable solutions to support our global processes Partner with cross-functional teams to improve Community Standards enforcement, quality, reporting and tools Collaborate with policy and product teams to drive continuous process improvements in the interest of improving user experience Remain up to date on key workflow changes, operational guidelines, policy updates and Community Standards Please note that some weekend and holiday work will be required on a shift basis MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 4+ years of experience in online operations, project management or online escalations environment Cross-functional and partnership skills Ability to communicate to a variety of audiences Ability to drive high priority cases through process of resolution Conflict management skills, negotiation skills and a sense of urgency Ability to work with traumatic, sensitive and potentially offensive content PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working with or in support of diverse communities Ability to use and learn tools like SQL and Excel to drive analytics and reporting Bilingual experience Demonstrated experience influencing across functional boundaries and globally Understanding of Facebook Community Standards and policies"}
