 and Instagram Respond to escalated user/press/partner inquiries with high quality, speed, and accuracy Ability to identify gray areas in policies and gaps in processes, and use excellent judgment to resolve those issues Interpret and enforce relevant Facebook/Instagram Community standards and policies Develop and implement scalable solutions to support our global processes Partner with cross-functional teams to improve Community Standards enforcement, quality, reporting and tools Collaborate with policy and product teams to drive continuous process improvements in the interest of improving user experience Remain up to date on key workflow changes, operational guidelines, policy updates and Community Standards Please note that some weekend and holiday work will be required on a shift basis MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 4+ years of experience in online operations, project management or online escalations environment Cross-functional and partnership skills Ability to communicate to a variety of audiences Ability to drive high priority cases through process of resolution Conflict management skills, negotiation skills and a sense of urgency Ability to work with traumatic, sensitive and potentially offensive content PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working with or in support of diverse communities Ability to use and learn tools like SQL and Excel to drive analytics and reporting Bilingual experience Demonstrated experience influencing across functional boundaries and globally Understanding of Facebook Community Standards and policies"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCCxYUAX/", "title": "Business Integrity Escalations Manager, Risk and Response", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Escalations Manager for Business Integrity will be responsible for managing a high-performing team within Risk & Response's Global Escalations team, ensuring that we build a deep understanding of issues impacting our community, building strong strategic relationship with stakeholders across the business, and providing direction, coaching, and mentorship to a diverse, motivated team of individual contributors and leaders. The Manager will help shape the team's long-term vision, devise and drive global goals, and identify opportunities to drive change to help Facebook provide the best support for the community. The Manager will be responsible for driving relationships with partners within various cross-functional teams to drive priorities, anticipate challenges, and mitigate & prevent risk. The manager will lead a team that will be optimizing processes, solving challenging problems and most importantly, helping to prevent them in future. Helping people and solving challenging, global problems to strengthen and enrich our communities is core to the Risk & Response team. \n\nThis is a full-time position, based in the Austin, Texas office. RESPONSIBILITIES Provide mentorship, guidance and career development to members of your team Lead and enable a high-performing team to deliver on goals by providing superb 1:1 support, and enabling deeper, more scalable solutions Help shape global team vision and establish team goals and work with direct reports and leaders across the organization on strategies for executing, measuring progress and sharing results Deliver projects involving quantitative analysis, industry research, and strategy development, working directly with global cross-functional teams to problem solve and develop solutions Identify actionable insights, suggest recommendations and influence team strategy through effective communication Lead strategic tools, systems, and data projects to help the team analyze trends and delivering insights to define goals and improve processes Build strategic relationships with global and cross-functional teams to understand and anticipate risks to the company, develop global solutions across operations and policy Regularly communicate and interface with leadership and global executives in crisis management situations MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Operations domain experience: 4+ years of experience working in large-scale operations, domains such as online operations, escalations, informational systems, compliance, risk management, policy, legal operations or management consulting Leadership: 1+ years of people management experience Proven track record of transforming operations to provide customer experience through innovation and continuous improvement Communication: Demonstrated experience influencing across functional boundaries and/or globally Analytical and problem-solving experience BS/BA Degree PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Prior experience with analytical tools (like Excel, SQL, or R)"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCMKyUAP/", "title": "Manager, Software Engineering - Business Integrity (Ads)", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Ads team at FB helps provide meaningful connections between billions of users and millions of advertisers, and ensures great ad experiences across the family of Facebook Apps (Facebook, Instagram, Messenger, Audience Network, and WhatsApp). As Manager, Software Engineering in the Business Integrity team you will lead an exciting effort helping us create an ecosystem that rewards high quality user experiences and advertiser value.\n \nWe are looking for an extremely entrepreneurial Software Engineering Manager with online advertising knowledge to manage quality and integrity work across Facebook\u2019s suite of apps. A deep understanding of risk, fraud, payments, marketplace, and/or e-commerce technology is a plus, but experience building, launching, and scaling great products is most critical. As a member of the Business Integrity team you'll be responsible for ensuring trustworthy connections between people, publishers and advertisers. You'll be building solutions and systems that improve people's experiences with ads across the platform. This is a full-time position based in Menlo Park, California. RESPONSIBILITIES Manage a team of full stack web/mobile application developers with a variety of languages including but not limited to Java, Objective-C, PHP, React, etc. Be both a highly technical, hands-on coder and effective people manager Communicate cross-functionally and drive growth-focused engineering efforts Hold your own in technical discussion, be a subject matter expert, and have strategic influence MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years of software engineering work experience, including hands-on technical management 5+ years experience coding in one of the following languages: C++, Java, Objective-C, and/or PHP Demonstrated ability to recruit and manage technical teams, including performance management BA/BS in Computer Science (In lieu of degree, 4+ years relevant work experience) PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience with risk, fraud, payments, marketplace, and/or e-commerce technology."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LJpFpUAL/", "title": "Product Management Lead, Harmful Behaviour (Community Integrity)", "location": "London, United Kingdom", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Facebook community is built on a model of trust and safety, and at a scale of over 2B+ monthly active users ensuring and maintaining these values can be an unbelievably motivating and impactful challenge. The Integrity team in London is looking for an experienced PM leader to direct our work minimizing harmful behaviours. There are unfortunately bad actors, and this leadership role is a unique opportunity to leverage technology to minimize and eliminate specific behaviours that lead to real-world harm. With a heavy emphasis on data analysis, industry leading behavioural research, and scalable machine learning models the team is detecting and stopping the use of Facebook for these purposes. \n \nIt is crucial that we foster safe and supportive communities on Facebook. In our latest efforts to keep bad experiences off of our platform, we are now proactively detecting fake and inauthentic accounts that may be trying to scam people (through ML, human review, etc\u2026), including preventing them from even initiating contact when we can.. We also want scammers to know we take this issue seriously and are developing ways to identify scam network coordinators, e.g. the actual criminal behind the scam (not just individual fake accounts).\n \nWe\u2019re looking for a leadership-oriented PM excited by this opportunity for real-world impact and comfortable being both strategic and hands-on to join and direct the teams working on these problems. \n \n \nCompetitive Salary including the following benefits apply:\n \nMedical Benefits\nDental Benefits \nVision Benefits \nPension Benefits \nLife Assurance \nChildcare Benefits \nGym Benefits\nTransport benefits\nLaundry Benefit \nPosted: 21st March 2018\nClosing date: 18th April 2018 RESPONSIBILITIES The initial focus of the team is on financial scams, which is when someone contacts a person on Facebook and cons them into giving money (includes romance scams, lottery scams, etc\u2026). But there are even more serious types of scams, some of which target susceptible populations such as youths, the elderly, etc\n\nWe\u2019re also looking for an experienced team leader capable of hiring and mentoring PM teams. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 8+ years product management experience \n3+ years experience of managing a team of Product Managers\n\nCore skills including delivery of entire products start to finish Exceptional communication and presentation skills Exceptional organisational and analytical skills Understanding of the technical architecture of complex and highly scalable web applications and/or media products Experience designing simple and intuitive user interfaces \u2013 ability to create examples through wire frames and mock ups Experience developing social products, technologies and platforms is strongly desired Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, start-up environment"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LBjb7UAD/", "title": "Business Integrity Escalations Specialist, Risk and Response", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Risk & Response Escalations Team coordinates across different internal and external teams to help intelligently scale enforcement and application of Facebook's policies across products like Pages, Ads, & Marketplace. Our team focuses on identifying areas for improvement, optimizing processes, solving challenging problems, and most importantly, helping to prevent them in future. This is an exciting opportunity to help drive impact and strengthen user trust on Facebook and Instagram.\n\nThe Escalations Team is looking for a specialist with a focus on Business Integrity to help Facebook build a high-quality commerce ecosystem for people around the world. We are seeking a team-oriented problem solver who can build strong relationships and thrives in ambiguity. You work well in high-pressure situations, and quickly implement activating partners and subject matter experts as needed. You communicate clearly to various stakeholders and provide key updates and findings as high priority escalations unfold. RESPONSIBILITIES Investigate reported escalations across multiple channels on Facebook and Instagram Respond to escalated user/press/partner inquiries with high quality, speed, and accuracy Ability to identify gray areas in policies and gaps in processes, and use excellent judgment to resolve those issues Interpret and enforce relevant Facebook/Instagram Community standards and policies Develop and implement scalable solutions to support our global processes Partner with cross-functional teams to improve Community Standards enforcement, quality, reporting and tools Collaborate with policy and product teams to drive continuous process improvements in the interest of improving user experience Remain up to date on key workflow changes, operational guidelines, policy updates and Community Standards Please note that some weekend and holiday work will be required on a shift basis MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 4+ years of experience in online operations, project management or online escalations environment Cross-functional and partnership skills Ability to communicate to a variety of audiences Ability to drive high priority cases through process of resolution Conflict management skills, negotiation skills and a sense of urgency Ability to work with traumatic, sensitive and potentially offensive content PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working with or in support of diverse communities Ability to use and learn tools like SQL and Excel to drive analytics and reporting Bilingual experience Demonstrated experience influencing across functional boundaries and globally Understanding of Facebook Community Standards and policies"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCCxYUAX/", "title": "Business Integrity Escalations Manager, Risk and Response", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Escalations Manager for Business Integrity will be responsible for managing a high-performing team within Risk & Response's Global Escalations team, ensuring that we build a deep understanding of issues impacting our community, building strong strategic relationship with stakeholders across the business, and providing direction, coaching, and mentorship to a diverse, motivated team of individual contributors and leaders. The Manager will help shape the team's long-term vision, devise and drive global goals, and identify opportunities to drive change to help Facebook provide the best support for the community. The Manager will be responsible for driving relationships with partners within various cross-functional teams to drive priorities, anticipate challenges, and mitigate & prevent risk. The manager will lead a team that will be optimizing processes, solving challenging problems and most importantly, helping to prevent them in future. Helping people and solving challenging, global problems to strengthen and enrich our communities is core to the Risk & Response team. \n\nThis is a full-time position, based in the Austin, Texas office. RESPONSIBILITIES Provide mentorship, guidance and career development to members of your team Lead and enable a high-performing team to deliver on goals by providing superb 1:1 support, and enabling deeper, more scalable solutions Help shape global team vision and establish team goals and work with direct reports and leaders across the organization on strategies for executing, measuring progress and sharing results Deliver projects involving quantitative analysis, industry research, and strategy development, working directly with global cross-functional teams to problem solve and develop solutions Identify actionable insights, suggest recommendations and influence team strategy through effective communication Lead strategic tools, systems, and data projects to help the team analyze trends and delivering insights to define goals and improve processes Build strategic relationships with global and cross-functional teams to understand and anticipate risks to the company, develop global solutions across operations and policy Regularly communicate and interface with leadership and global executives in crisis management situations MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Operations domain experience: 4+ years of experience working in large-scale operations, domains such as online operations, escalations, informational systems, compliance, risk management, policy, legal operations or management consulting Leadership: 1+ years of people management experience Proven track record of transforming operations to provide customer experience through innovation and continuous improvement Communication: Demonstrated experience influencing across functional boundaries and/or globally Analytical and problem-solving experience BS/BA Degree PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Prior experience with analytical tools (like Excel, SQL, or R)"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCMKyUAP/", "title": "Manager, Software Engineering - Business Integrity (Ads)", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Ads team at FB helps provide meaningful connections between billions of users and millions of advertisers, and ensures great ad experiences across the family of Facebook Apps (Facebook, Instagram, Messenger, Audience Network, and WhatsApp). As Manager, Software Engineering in the Business Integrity team you will lead an exciting effort helping us create an ecosystem that rewards high quality user experiences and advertiser value.\n \nWe are looking for an extremely entrepreneurial Software Engineering Manager with online advertising knowledge to manage quality and integrity work across Facebook\u2019s suite of apps. A deep understanding of risk, fraud, payments, marketplace, and/or e-commerce technology is a plus, but experience building, launching, and scaling great products is most critical. As a member of the Business Integrity team you'll be responsible for ensuring trustworthy connections between people, publishers and advertisers. You'll be building solutions and systems that improve people's experiences with ads across the platform. This is a full-time position based in Menlo Park, California. RESPONSIBILITIES Manage a team of full stack web/mobile application developers with a variety of languages including but not limited to Java, Objective-C, PHP, React, etc. Be both a highly technical, hands-on coder and effective people manager Communicate cross-functionally and drive growth-focused engineering efforts Hold your own in technical discussion, be a subject matter expert, and have strategic influence MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years of software engineering work experience, including hands-on technical management 5+ years experience coding in one of the following languages: C++, Java, Objective-C, and/or PHP Demonstrated ability to recruit and manage technical teams, including performance management BA/BS in Computer Science (In lieu of degree, 4+ years relevant work experience) PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience with risk, fraud, payments, marketplace, and/or e-commerce technology."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mou4DUAR/", "title": "Risk and Integrity Associate - GMS Partnerships, Systems & Services", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Global Marketing Solutions Partnerships team focuses on accelerating client success through enabling ecosystems, partnerships, and technology solutions. The team manages the diverse ecosystem of companies that provides solutions and services to maximize the performance of marketing on Facebook, Instagram, and Messenger for shared clients. The ecosystem spans 55 countries and ranges from top global agencies to startup ad tech companies in developing markets and works as an integral aspect of Facebook's multi-billion-dollar global advertising business. We succeed when partners help our customers grow their business.\n \nAs a Risk and Integrity Associate in Partnerships, you will be responsible for defining criteria for monitoring risk across partnerships as well as design and build tools to detect violations. You will need to leverage data analysis, machine learning and a robust infrastructure to monitor and review partners for compliance and risk. While other teams build the systems, which oversee specific risk areas, you will need to work across several teams to ensure high quality and safe experiences for both people and businesses across the Facebook family of apps. Successful candidates for this team are adaptable, creative, have a bias toward action, aren't afraid of being wrong, and can successfully work across various teams & countries. You should feel comfortable in a constantly evolving environment in which you have to manage multiple streams of work to drive concrete, actionable solutions for Facebook and its partners.  RESPONSIBILITIES Develop analysis to execute data-informed initiatives that ensure that partners in our program represent the most trusted companies on our platform Apply expertise in quantitative analysis, data mining, and data visualization to see beyond the numbers and pull insights to help identify trends & opportunities to reduce risk to Facebook and clients who leverage our program's partners Be a thought leader for data-informed initiatives and guide the team's direction overall Conduct in-depth investigations leveraging large and complex data sets Partner with cross-functional teams to solve problems at scale Inform, influence, and execute new strategies and tactics using analysis and impact metrics to support your positions MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS in Computer Science, Engineering, Math/Finance, Physics, Economics, Statistics or other technical discipline with experience in a quantitative field Experience with SQL Experience with reporting systems and data pipeline architecture Experience leveraging data to make decisions and solve problems Experience resolving, communicating, and presenting issues & insights to both technical and non-technical audiences Critical thinking and problem-solving experience Experience assessing, analyzing and resolving issues Project Management experience across cross-functional teams PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working and communicating with global teams"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoqVJUAZ/", "title": "Software Engineer, Integrity and Anti-Abuse (WhatsApp - LONDON)", "location": "London, United Kingdom", "description": "WhatsApp is a fast, simple and reliable way to talk to anyone in the world. More than 1.5 billion people in over 180 countries use WhatsApp to stay in touch with friends and family, anytime and anywhere. WhatsApp is not only free but also available on multiple mobile devices and in low connectivity areas - making it accessible and reliable wherever you are. It's a simple and secure way to share your favorite moments, send important information or catch up with a friend. WhatsApp helps people connect and share no matter where they are in the world. \n \nJoin a world-class engineering-driven company, where you'll have instant impact from day one. WhatsApp has an open culture and flat organization. Every engineer is literally sitting a few steps away from the founders. As a member of our engineering team you will tackle challenging issues of scale, reliability and security while delivering a delightful, simple user experience to a global user base. If you love writing code, hate tons of meetings, then come talk to us.\n \nThe ideal candidate will have industry experience working and building scalable detection systems on a range of problems that keep spam, fraud, deception, and abuse at bay, and are resistant to adversarial iterations. WhatsApp integrity faces unique problem of fitting abuse without having content. If you want to learn more about our team, you can see the video of a talk describing our main concepts: https://developers.facebook.com/videos/f8-2017/how-whatsapp-reduced-spam-for-over-1-billion-people/\n RESPONSIBILITIES Develop situational awareness in a highly adversarial environment and keep WhatsApp anti-abuse capabilities ahead of our attacker Write clean, awesome and bug free code using Erlang, Haskell, PHP to build abuse detection systems Scale servers to handle millions of users Develop system monitoring and instrumentation tools Building ML models for abuse detection MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Experience building abuse detection systems 1+ years of experience in one or more of the following areas: abuse, spam or fraud detection, trust & safety 2 + years experience in either Erlang, Haskell, PHP, C++ Knowledge of Unix internals Experience working in a team BS in Computer Science or equivalent"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MookCUAR/", "title": "Software Engineer, Machine Learning \u2013 Integrity and Anti-Abuse", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking Machine Learning Engineers to join our engineering team. The ideal candidate will have industry experience working on a range of classification, ranking and optimization problems, e.g. payment fraud, abuse detection, click-fraud detection, quality-based ranking, bad actor behavior modeling, adversarial ML, or spam detection. The position will involve taking these skills and applying them to some of the most exciting and massive social data, actor and content understanding problems that exist on the web. RESPONSIBILITIES Develop situational awareness in a highly adversarial environment and keep Facebook's anti-abuse capabilities ahead of our attackers Develop highly scalable classifiers and tools leveraging machine learning, data regression, and rule-based models Suggest, collect and synthesize requirements and create effective feature roadmap Apply state of the art ML techniques to a broad range of products and use cases Extend state of the art ML on areas such as actor profiling, content understanding (text, image, video, audio, web) as well as new adversarial ML techniques Analyze the latest attacker techniques and apply solutions to detect them holistically and stop them proactively Take a leadership role in driving anti-abuse initiatives across the company MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS MS degree or Ph.D. degree in Computer Science or related quantitative field 3+ years of industry engineering experience in one or more of the following areas: machine learning, anomaly detection, recommendation systems, pattern recognition, data mining, content understanding or artificial intelligence Experience performing data analysis and translating the results into business recommendations Experience with Hadoop/HBase/Pig or MapReduce/Sawzall/Bigtable Knowledge developing and debugging in C/C++ and Java Experience with scripting languages such as Perl, Python, PHP, and shell scripts"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MomtbUAB/", "title": "Automation Specialist, Media Operations", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Media Operations team develops solutions for partners by creating scaled systems to address issues impacting their experiences with the suite of Facebook products. Within Media Operations, the Media Integrity team protects users and ensures safe connections between Media constituents and their followers. We do so by understanding the landscape, identifying and analyzing problems and trends, and executing scalable solutions. We partner with engineering and other integrity teams to drive solutions. RESPONSIBILITIES Develop a deep understanding of issues facing our constituents and how it affects Facebook, Instagram and our communities Implement effective anti-fraud automation to eliminate abuse based on identified risks Analyze and interpret data in order to devise hypotheses on how fraudulent and other nefarious activity is proliferating Requires contributing to Facebook\u2019s anti-abuse codebase Be a thought leader for data-informed initiatives and guide the team\u2019s direction overall Proactively  investigate, troubleshoot, and resolve sensitive escalations Work collaboratively with cross-functional stakeholders including but not limited to Policy, Communications, Escalations, Spam and other operations teams to solve problems at scale Weekend and holiday work will be required on a shift basis MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree in Business, Science, Engineering, Economics or equivalent practical experience 1+ years of SQL experience 1+ years of experience in at least one scripting language (PHP, Python, Perl), statistical software (R, SAS, SPSS), or data visualization tool (Tableau) 2+ years of work experience in an abuse, investigations, consulting, or online operations environment"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MormuUAB/", "title": "Postdoctoral Applied Researcher, Security & Anti-Abuse (PhD University Grad)", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a Postdoctoral Applied Researcher to help us address the challenges we face in security, integrity, and anti-abuse, and make the platform safer and more secure for our users. Individuals in this role are expected to be recognized experts in security and/or privacy, and to be able to translate their research ideas into practice. The ideal candidate will have a keen interest in producing new science and building systems to protect internet users worldwide.  Term length will be considered on a case-by-case basis. To learn more about our research, visit https://research.facebook.com (https://research.facebook.com/). \n \nObtain and maintain work authorization in the US before employment in 2018. RESPONSIBILITIES Collaborate on research to advance the state of the art in security of social networks. Prototype solutions to enhance the security of Facebook's users and protect them from spam and abuse. Devise novel methods for measuring various types of abuse on Facebook and determining the effect of interventions. Collaborate and increase productivity on existing Integrity projects as a contributing team member. Influence the progress of relevant research communities by producing publications. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Currently has or is in the process of obtaining a PhD degree in Computer Science or related field. Track record of publications that demonstrate experience in a quantitative domain. Experience collaborating within a team to solve analytical problems using quantitative approaches. Experience manipulating and analyzing data from varying sources. Experience communicating research to public audiences of peers. Knowledge of a programming language. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS First-author publications at top-tier security conferences (USENIX, CCS, IEEE S&P, NDSS). Experience conducting original research that can be applied to integrity problems on Facebook."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCT0AUAX/", "title": "Abuse Analyst", "location": "London, United Kingdom", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Passionate about diving into the world of big data and trends analyses? Interested in solving complex problems that are geared towards improving Facebook and its community\u2019s experiences? Excited about learning how to scale and automate processes? Come join Site Integrity at Facebook! The Site Integrity teams uses a state of the art Haskell-based system to prevent spam and abuse from impacting Facebook. We are building an analytics-driven team that thinks upstream to constantly implement solutions at scale through better automation strategies. Our focus on data analysis, machine learning and a robust infrastructure of back-end systems allows us to work effectively with our engineering, operations and product teams to build proprietary tools and techniques to enforce the quality of content at scale. Successful candidates for this team have a bias toward action and enjoy finding patterns amid chaos, making quick decisions, and aren't afraid of being wrong. The perfect candidate will have a background in a quantitative or technical field, will have experience working with large data sets, and will have in-depth experience in data-driven decision making. You are scrappy, focused on results, a self-starter, and have demonstrated success in using analytics to reduce abuse and negative user experiences across the platform. RESPONSIBILITIES Apply your expertise in quantitative business analysis, data mining, and the presentation of data to identify trends and opportunities in driving down spam and other nefarious behavior Analyze and interpret data in order to devise hypotheses on how spam and other nefarious activity is proliferating Implement effective countermeasures to eliminate spam based on these identified patterns Requires contributing to Facebook\u2019s anti-abuse codebase in Haskell. Be a thought leader for data-informed initiatives and guide the team\u2019s direction overall Partner with Data Science, Product, Engineering and Operations teams to solve problems at scale MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 4+ years experience doing quantitative analysis. Experience in functional or scripting language (JavaScript, PHP, Python, OCaml) PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS in Computer Science, Math/Finance, Physics, Applied Economics, Statistics or other technical field. Advanced degrees. Experience in adversarial space like fraud and spam. Experience with data sets and familiarity with SQL. Development experience in Haskell.\nCompetitive Salary including the following benefits apply: Medical Benefits Dental Benefits Vision Benefits Pension Benefits Life Assurance Childcare Benefits Gym Benefits Transport benefits Laundry Benefit Posted: 27/04/2018 Closing: 27/05/2018"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MouUKUAZ/", "title": "Product Policy Associate Manager", "location": "London, United Kingdom", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is looking for a critical thinker with engineering and social media policy experience to join its Public Policy team and support the Community Integrity team. The mission of the policy team is to create and communicate rules for how Facebook products may be used. This role will support Facebook\u2019s integrity engineering team and their Community Operations counterparts, focusing on aligning goals based on data-driven analysis, policy risks, and business priorities.\n  \nIn this role, you will work with teams from across Facebook including Engineering, Operations, Policy Enforcement, Legal, Product and Public Policy teams. You will be responsible for understanding Facebook\u2019s business priorities, policy risks, and operational needs. You will provide on-the-ground policy guidance to Facebook\u2019s integrity engineering and product teams. You will strengthen cross-functional processes and coordinate input from other subject matter experts from across organizations and time zones.\n \nThe ideal candidate will be an excellent communicator and organizer. Candidates must be able to understand and explain technical engineering issues. Candidates must be able to make difficult decisions under pressure while balancing data-driven analyses with stakeholder positions and risks. Candidates must also demonstrate strong leadership and interpersonal skills when organizing and motivating teams. You should be passionate about the services we provide and the people that we serve. \n \nThis is a full-time position located at our London office. RESPONSIBILITIES Build relationships across Facebook engineering, operations and policy teams. Work closely with Engineering teams and cross-functional stakeholders to roadmap and build product, policy and operational solutions to policy issues. Ensure efficient communication and action during policy escalations. Articulate policy philosophy, product launches, and priority changes to relevant parties including management, operations, and other internal and external stakeholders. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelors Degree in Public Policy, Legal, Political Science or related field. 4+ years of work experience in policy, enforcement, or public policy, with an emphasis on technology. Experience in product management or engineering collaboration. Experience in international Internet/social media content issues. Experience with consensus-building between organizations or businesses. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Advanced Degree, MBA, or Law Degree. Experience working at a Tech Company.\n\nCompetitive Salary including the following benefits apply: Medical Benefits Dental Benefits Vision Benefits Pension Benefits Life Assurance Childcare Benefits Gym Benefits Transport benefits Laundry Benefit Posted: Monday 2nd July 2018 Closing date: Monday 30th July 2018"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoLHWUA3/", "title": "Technology Internal Audit Manager", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a manager to join the Internal Audit Technology team to lead operational audits, readiness reviews for newly monetized products and manage risk assessment processes focused on ads and user metrics. The manager will be responsible for evaluating risks and controls around new systems implementation, fraud and integrity tools, data pipelines and machine learning models supporting ads and user metrics calculation. The ideal candidate will have experience working with proprietary in-house built engineering systems, analyzing large data sets, strong technical and project management skills.  RESPONSIBILITIES Operational audits -  Plan and manage complex operational audits including risk assessment, execution and post-remediation validation -  Deliver progress updates and audit results to all levels of management -  Anticipate potential roadblocks and issues and provide suggestions and alternatives -  Partner with cross-functional process owners on control improvements and drive implementation to ensure effective and timely execution -  Administer and manage control self-assessments related to metrics management and disclosures of key user metrics Readiness reviews -  Partner with Engineering, Product, Finance teams to stay informed of product roadmaps and provide input on controls and process requirements -  Participate in system implementations or upgrades to ensure controls are considered and implemented as part of the system design -  Manage relationship with co-sourcing partners, providing direction and ensuring accomplishment of audits and projects -  Collaborate with Internal Audit Fin/Ops team to ensure alignment on audits including coordination on the audit scope, work program, fieldwork and reporting -  Leverage data analytics to enhance audit procedures and build continuous monitoring capability -  Build collaborative and trusting relationships with business partners and cross-functional stakeholders MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS B.S. in computer science, management information systems, business or related field 7+ years of IT auditing, software engineering, data science or similar experience, in addition to project/program management experience Organizational, multi-tasking and prioritization experience Interpersonal, relationship building and collaboration experience Experience in auditing proprietary in-house built systems and working with internet scale data reporting analysis Experience with SQL or other programming languages Demonstrated experience of project management practices, tooling, and managing audit projects through their lifecycle PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS CISA certification Experience working with large data sets and distributed computing (Hive/ Hadoop) Understanding of advertisement, e-commerce, cloud computing, operating systems, web technologies Ability to work in an environment of fast growth and ambiguity and stay on top of business and product changes that could affect compliance requirements"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MosOHUAZ/", "title": "Marketing Researcher", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking an experienced research professional who is passionate about the intersection of technology, civic engagement & democracy to join our Policy insights team. \n \n \nIn this role, you will partner with our product marketing, public affairs, and communication teams to inform outreach programs, product launches, and communication strategies around products designed to improve civic participation of our users, and integrity efforts designed to ensure that Facebook\u2019s platforms play a positive role in democratic processes like elections.  \n \n \nThe ideal candidate will be a qualitative and quantitative marketing research expert who has applied their skills in the public affairs, policy, political or advocacy sphere.   They will have delivered work that has driven strategy and done so with phenomenal analytical, communication, project management skills.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Deliver insights that support a holistic marketing strategy that encompasses audience research, product launch support and proactive marketing campaigns Leverage quantitative and qualitative insights to influence product strategy and inform go-to-market plan Support proactive and reactive communications efforts in the area of elections and civic participation, including the development and refinement of messaging Inform the development of public policy, partnerships and alliances Travel up to 30% of the time MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 8+ years of experience working in consumer insights roles, with 6+ years of experience working in service of policy, public or government affairs, advocacy, or politics. Experience with hands-on design and execution of quantitative and qualitative methods against audiences. Experience with message development and optimization (both generation and testing). Experience with synthesis and summarization of findings for an executive audience. Experience with product marketing including positioning, messaging, and go-to-market planning. Experience with using research to influence executives and colleagues."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mp5G0UAJ/", "title": "Policy Program Manager, WhatsApp Elections", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  WhatsApp Inc., a subsidiary of Facebook, is seeking a Policy Program Manager to lead WhatsApp\u2019s programs in regard to elections throughout the world. This is a great opportunity for someone wanting to make an impact as part of a small, nimble team serving more than 1 billion people around the world. \n \nCandidates should have knowledge of the process of elections, the integrity issues facing countries during elections, and relationships with regulators and civil society groups that work in this space. The person will work closely with the Facebook Policy team and other relevant groups at Facebook. \n \nThis is a full-time position and will be based in our WhatsApp\u2019s offices in Menlo Park, California. RESPONSIBILITIES Develop and execute WhatsApp\u2019s global election program strategy. Identify, monitor, and analyze election-related policy issues affecting WhatsApp at the international, federal, and state level. Represent WhatsApp in meetings with government officials and elected members. Develop policy positions on election-related policy issues affecting WhatsApp. Build coalitions with other organizations to advance WhatsApp\u2019s efforts. Help create innovative programs for outreach to citizens, policy makers, civil society and other influencers. Articulate WhatsApp efforts in briefing papers, consultation responses and internal policy meetings. Advise WhatsApp teams on election-related policy matters to guide development of products, services, and policies. Communicate WhatsApp\u2019s positions at public events and with media. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree in public policy, legal, political science or similar field 10+ years of public policy experience Knowledge of technology and related policy issues Knowledge of electoral law and compliance with electoral laws Experience working on elections outside of the U.S. Fluency in Spanish, French, or Portuguese, in addition to English PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Juris Doctorate degree Experience in Tech Policy"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mp6RqUAJ/", "title": "Recruiting Compliance and Support Specialist", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The People Compliance team provides innovative global HR compliance solutions while driving business value through risk mitigation, proactive program design, and strategic partnerships. As part of that team, the Recruiting Compliance & Support Specialist will play an important part in supporting our Recruiting partners, driving data integrity and identifying solutions to process and systems problems. We are looking for a self-motivated team player to join our efforts to drive best practices while meeting critical SLAs and influencing key stakeholders.  This Specialist role will report to the Recruiting Compliance & Support Lead. RESPONSIBILITIES Maintain support queue within case management system, prioritizing tickets within agreed upon SLA Support Recruiting clients and cross-functional partners with clear and concise technical resolution Partner with Team Lead and colleagues on People Compliance team to assess risk, identify escalations and enable approved exceptions Provide on-going technical end user support for Recruitment systems and processes Assist in managing daily requisition management and candidate management transaction activity Support HR interfaces/integrations and ensure data integrity between systems Identify process and tool improvements and develop solutions to implement with broader team Provide case documentation, including resolutions Perform bug resolution and triage with the appropriate internal and external (vendor) resources Leverage cross-functional SMEs (e.g., Legal, Engineering) for problem solving and issue escalation Perform data analysis and trending of support queue as well as identifying core HR/Recruiting data discrepancies for resolution Identify and remediate recruiting practices that affect data integrity, as well as make recommendations to reduce associated risks MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 3+ years systems technical support experience and/or training 2+ years experience working with Recruiting systems and/or within Recruiting Operations environment Experience navigating between multiple systems and reporting tools Experience managing stakeholder expectations and embedding resources and education into case resolution documentation Experience with customer service or consulting (internal or external) Experience using MS Office tools (Excel, PowerPoint, Word, Visio or other process mapping software) Experience prioritizing workload within published SLA PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in HR Operations, HRIS or HR Compliance Experience with case management system (e.g., Salesforce) Experience with OFCCP record keeping and data retention requirements Salesforce reporting knowledge/experience Experience with knowledge management and/or project management Bachelor\u2019s degree Experience working with or in support of diverse communities"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LgoJDUAZ/", "title": "Head of Global Product Support, Media Operations", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Media Operations team develops solutions for public figures on Facebooks family of apps by creating scaled systems to address issues impacting their experiences with our products. Within Media Operations, the Media Integrity team protects accounts and strives to ensure safe connections between users and Media constituents.\n \n The team is looking for an experienced professional who will provide global strategic and operational leadership by leveraging industry expertise, qualitative and quantitative insights, and inspiring a global workforce to build a supportive and inclusive community for all.\n \nA successful candidate will be able to use these skills along with strong critical thinking, creative problem solving, and impeccable judgment to juggle multiple priorities and make impact in this critical area of our business.  This role is based in Menlo Park, CA. RESPONSIBILITIES Improve support operations by understanding global and local challenges and needs Build scalable solutions to address market segment, constituent, and legal concerns Identify automation opportunities for accuracy and scale Develop strong cross-functional partnerships with legal, policy, Media Partnerships, policy, engineering, data science, sales, product management and other operational teams at Facebook in order to implement optimal solutions Responsible for a distributed team Identify trends and key insights to drive impact to team goals including user experience and operational efficiency Partner closely with the cross-functional product teams to execute seamlessly on our strategy and priorities across each business line and product area Provide mentorship, guidance and career development to members of the team MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA or BS degree 10+ years of experience in product management, program management, online operations, consultancy, analytics, or related industries Experience managing a global distributed workforce of full-time and contract employees Experience communicating the results of analyses Experience working with global teams PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience leading and developing high performing teams Experience in a fast-paced start-up environment"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoquRUAR/", "title": "Strategic Partner Development, News APAC", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a strategic partner development lead to support the Facebook Journalism's Project's Global Strategic Initiatives in Asia Pacific. This person will manage our regional integrity programs and product rollouts, develop and deliver training programs on Facebook tools, and lead regional collaborative product development with the news industry. \n \n \nThis position will be responsible for daily project management and ensuring forward momentum across multiple ongoing initiatives. Success in this position requires an understanding of Facebook\u2019s media products, the ability to work with cross-functional teams and exhibit critical thinking & attention to detail. The ideal candidate has demonstrated success expanding projects into new markets.\n \n \nA strong sense of prioritization and focus, as well as exceptional communication and presentation skills, are a must. The Media Partnerships team is the face of Facebook to our external partners. \n \n \nThis is a full time position based in Singapore, and will require travel. RESPONSIBILITIES Support integrity programmatic and product expansion in new markets Track ongoing regional progress of programs and products Manage multiple working groups, and track progress Draft internal progress reports Manage logistics for partner engagement Draft executive communication & updates Identify trends across partners & advocate for industry needs Be a source of insight for international perspective in the news and integrity ecosystem MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS degree required 5+ years of experience in Publishing or social media and digital media industries Extraordinary organizational and project management skills Ability to work cross functionally with multiple internal stakeholders Understanding of Facebook and the impact it can make for the news media and journalists Communication and presentation skills, and the ability to host public trainings for Facebook Ability to think strategically about issues, leading to recommendations and action plans Entrepreneurial - we\u2019re still only 1% done at Facebook. This team is inventing every day and it takes tenacity, bravery and the ability to see the big opportunities to thrive here Open to regional and international travel"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoJUnUAN/", "title": "Applied Research Scientist, Video Understanding", "location": "New York, NY", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Every day, massive amounts of video are uploaded into Facebook's services. In order to serve our communities better, it is critical that we can understand this content; think about being able to answer questions like \"This person will like this video because....\" or \"This person will find this video inappropriate because...\" Our goals broadly encompass content understanding, including the ability to produce video summaries, categorize content according to topic and purpose, identify audio events, find key-frames, and do keyword spotting. To achieve these goals, we are building a Video Understanding team in New York City, that will engage in a multidisciplinary effort combining speech recognition, natural language processing, and image processing. We view video as inherently multi-modal content, and seek to develop methods that use all the information available. We are looking for researchers in machine learning and AI with strong software engineering skills, and a desire to build systems that will ship to billions of people.\n \nThe Video Understanding Team is part of the Applied Machine Learning organization. The team carries out applied research in ML/AI and designs, develops and deploys state of the art ML/AI algorithms to the rest of Facebook. Our algorithms are used for ranking, improving content integrity, keeping communities safe, and power multiple product experiences across Facebook, Messenger, Instagram, WhatsApp and Oculus. RESPONSIBILITIES Develop highly scalable algorithms based on state-of-the-art machine learning and neural network methodologies Conduct research to advance the state-of-the-art, and publish work in relevant speech, NLP, and machine learning conferences and journals Apply expert coding skills to projects in partnership with other engineers across research, product, and infrastructure teams Adapt machine learning and neural network algorithms for training competitive, state-of-the-art models which make the best use of modern parallel environments (e.g. distributed clusters, GPU) MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS MS degree in Computer Science or related quantitative field with 5+ years of work experience, or Ph.D. degree in Computer Science or related quantitative field Knowledge of machine learning, neural networks, and  deep learning Experience building systems based on machine learning and/or deep learning methods, especially in the areas of speech recognition, natural language processing, image processing, or other machine-perception tasks Experience developing and debugging in C/C++ and/or Python"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoNAoUAN/", "title": "Product Policy Associate Manager, Appeals", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is looking for an analytical thinker with experience in law, policy, program management, alternative dispute resolution, or government to join our Product Policy team. The team\u2019s mission is to create and communicate rules for how our products may be used by people on Facebook and its family of applications. This person will primarily support efforts to let people appeal enforcement decisions related to our Community Standards.  \n \nIn this role, you will work closely with a number of other teams at Facebook, including our Community Integrity, Legal, Public Policy, Marketing, Communications, and other product teams. You will be responsible for understanding our Community Standards and enforcement systems, and recommending changes to ensure that people have a meaningful ability to tell us when they think we have made a mistake.\n \nThe ideal candidate will be able to critically analyze and communicate the costs and benefits of refinements to these policies and practices, as well as manage small-scale projects and programs. You should be passionate about the services we provide and the people that we serve. \n \nThis is a full-time position located at our headquarters in Menlo Park, California. RESPONSIBILITIES Help develop and refine principles and policies for appealing enforcement decisions related to our Community Standards. Work with Legal, Engineering, and other teams to ensure that we are building the right products, organizational structures, partnerships, and systems necessary to ensure meaningful appeals. Build relationships with and understand the perspectives of partners on internal teams such as Community Integrity, Community Operations, Legal, Communications, and Partnerships. Provide ongoing programmatic Policy support to appeals process/partners. Build relationships with and understand the perspectives of partners on internal teams, such as Public Policy, Engineering, Product Management, Communications, Marketing, Partnerships, and Legal. Act as a global escalation point of contact and manage internal communications for policy issues. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelors degree in public policy, legal, political science or related field 6+ years of work experience in law, alternative dispute resolution, public policy, or policy enforcement, with an emphasis on technology Experience in Internet/social media/media content issues Experience with consensus-building Knowledge of Facebook products and principles PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working at a Tech Company or with Tech Clients Experience working on Alternative Dispute Resolution Experience working on Comparative Law/Comparative Legal Systems"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoNAtUAN/", "title": "Product Policy Associate Manager, Appeals", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is looking for an analytical thinker with experience in law, policy, program management, alternative dispute resolution, or government to join our Product Policy team. The team\u2019s mission is to create and communicate rules for how our products may be used by people on Facebook and its family of applications. This person will primarily support efforts to let people appeal enforcement decisions related to our Community Standards.  \n \nIn this role, you will work closely with a number of other teams at Facebook, including our Community Integrity, Legal, Public Policy, Marketing, Communications, and other product teams. You will be responsible for understanding our Community Standards and enforcement systems, and recommending changes to ensure that people have a meaningful ability to tell us when they think we have made a mistake.\n \nThe ideal candidate will be able to critically analyze and communicate the costs and benefits of refinements to these policies and practices, as well as manage small-scale projects and programs. You should be passionate about the services we provide and the people that we serve. \n \nThis is a full-time position located at our headquarters in Menlo Park, California. RESPONSIBILITIES Help develop and refine principles and policies for appealing enforcement decisions related to our Community Standards. Work with Legal, Engineering, and other teams to ensure that we are building the right products, organizational structures, partnerships, and systems necessary to ensure meaningful appeals. Build relationships with and understand the perspectives of partners on internal teams such as Community Integrity, Community Operations, Legal, Communications, Public Policy, Engineering, Product Management, and Partnerships. Provide ongoing programmatic Policy support to appeals process/partners. Act as a global escalation point of contact and manage internal communications for policy issues. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelors degree in public policy, legal, political science or related field 6+ years of work experience in law, alternative dispute resolution, public policy, or policy enforcement, with an emphasis on technology Experience in Internet/social media/media content issues Experience with consensus-building Knowledge of Facebook products and principles PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working at a Tech Company or with Tech Clients Experience working on Alternative Dispute Resolution Experience working on Comparative Law/Comparative Legal Systems"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCNVHUA5/", "title": "Technical Program Manager, Infrastructure Security", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Are you passionate about helping those around you be more effective?  Do you think about technology as a way to increase efficiency and change how business operates?  Are you excited about the opportunity to work on the platforms that keep our infrastructure protected at scale?  We are looking for candidates that share our passion for tackling complexity head-on, to help build integrity platforms that can scale through multiple orders of magnitude.  As a Technical Program Manager, you will play a key role within infrastructure engineering, driving huge projects that span across the company. \n\nRelevant experience is important, but ultimately less than your demonstrated abilities and attitude.  Facebook infrastructure is constantly redefining what is possible, and we need technical program managers who can do the same. RESPONSIBILITIES Manage cross-functional infrastructure security engineering projects in a flat, matrix organization. Build and maintain relationships with internal client teams, and engineering partners across company. Collaborate with engineering teams & and partner teams to gather program scope, and build integrity platform roadmaps. Drive platform roadmaps to align with company and organizational goals. Develop and manage end-to-end project plans to ensure on-time delivery. Design measurements to track impact, drive improvements, and influence cross-functional engineering roadmaps. Create and maintain ongoing communication of planning, project status, issues, and risks in a timely fashion to stakeholders. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS B.S. or M.S. in Computer Science or related field, or equivalent experience. 5+ years of software engineering/systems engineering/security engineering or similar experience. In addition, 5+ years of program management experience. Analytical and problem-solving experience, platforms, large-scale distributed systems, and experience writing code. Interpersonal experience, including relationship building and collaboration, across a flat org, and diverse cross-functional technical teams. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience building platforms, with experience in building malware detection or abuse detection systems. Experience with operating system internals, filesystems, malware analysis, threat intelligence. Experience with programming language design, compilers. Experience with functional languages such as Haskell, OCaml, Erlang or Scala."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MojNUUAZ/", "title": "Public Policy Manager, Content Standards & Practices, News", "location": "New York, NY", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is looking for a Content Standards & Practices Manager for our Watch product to review a variety of News and Entertainment programs at all stages of production and editing. The focus of this role is to ensure programming compliance with our Standards & Practices, as well as Facebook's Community Standards. The candidate will collaborate proactively with both original content producers and Facebook's own News Partnerships Team. \n \nThe ideal candidate will have a proven track record of producing News with the highest journalistic integrity, be a dependable collaborator, and have an understanding of the Television News S&P landscape for both media networks and digital content. \n \nThis is a full-time position located in our New York Office. RESPONSIBILITIES Ensure News programs are fair, accurate and responsible. Collaborate closely with our News Partnerships Team and Productions to manage feedback in all phases of show development and production. Proactively work with show creators in the creation phase to develop creative solutions to ensure compliance with Facebook's Standards & Practices and Community Standards. Provide feedback for scripts and/or cuts to teams internally and creative teams externally. Manage inbound questions from producers, show creators, and writers during production or post-production. Engage with external stakeholders on content issues. Willingness to travel to set for production. Willingness to address content issues relating to news integrity and other related S&P issues like to foul or derogatory language, graphic images, nudity, etc. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelors degree in Journalism, Communications, or other related field 6+ years work experience in Television News as a Producer, Editor and/or Standards & Practices Executive Experience collaborating with internal and external stakeholders to identify and resolve issues Experience with negotiations and influencing mutually agreeable outcomes Experience working with producers, cross-functional teams, colleagues and leadership Experience spotting issues and problem solving Experience managing priorities while delivering results Experience driving innovation at every level PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in both hard and soft news magazine programming Knowledge of the intellectual property and rights management landscape Knowledge of Broadcast News Standards & Practices Knowledge of Entertainment S&P (network and/or basic cable) and the Television Parental Guidelines Advanced degree in Journalism, Communications, or other related field"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCQC7UAP/", "title": "Monetization Product Marketing Manager, Local Trust & Safety", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook seeks an experienced Product Monetization and Marketing Leader who is passionate about small businesses, technology, and platform trust and safety to join the Monetization Product Marketing team, focused on Pages integrity. Facebook\u2019s business platform is only as strong as our users\u2019 trust \u2013 and the tools, processes, and education we have in place to help businesses establish authentic and trustworthy presence on our platform. \n\nThis person will help define and launch solutions to help businesses establish authentic and trustworthy presence and drive meaningful connections with people on our platform. The ideal candidate for this role will be a customer focused leader who can partner cross-functionally across the Local, Advertising, and News Feed product integrity teams to identify opportunities to provide businesses with improved tools and processes to establish and maintain trustworthy presence on our platform and develop go-to-market strategies to bring these solutions to businesses. On this team, you're a big-picture thinker and strategic leader. You understand business\u2019 point of view and ideally have prior experience with and strong opinions on marketplace and business platform trust and safety, small and medium businesses, online presences. She or he must have experience effectively collaborating with cross-functional teams to drive results, and developing and executing against global launch plans marketing to very large numbers of business. Excellent analytical and communications skills and comfort with ambiguity are a must. This is a full-time position located in our Menlo Park office. RESPONSIBILITIES Lead market assessment, quantitative analysis, qualitative feedback, and represent the requirements of the market internally with Product Management and Engineering Demonstrate an understanding of the broader Facebook ecosystem to develop product direction and positioning Lead market segmentation and opportunity assessment efforts to prioritize product opportunities for helping businesses establish a trustworthy presence on our platform Plan and lead cross-functional efforts to drive product beta programs and launches Partner with Product Marketing Communications and all sales channels to create product marketing communications, including all sales-facing materials, press releases, etc. Drive product adoption and usage by developing and managing adoption plans in partnership with Sales, Marketing, and Product MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS degree Experience in analytic fields such as strategy consulting, brand management/online marketing, ad operations, investment banking/venture capital and/or analytics 6+ years of work experience with at least 2 years working in a product marketing or product management capacity (work closely with sales and engineering) PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS MBA Experience with people-to-business messaging products"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LBmG1UAL/", "title": "Manager, Software Engineering - Instagram", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Over a billion people use Instagram, which means jobs here offer countless ways to make an impact in a fast growing organization. Instagram was built to connect people to the people and interests they love. Our app has played a critical part in forming meaningful communities where people can connect with each other and share what matters most to them.  Instagram is a treasure trove of authentic, creative and inspiring content \u2014 every day over 72 million photos are shared by over 172 million people all over the world. These are the world\u2019s most memorable moments expressed by our 400 million strong community of storytellers. \n\nOur Community Engineering team is responsible for the safety and trust of the people who use Instagram. Our mission is to help our community share and consume stories fearlessly, free of spam and abuse. We strive to make our community\u2019s experience on the site as meaningful as the moment captured. \n\nAs we build out our CE team, we\u2019re looking for a leader to drive engineering efforts to detect and eradicate spam and fake accounts, to develop IG\u2019s login and account lifecycle experience, and to build tools to ensure the safety and integrity of our product. The ideal candidate brings an unwavering passion for Instagram and managing the dynamics of a fast-paced and creative environment. RESPONSIBILITIES Provide technical and organizational leadership over the community engineering team Communicate cross-functionally and drive engineering efforts Hold your own in technical discussion, be a subject matter expert, and have strategic influence. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 8+ years of software engineering experience, including 5+ years of hands-on technical management Prior experience in one of the following C++, Java, and/or Python Demonstrated domain experience in spam detection, pattern recognition, authentication systems and data analytics Demonstrated ability to recruit and manage technical teams, including performance management BA/BS in Computer Science (In lieu of degree, 4+ years relevant work)"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LJo8vUAD/", "title": "Product Manager (Growth)", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  With over 2.1 billion people, our community is growing rapidly and the Facebook Growth team is responsible for building products that help make Facebook the largest and most active community on the planet. Facebook Growth Product Managers work with teams of engineers, designers, scientists, and researchers on the company\u2019s hardest problems to create meaningful experiences and connections at incredible scale that help us fulfill our mission. We are looking for world class Product Managers that are entrepreneurial, technical, and highly analytical to innovate and execute across these important products at Facebook. Growth allocation areas include; Community Growth, Community Integrity, Growth Infrastructure, Messenger and Social Good and Goodwill based in our Menlo Park office.\n \n RESPONSIBILITIES Drive innovation and impact through excellent execution with a team of world-class engineers, designers, scientists, researchers Understand, identify and execute on the right people and product problems while building scalable process and infrastructure Define, analyze and ship experiments that inform product strategy and consistently make high priority trade-offs between performance, speed to market, usability, short-term and long-term success Establish shared vision across the company by building consensus on priorities leading to product execution Integrate usability studies, research and market analysis into product requirements to enhance user satisfaction Understand Facebook\u2019s strategic and competitive position and deliver products that are recognized best in the industry Maximize efficiency in a constantly evolving environment where the process is fluid and creative solutions are the norm MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years product management experience Demonstrated organizational and analytical experience Track record of prioritizing, communicating and influencing teams Experience thinking strategically, structurally solving product problems, and simultaneously driving tactical execution 5+ years experience designing user interfaces for mobile and web in consumer domains Proven experience in delivering technology products and services PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience defining and understanding funnel analyses, conversion, consumer acquisition, retention and go-to-market strategies Experience developing social products, technologies and platforms with significant user traction MBA or Master\u2019s in Technology (Computer Science, Computer Engineering)"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LBujYUAT/", "title": "UX Researcher, Pages", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Come join a diverse and collaborative team of researchers who work directly with product design to make the best social platform for Facebook's billion plus users.\n\nThe Pages Integrity team mission is to make Pages authentic and transparent, develop new Facebook Pages policy, and ensure all policy is enforced consistently on Page surfaces. We will also introduce effective tools which help us achieve all of this. For this position, we are looking for a mixed methods research who is passionate about creating a safe and trustworthy ecosystem, with broad skills in both qualitative and design research methods as well as quantitative concepts, including survey design and applied statistical analyses\n\nThe right candidates will be excellent communicators, knowledgeable about UI design, passionate about fostering safe and trustworthy social ecosystems, comfortable in a flat, fast moving organization, excited to collaborate, and focused squarely on impacting the design of Facebook. RESPONSIBILITIES Work closely with product teams to identify research topics Design studies that address both user behavior and attitudes Generate insights that both fuel ideation and evaluate designs Conduct research using a wide variety of qualitative methods and quantitative methods Work cross-functionally with design, product management, content strategy, engineering and marketing Communicate results and illustrate suggestions in compelling and creative ways MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS MS/PhD, human behavior related field (HCI, Psychology, Social Science, Information Science, etc.) 3+ years experience in applied product research Knowledge of a set of qualitative and user-centered design methods Knowledge of quantitative, behavioral analysis, and statistical concepts including survey design and response effects Experience working with large scale data in multi-method studies Ability to ask, as well as answer questions Communication skills"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoqugUAB/", "title": "Strategic Partner Development, News - India", "location": "Mumbai, India", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a strategic partner development lead to support the Facebook Journalism's Project's Global Strategic Initiatives in India. This person will manage our regional integrity programs and product rollouts, develop and deliver training programs on Facebook tools, and lead regional collaborative product development with the news industry. \n \n \nThis position will be responsible for daily project management and ensuring forward momentum across multiple ongoing initiatives. Success in this position requires an understanding of Facebook\u2019s media products, the ability to work with cross-functional teams and exhibit critical thinking & attention to detail. The ideal candidate has demonstrated success expanding projects into new markets.\n \n \nA strong sense of prioritization and focus, as well as exceptional communication and presentation skills, are a must. The Media Partnerships team is the face of Facebook to our external partners. \n \n \nThis position can be based in either Delhi or Mumbai and will involve travel. RESPONSIBILITIES Support integrity programmatic and product expansion in new markets Track ongoing regional progress of programs and products Manage multiple working groups, and track progress Draft internal progress reports Manage logistics for partner engagement Draft executive communication & updates Identify trends across partners & advocate for industry needs Be a source of insight for international perspective in the news and integrity ecosystem MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS degree required 5+ years of experience in Publishing or social media and digital media industries Extraordinary organizational and project management skills Ability to work cross functionally with multiple internal stakeholders Understanding of Facebook and the impact it can make for the news media and journalists Communication and presentation skills, and the ability to host public trainings for Facebook Ability to think strategically about issues, leading to recommendations and action plans Entrepreneurial - we\u2019re still only 1% done at Facebook. This team is inventing every day and it takes tenacity, bravery and the ability to see the big opportunities to thrive here Open to regional and international travel"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MovGeUAJ/", "title": "Strategic Partner Development, News", "location": "Buenos Aires, Argentina", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a strategic partner development lead in Latin America to support the Facebook Journalism's Project's Global Strategic Initiatives. This person will manage our Latin America integrity programs and product roll outs, develop and deliver training programs on Facebook tools, and lead regional collaborative product development with the news industry. This position will be responsible for daily project management and ensuring forward momentum across multiple ongoing initiatives. Success in this position requires an understanding of Facebook\u2019s media products, the ability to work with cross-functional teams and exhibit critical thinking & attention to detail. The ideal candidate has demonstrated success expanding projects into new markets.\n \nThe Media Partnerships team is the face of Facebook to our external partners. This position is full-time and will report to the LATAM Head of News Partnerships in S\u00e3o Paulo. RESPONSIBILITIES Support integrity programmatic and product expansion in new markets Track ongoing regional progress of programs and products Manage multiple working groups, and track progress Draft internal progress reports Manage logistics for partner engagement Draft executive communication & updates Identify trends across partners & advocate for industry needs Be a source of insight for international perspective in the news and integrity ecosystem MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS A strong sense of prioritization and focus, as well as exceptional communication and presentation skills, are a must BA/BS degree required. MBA preferred Fluent in English 10+ years of experience in Publishing or social media and digital media industries Extraordinary organizational and project management skills Ability to work cross functionally with multiple internal stakeholders Understanding of Facebook and the impact it can make for the news media and journalists Communication and presentation skills, and the ability to host public trainings for Facebook Ability to think strategically about issues, leading to recommendations and action plans Entrepreneurial - we\u2019re still only 1% done at Facebook. This team is inventing every day and it takes tenacity, bravery and the ability to see the big opportunities to thrive here Open to regional and international travel Fluency in English and Portuguese or Spanish"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCPqPUAX/", "title": "Marketing Research Lead", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  This is an exciting time at Facebook, and the role of Insights is impacting the business greater than ever. The Lead Marketing Researcher will be an integral part of the marketing team, and will lead research for Facebook\u2019s News, News Feed, Integrity, and Sharing teams.  These teams are responsible of for some of the most important issues facing Facebook and society.   \n\nIn this role, you will design, execute and deliver high-impact primary quantitative and qualitative research to influence  corporate policy, product go-to-market strategy, press communications, and marketing programs.   The ideal candidate will combine marketing research expertise, strategic consulting, product thinking, and organizational savvy. \n \n  \nYou\u2019ll partner with Product Marketing and Communications to understand the needs of key audiences and help inform marketing programs and product launches core to the reputation of Facebook.   As part of the launch process you\u2019ll work to position products strategically for success with a particular focus on benefit articulation, messaging and creative. \nCreativity, energy, flexibility, leadership, collaboration, and a passion for innovative research are a must. If you're invigorated by understanding the role social media has on how people get information and build relationships, this could be the right role for you. If you're excited by current events, the opportunity for shape public discourse and make a real and substantial impact, we want to speak with you! RESPONSIBILITIES Design and execute innovative quantitative and qualitative research to support the marketing organization and Facebook at large. Core focus will be on developing marketing and communications strategy. Translate research findings into actionable insights that will have an effect on reaching hundreds of millions of people. Leveraging research, you will establish product market fit, shape positioning and messaging, drive creative briefs, inform the development of product level or company level narratives, or answer urgent executive level questions impacting the business. Develop and mentor a small team of high performance researchers. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 10+ years of qualitative and quantitative primary research experience on client or supplier side. Experience on the front end of the marketing process. Demonstrated quantitative and qualitative experience including hands-on experience in Survey and Discussion Guide writing, Quantitative and Qualitative Data Analysis. Experience with Positioning, Message Development and Optimization, Value Proposition Development and Communications Checks. Track record of using primary and secondary research to influence executives and colleagues. Problem solving experience and experience moving from blank slate to a research problem matched with a methodology. Synthesis and storytelling experience to bring data points together into a strategy. Knowledge of brand and advertising research. Experience directing agencies/vendors to deliver results. Experience executing quantitative research from questionnaire design, fielding, analytics, and reporting. Communication and presentation experience. Experience developing and managing research teams. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Passion for Facebook Intellectual curiosity for in the ways social media is shaping public discourse, news, and politics Keen interest in new ways of sharing, communication and maintaining relationships"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoNuuUAF/", "title": "Software Engineer, Machine Learning (WhatsApp)", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": "WhatsApp is a fast, simple and reliable way to talk to anyone in the world. More than 1.5 billion people in over 180 countries use WhatsApp to stay in touch with friends and family, anytime and anywhere. WhatsApp is not only free but also available on multiple mobile devices and in low connectivity areas - making it accessible and reliable wherever you are. It's a simple and secure way to share your favorite moments, send important information or catch up with a friend. WhatsApp helps people connect and share no matter where they are in the world.  Join a world-class engineering-driven company, where you'll have instant impact from day one. WhatsApp has an open culture and flat organization. Every engineer is literally sitting a few steps away from the founders. As a member of our engineering team you will tackle challenging issues of scale, reliability and security while delivering a delightful, simple user experience to a global user base. If you love writing code, hate tons of meetings, then come talk to us. WhatsApp Integrity team is seeking Machine Learning Engineers to join our small team. The ideal candidate will have industry experience applying machine learning techniques in a range of classification and optimization problems. The position involves taking these skills and applying them to prevent abuse on WhatsApp.  RESPONSIBILITIES Develop highly scalable classifiers and tools leveraging machine learning, data regression, and rules based models Adapt standard machine learning methods to new problem domains to prevent abuse on WhatsApp Write clean, awesome and bug free code using Erlang, Haskell, PHP, C++ Work with multi-node cluster handling live traffic Develop system monitoring and instrumentation tools MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Experience using and training Machine Learning models 2 + years experience in either Erlang, Haskell, C++ or Python Programming Experience building and scaling distributed, available systems Knowledge of Unix internals (especially FreeBSD and Linux) Experience working in a team BS in Computer Science or equivalent"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MowqoUAB/", "title": "Technical Program Manager, Metrics", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Our mission is to prevent people from having negative experiences on Facebook due to product or platform abuse. We build large scale, complex systems and operate an infrastructure to enable detection and remediation of content and behaviors that violate our Community Standards. We do this on a global scale across the full suite of Facebook products. \n \nAs a Technical Program Manager, you will play a key role within infrastructure engineering, driving huge projects that span the organization. You will work across all teams working on Community Standards abuse detection to enable reliable metrics that will inform our product strategy. You will closely partner with the platform engineering team to build data sets and data governance processes to provide end-to-end tracking of the overall integrity work across the organization. \n \nAre you passionate about helping those around you be more effective? Do you think about technology and data as a way to increase efficiency and change how a business operates? We are looking for candidates that share our passion for tackling complexity head-on, to help build platforms that can scale through multiple orders of magnitude. This is a full-time position based in our office in Menlo Park and will report to the Group Technical Program Manager. Our team is global so some travel is expected. RESPONSIBILITIES Manage cross-functional infrastructure software engineering programs in a matrix organization covering a range of areas. Develop and manage end-to-end project plans and ensure on-time delivery. Provide hands-on program management during analysis, design, development, testing, implementation, and post implementation phases. Perform risk management and change management on projects. Provide day-to-day coordination and quality assurance for projects and tasks. Drive internal and external process improvements across multiple teams and functions. Interface with Engineering and business owners for project requirements and scope. Help drive product decisions to align with higher company initiatives. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS B.S. in a Computer Science or equivalent experience. At least five years of software engineering, systems engineering, program/product management, or similar experience. Experience in backend reliability, efficiency, quality and/or performance work. Communication experience and experience working with technical management teams. Organizational, coordination and multi-tasking experience. Analytical and problem-solving experience, experience to large-scale systems and experience writing code/queries. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience with data governance, data quality, data mapping, monitoring, Six Sigma Experience with building systems to power and operationalize top line business metrics Experience delivering ML-based products Working knowledge of statistical concepts: confidence intervals, statistical bias, systematic and random errors"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Moj5fUAB/", "title": "Technical Program Manager, Instagram Well-being", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Over a billion people use Instagram, which means jobs here offer countless ways to make an impact in a fast growing organization. Instagram was built to connect people to the people and interests they love. Our app has played a critical part in forming meaningful communities where people can connect with each other and share what matters most to them.  Join a collaborative and passionate team working to make Instagram the safest, kindest, and most supportive global community. The Instagram Well-being team focuses on reducing negative and promoting positive experiences on Instagram, in addition to feeling cared for and supported when facing a negative or challenging experience on the platform.  We build large-scale, complex systems, state-of-the-art Machine Learning, and operate an infrastructure to enable detection and remediation of content and behaviors that violate our Community Guidelines. As a TPM on Instagram Well-being, you will develop deep subject matter expertise in our integrity areas of work, then leverage your expertise as you work with a number of product, engineering, and operations teams to build experiences that ensure Instagram remains a safe, kind, and supportive community. \nTechnical Program Managers are a group of passionate individuals who go deep on learning their teams\u2019 systems, then leverage this technical knowledge to influence and drive cross-team projects and roadmaps. TPMs work horizontally to create long term value for Instagram by promoting the right technologies for productivity, stability, and growth. Well-being TPM's are expected to have an understanding of the safety, security, and wellbeing of the community, as well as the systems that enable this ecosystem. The right candidate will be an excellent communicator, knowledgeable in mobile product development, passionate about the wellbeing of the community, excited to collaborate, and focused on advancing Instagram engineering and products. This is a constantly evolving space, and the TPM is expected to be flexible and pivot based on the problems we are trying to solve. \nThis is a full-time position based in our office in Menlo Park, CA. RESPONSIBILITIES Articulate the technology, requirements, goals and milestones of Well-being initiatives Drive internal process improvements across multiple teams and functions, remove roadblocks, and deliver on high impact projects that align with the company mission and goals Develop programs to measure the efficacy of engineering, machine learning, and content classification efforts Develop and manage cross-functional programs in a matrix organization covering a range of areas Facilitate relationships across teams at Instagram and Facebook to manage dependencies and maximize resources Collaborate with Engineering and Product Management to define roadmap and long-term strategy for the Well-being organization Roadmap and communicate program updates, risks and new opportunities to leaders and stakeholders Identify dependencies and perform risk/change management on projects Drive accountability and ownership in a fast-paced environment through project planning and interpersonal skills MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS B.S. in a technical discipline or equivalent experience 2+ years of technical program management experience, systems or software engineering experience Experience working with technical engineering teams, designers, cross-functional teams and senior management to build and deliver products Communication, coordination, and organizational experience Interpersonal and leadership experience, including relationship building and collaboration within a cross-functional team and collaborating to reach goals Analytical and problem-solving experience to large-scale systems and experience writing code PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in using technology to detect and action online integrity related issues Ability to get things done in a fast-paced environment that spans multiple offices Self-motivated, proactive with demonstrated creative and critical thinking capabilities"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LgmlaUAB/", "title": "Strategic Intelligence Analyst", "location": "Washington, DC", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a Strategic Intelligence Analyst to join our Integrity, Investigations, and Intelligence team. The candidate will be responsible for helping Facebook understand and anticipate how the intersection of geopolitical dynamics and security risks impact the people who use Facebook's products, and help guide the company in its responses to these threats. The candidate will work cross-functionally with partners across the organization, and their analytic insights will be applied to make Facebook and its users more secure through product and policy changes. The potential for impact with this work is substantial, as outcomes could affect the billions of people who use our products. Analysts will have the opportunity to work on some of the most challenging, complicated, and high-visibility security risks the company is facing.\n \nThe perfect candidate will have a multidisciplinary analytic background, with at least some experience in quantitative or technical fields and data-driven decision making.  It is highly important candidates are focused on results, and are self-starters.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Conduct  research and analysis on the intersection of geopolitical and security risks as they apply to the Facebook platform and its community of users Design,  develop, and produce analytic products and risk reports based on  geopolitical, demographic, and social data points Collaborate on requirements solicitation and gather feedback from internal Facebook stakeholders Manage multiple research projects at once while effectively prioritizing time Work closely with the investigations and threat detection staff and other teams within  the company MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 2+ years of post-college work in an analytic role with experience conducting technical and non-technical investigations Experience working with large data sets and assimilating all-source inputs Experience creating research requirements and developing new tradecraft and tooling to meet research needs Experience understanding the intersection of global security risks Experience thinking critically and properly qualifying assessments with communications Proven track record of managing and executing on short-term and long-term projects Experience setting and managing expectations with key stakeholders and team members Experience communicating and establishing rapport with a global team Experience prioritizing and executing with minimal direction or oversight PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor\u2019s degree in political science, economics, international relations, or regional studies Knowledge with SQL or other data analytics programming languages Familiarity and experience working in the context of an intelligence organization in private or non-government sector Deep-dive regional studies and language skills Experience with an Internet-based company"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MohCgUAJ/", "title": "Research Review Program Manager", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Our fast-growing group of Research Program Managers build and scale global research programs to strengthen the impact of our world-class Research team. We do this by implementing operational systems, connecting teams and knowledge, and problem solving operational hurdles to enable Researchers to do their most impactful work. In this position you will use a full range of organizational and interpersonal skills that help our talented teams operate at their highest and most effective level. \n \nThis particular Program Manager role is a new role, with an opportunity for someone to build on and improve our survey research review process and resources. The main responsibilities for this role are to own and evolve the logistics and monitoring of our internal and external facing survey research review processes. You will liaison with internal partner team members and external research vendors to build the right tooling and processes to support our survey research reviews and to refine and adjust it as necessary. You will also develop educational and training materials for Researchers and aid in monitoring the quality and integrity of the survey research review process. You will oversee and facilitate the training of our staff research reviewers, and schedule staff researchers to provide consistent research reviewer availability. \n \nThis role requires project management experience and broad knowledge of research\u2019s impact on product development. Communication skills, ability to manage complex logistics, and an organized approach are mandatory. This is a full-time position based in our Menlo Park office.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Program Management and Education -Act as the lead for research review operations, managing and maintaining the logistics of internal and external research review processes -Develop, maintain, monitor and refine processes, including training for staff research reviewers -Aid and monitor project management tooling and processes for research review -Predict obstacles and establish solutions to overcome challenges -Move initiatives forward, find resources, raise concerns to owners early and resolve open issues that prevent progress -Hold the line when progress is in jeopardy while maintaining relationships -Collaborate on other research team programs and initiatives -Travel up to 15% (domestic and international) as needed Internal Team Liaison -Manage relationships with Corporate Communications, Legal, Policy and Privacy teams -Receive updates from these teams and participates in translating these into educational and training materials -Communicate regularly to ensure all stakeholders are aware of updates to processes, rules and regulations -Track and maintains training of staff research reviewers to ensure uninterrupted research review coverage -Track the performance of the research review process against benchmarks and communicates performance metrics to research leadership MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 4+ years of program or project management experience 2+ years\u2019 experience working with research Experience managing survey collection market research projects Experience with communication, organization and juggling multiple priorities Track record of operating independently and delivering results PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Knowledge of regulatory compliance processes Research review process management experience"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCJsrUAH/", "title": "Manager, Risk Investigations, Risk & Payment Operations, APAC", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Our Risk & Payments team\u2019s purpose is to enable anyone, anywhere to pay and be paid with confidence. To help us achieve this mission, we are adding an additional Investigations leader. The Investigations team is responsible for the integrity of all payments across all Facebook, Instagram, Messenger, and Oculus. We are responsible for managing transactional risk at Facebook. We build, monitor, and analyze key performance metrics, and understand root causes of change. Investigators are responsible for performing quantitative analysis (e.g. data mining and machine learning) to understand how fraud is proliferating on the Facebook platform, and for implementing effective countermeasures. We partner with Data Science, Product, Engineering, and Operations counterparts to implement solutions that scale. You\u2019ll be leading a team of analysts responsible for monitoring, understanding and building a scalable payments ecosystem.\n \nWe are looking for a manager to drive the team\u2019s direction as well grow the skills and professional development of each individual. Our ideal candidate is passionate about data, has a track record of influencing change within large organizations, and loves developing people.\n \n \n \n \n RESPONSIBILITIES Lead our global R&P team to drive measurable business outcomes enabling product adoption while minimize risk exposure Provide expertise in career planning, performance management, and coaching Drive team-wide results, determine what is important, clarify next steps and delegate effectively to meet expectations Be an active member of our leadership team, helping to drive the broader organization forward Work with Risk Leadership team to determine team\u2019s project roadmap and priorities while holding accountable to milestones and delivery deadlines Be a company-level expert and advocate for Risk Operations, coordinating across partner teams including Data Science, Product, Engineering and Operations Become an expert in core risk infrastructure, tools, systems, and data Collaborate with our product, partnerships, and sales teams to ensure we are meeting our operational, service and revenue goals Represent Risk Operations for all cross functional partners in APAC MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 3+ years managing people preferred 5+ years experience with financial fraud, risk mitigation or payments integrity Experience with relationship management and working within a global organization Experience with strategic thinking with an analytical and problem solving approach"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCWnAUAX/", "title": "Systems Project Manager, Community Operations", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Community Operations' focus is on improving the health of our products and helping people understand how to use them through both direct support interactions as well as scalable solutions. Those who join our teams are very passionate about solving people\u2019s issues and are strong advocates for the Facebook community. We need influencers who can align cross-functional partners to ensure that the people who use Facebook have the best possible experiences, and when they don\u2019t that they receive quality support. If you like helping people, Community Operations is for you. \n  \nFacebook is looking for a full-time team member to join the Community Operations Infrastructure team. We value both 1:1 interactions with users and driving solutions at scale, and we count on Systems Project Managers to balance these needs. \n RESPONSIBILITIES Become a technical expert on all automation and routing systems across Community Operations Support the building and debugging of this infrastructure as needed Diagnose, troubleshoot and escalate tool bugs to Community Integrity Engineering Analyze weekly bug reports and collaborate with Tool Bugs coordinator Consult with CO teams to solve workflow problems and ensure internal tools and automation systems are fully leveraged Collaborate with peers in developing and prioritizing comprehensive, data-driven tool improvement requests (includes communicating the status and priority of all requests to local teams, Community Operations Engineering, Community Integrity Engineering and global System Project Manager partners) Analyze trends in tool improvement requests and automation requests and work with the Tools team to raise core problems to Community Integrity Engineering and the Community Operations Engineering Team Build strong relationships with an offsite manager and global team Address sensitive content issues, including but not limited to graphic images, videos and writings, offensive or derogatory language, and other objectionable material. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS degree or international equivalent 4+ years of project management experience Experience communicating to a variety of audiences Analytical-thinking and problem-solving experience PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Ability to work autonomously, set agenda and prioritize work with minimal input Proven ability to collaborate and communicate across a global team Experience with data analysis or internal tools Prior technical experience (PHP, SQL) Knowledgeable in driving solutions for global operational teams Time management and multitasking abilities"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LByEXUA1/", "title": "Enterprise Engineer, JAVA/JS", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook\u2019s Business Applications team is responsible for building integrated, scalable, and robust enterprise applications. As a member of BizApps, you will play a key role in re-imagining productivity by shipping transformative products that serve diverse aspects of the enterprise.\n\nThis full-time position will be based in our Menlo Park, CA RESPONSIBILITIES Work  with product managers to drive strategic and tactical initiatives Architect highly available, scalable, and secure systems Build features in their entirety Comply with change management policies to ensure data integrity and system stability Understand performance metrics for business value Build interfaces for complex systems and high-quality tools Passionate about UI/UX and that should reflect in your work Technical ownership of projects and managing resources MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BS in Computer Science or equivalent experience Experience building and supporting production quality software Experience owning projects from end-to-end 1+ years working with a relational database SQL experience in handling volumes of data, performance tuning Experience in understanding code bases, including API design techniques 1+ years programming in Java, Oracle ADF or Javascript technologies such as ReactJS or AngularJS 1+ years experience with object-oriented software development Experience using web services, SOAP, REST APIs, GraphQL Experience developing  web or mobile applications Experience partnering with designers to implement pixel-perfect designs PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working with or in support of diverse communities"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000ModJSUAZ/", "title": "Technical Program Manager, Core Data Science", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Through our growing family of apps and services, we're helping billions of people around the world connect and share what matters most to them, including discussing political issues and connecting to their elected representatives. To help provide valuable insight into the role of social media in politics, an Election Commission has been formed, which will support independent academic research on the topic. \n \nAs a Technical Program Manager, you will be driving a project that spans the organization in order to enable this new model of research collaboration between the academic community and industry. The collaboration will need to ensure data quality and security as well as user privacy. This is a full-time position based in our office in Menlo Park. RESPONSIBILITIES Manage cross-functional teams to enable election integrity research. Develop and manage end-to-end project plans and ensure on-time delivery. Provide hands-on program management during analysis, design, development, testing, implementation phases. Perform risk management and change management on projects. Provide day-to-day coordination and quality assurance for projects and tasks. Drive internal and external process improvements across multiple teams and functions. Interface with data scientists, engineers, internal and external teams for project requirements and scope. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS M.S. in Statistics, quantitative social science, computer science, or equivalent experience. At least 10 years of research, program/product management, policy management or similar experience. Knowledge with quantitative research methods. Communication experience and experience working with technical management teams. Organizational, coordination and multi-tasking experience. Analytical and problem solving experience, knowledge to systems and experience writing code/queries. Knowledge of research or data privacy issues. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience with data governance, data quality, and data mapping. Experience with data tools such as SQL, R, Python, or similar. Experience working with Governments or NGO's supporting research. Experience with processes to provide public access or open source information. Consulting experience."}
