rience in understanding code bases, including API design techniques 1+ years programming in Java, Oracle ADF or Javascript technologies such as ReactJS or AngularJS 1+ years experience with object-oriented software development Experience using web services, SOAP, REST APIs, GraphQL Experience developing  web or mobile applications Experience partnering with designers to implement pixel-perfect designs PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working with or in support of diverse communities"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Moda0UAB/", "title": "Application Developer, Salesforce", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook\u2019s Customer Insights team is responsible for building integrated, scalable, and robust enterprise applications. As an Application Developer, Salesforce, you will play a key role in re-imagining productivity by shipping transformative products that serve Facebook's Sales & Marketing teams.  RESPONSIBILITIES Work with product managers to drive strategic value through custom applications built on http://force.com/ Architect highly available, scalable, and secure systems Comply with change management policies to ensure data integrity and system stability Understand performance metrics for business value Build interfaces for complex systems and high-quality tools Technical ownership of projects and managing resources MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 3+ years of experience developing http://force.com/ (http://force.com//) business applications 3+ years of experience with http://salesforce.com/ Web Services APIs - http://force.com/ SOAP and REST-based Web Service APIs, the Bulk API, and the Metadata API 1+ years of experience in Visualforce/Apex incorporating JS frameworks like React, Bootstrap or Angular PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS BS in Computer Science Platform Developer II certification Experience building and supporting production quality software Experience owning projects from end-to-end Expertise with data management - structured and unstructured DBs, SQL and RDBMS technologies, SOA design principles SQL experience in handling volumes of data, performance tuning Experience in understanding code bases, including API design techniques Passionate about UI/UX and that should reflect in your work"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mp0poUAB/", "title": "Security Engineer, Malware Analysis", "location": "Washington, DC", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook Security is looking for a Security Engineer, Malware Analysis with experience in malware analysis, reverse engineering, and detection. You will be creating protections for Facebook's users and infrastructure. You will advance Facebook's mission of making the world more open and connected by quickly identifying and analyzing threats that aim to collect sensitive/proprietary information or disrupt our business. We are looking for someone that is passionate about ripping apart binaries, discovering their intention and secrets, and creating signatures to hunt and proactively defend against threats. RESPONSIBILITIES Surface and triage novel malware on our platform, corporate networks, and third party submissions In-depth malware analysis to support threat intelligence, incident response, and application integrity Create signatures (file, host, network) to detect, hunt, and prevent malware compromise Create tooling to increase our ability to triage, respond, and understand malware Advise and consult with other teams as a subject matter expert MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Experience with static and dynamic analysis tools for multiple systems and file formats Knowledge in system internals for one of: Windows, macOS, Android, Linux, and iOS Knowledge with machine code in one or more architectures (x86, ARM, other) Knowledge with multiple file formats Experience creating host or network based signatures (Yara, ClamAV, Suricata) Experience developing parsers or decoders based on malware analysis Experience analyzing and decoding network traffic Experience in at least one of PHP, Python, C++, or Java BA/BS in Computer Science or 3+ years similar work experience PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience with campaign tracking, threat intelligence, and TTPs of advanced actors Experience with relational databases and SQL Experience analyzing and processing large data sets Demonstrated ability to work cross-functionally with different teams Expertise in system internals for multiple systems Expertise with machine code in multiple architectures Knowledge with multiple file formats (PE, CDF, PDF, etc.)"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MouLnUAJ/", "title": "Systems Project Manager", "location": "Dublin, Ireland", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Community Operations' focus is on improving the health of our products and helping people understand how to use them through both direct support interactions as well as scalable solutions. Those who join our teams are very passionate about solving people\u2019s issues and are strong advocates for the Facebook community. We need influencers who can align cross-functional partners to ensure that the people who use Facebook have the best possible experiences, and when they don\u2019t that they receive quality support. If you like helping people, Community Operations is for you. \n \nFacebook is looking for a full-time team member to join the Community Operations Infrastructure team. We value both 1:1 interactions with users and driving solutions at scale, and we count on Systems Project Managers to balance these needs. \n RESPONSIBILITIES Become a technical expert on tooling, automation, and routing systems across Community Operations (CO) Build strong relationships with a global team and stakeholders Collaborate with peers in developing and prioritizing comprehensive, data-driven tool improvement requests (includes communicating the status and priority of all requests to local teams, Community Operations Engineering (COE), Community Integrity (CI) Engineering and global System Project Manager partners) Consult with CO teams to solve workflow problems and ensure internal tools and automation systems are fully leveraged Collect and scope business requirements and translate to development-ready technical requirements Analyze trends in tool improvement requests and automation requests and work with the Tools team to raise core problems to CI Engineering and the COE Team Proactively strategize with CO stakeholders to create longterm workflow roadmaps Diagnose, troubleshoot and escalate tool bugs to Community Integrity Engineering MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/ BS degree or degree level working equivalent experience 3+ years of project management experience Experience communicating to a variety of audiences Analytical-thinking and problem-solving experience PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Ability to work autonomously, set agenda and prioritize work with minimal input Proven ability to collaborate and communicate across a global team Experience with data analysis or internal tools\n\n\nPrior technical experience (PHP, SQL)\n\n\nKnowledgeable in driving solutions for global operational teams\n\n\nTime management and multitasking abilities"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mp30OUAR/", "title": "Recruiter, FB+ AR/VR", "location": "Los Angeles, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Recruiting is a core strategic driver of Facebook\u2019s success. We have a world-class team working together to help drive our ambitions and scale to the next level. We conceive practical and creative ways to surface leading talent, and we invest a great deal of time activating passive candidates through a highly engaged approach. We\u2019re passionate about delivering an awesome candidate experience, and that starts with the first conversation a candidate has with us.  \n \nOculus, Building 8, Camera, and Social VR are some of the organizations that make up what we at Facebook call FB+. It is the goal of these teams to create and ship new, category-defining consumer hardware and software products that are immersive, social, and define our consumer\u2019s daily experiences. We want to enable people to experience anything, anywhere. As a team of world-class experts, we drive innovation in the areas of augmented and virtual reality, artificial intelligence, connectivity, and more.\n \nAs a member of our team, you will be responsible for building and cultivating talent pipelines for our hiring needs and will be instrumental in our ability to scale our business and reach our mission of enabling people to experience anything, anywhere.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Manage full cycle recruiting for multiple, complex searches, creating innovative sourcing strategies and engagement to bring the best talent to each role Develop and execute fully comprehensive sourcing plans, analyzing requirements to determine target profile needs and matches Drive offer process - including extending offers, negotiations, closing candidates, and generating offer letters Collaborate closely with hiring managers throughout the recruiting process to ensure we meet their hiring needs and goals Regularly manage pipeline activity and maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders Facilitate and lead meetings and key initiatives and projects with client groups, and with the recruiting teams, that will continuously improve and scale our recruiting operations and results Establish and maintain meaningful relationships with management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, HR, Compensation, and Diversity teams) Coordinate closely with recruiting team members to innovate our research strategy for talent pooling, market mapping and competitor analysis MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years full-cycle technical recruiting experience Experience with sourcing and finding, engaging and activating passive candidates Experience with candidate care and balancing process with a candidate experience Knowledge with recruiting tools, applicant tracking systems, data management/reporting techniques and software collaboration tools Experience partnering and working with leadership and executive teams Experience with communication and working cross-functionally"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoagoUAB/", "title": "Data Center Security Manager", "location": "Newton County (Atlanta Metro), GA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Data Center Security Manager is responsible for reducing risk, responding to incidents and overall direction & leadership of the on-site security team. Supports and executes global physical security programs, initiatives, processes and best practices to build a safe and secure environment. Builds strong cross-functional partnerships across the data center team and Facebook by communicating team goals, wins and opportunities to maximize safe and secure work environments. Cultivates external partnerships with local and state law enforcement, federal agencies, third party vendors and community organizations. \n \nThis position will be located in Newton County and will be responsible for security at other Infrastructure locations within the region and may take on other responsibilities based on subject matter expertise. RESPONSIBILITIES Directly leads the on-site security team at the data center Develops and maintains local standards and procedures to ensure execution of Global Physical Security strategies to include enforcement of business conduct and integrity standards, employee safety and security, investigations, crisis response, business continuity and security and government partnerships Regularly communicates updates to key partners on incidents, emerging risks, and other issues that may impact Facebook\u2019s data center operations, employees, or vendors Works closely with the Global Security Operations Center and the Global Security Investigations and Intelligence Team to anticipate, identify and evaluate risks that carry a significant risk to Facebook\u2019s data center(s) Establishes and monitors performance metrics to determine team effectiveness: budget management, performance metrics and contract management Deliver training on security topics, assist in the coordination of security services to support planned and unplanned operations, and support incident investigation efforts MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5 + years of site/campus security management experience Planning, organizational, and motivational experience Experience drafting in technical and non-technical formats Experience presenting both extemporaneously and in formal settings Experience in root cause analysis, industry benchmarking, survey evaluation and data interpretation Experience in the areas of emergency/disaster management, physical security, critical incident stress management, risk management and business resiliency Experience with emergency procedure protocols and regulatory interfaces Knowledge in physical security strategies, principles, standards, policies, and procedures Experience with security technologies including Video Surveillance, Access Control, and Incident Management Systems, Security Operations Centers PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor\u2019s degree. ASIS Certified Protection Professional (CPP) and/or Physical Security Professional (PSP) certifications. Safety & Security management experience in a Data Center environment. Experience working with or in support of diverse communities."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MozDWUAZ/", "title": "Vendor Relationship Specialist, Chargebacks", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The mission of the Facebook Risk and Payments team is to enable anyone, anywhere to be able to pay and be paid with confidence. This can mean different things across our many payments products - from providing support to advertisers who need help paying their bill, helping charities onboard to receive donations, to identifying and resolving fraudulent transactions. We are looking for a strong individual contributor who can use data to drive insights that will help fuel the success of payments at Facebook.  RESPONSIBILITIES Ensure successful implementation of payments and chargebacks vendor solutions and drive projects to completion through effective project management practices. Conduct business reviews, measure vendor performance, and establish plans for continuous improvement. Ensure timely delivery and quality of data from vendors by reviewing key metrics and through identifying opportunities for continuous improvement. Understand the strategies, product roadmaps, and initiatives of key internal stakeholders and provide assistance wherever necessary. Monitor trends and patterns across the payments industry to identify potential risks and emerging technologies to evaluate new potential partners. Maintain the integrity and accuracy of project information to meet team, management and portfolio requirements. Work with a variety of different stakeholders (internal and external) to help gain alignment, synthesize information, and bring information together into a cohesive plan. Work directly with local issuers and payment partners to optimize payment performance and minimize chargebacks. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BS/BA degree in a quantitative discipline such as math, statistics, computer science. 2+ years of relationship or project management experience in the online payments ecosystem including payment processing operations and chargebacks. Organizational and project management experience. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience manipulating large data sets in SQL or equivalent and drawing actionable insights from data."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Momc2UAB/", "title": "Recruiter, APAC", "location": "Hyderabad, India", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Recruiting is a core strategic driver of Facebook\u2019s success. We are looking for a strong Recruiter to help redefine the way we recruit as we move into the next evolution of Facebook. As a Recruiter you will define and execute the talent acquisition strategy and execution. RESPONSIBILITIES Design and execute customized, full cycle staffing plans, partnering closely with hiring managers to achieve the best results possible Find and engage unique and/or passive candidates through creative sourcing techniques, coordinating with our sourcers as needed Facilitate and lead meetings and key initiatives and projects with client groups, and with the recruiting teams, that will continuously improve and scale our recruiting operations and results Regularly manage pipeline activity and maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders Establish and maintain meaningful relationships with management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, Compensation, and HR teams) Collaborate with others on the recruiting team on initiatives and/ or hiring needs that may spike in other areas Leverage and maintain data reports and performance metrics to drive improvements as needed MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years of relevant recruiting experience with a search agency or an in-house recruiting team Experience in full cycle recruiting across multiple functions Ability to consult, influence, and manage a range of stakeholders Experience in developing complex compensation packages and general HR requirements as related to hiring Consultative qualities and interpersonal skills with ability to communicate across all levels of the organization as well as externally Self-starter who can operate effectively in a fast-paced environment and navigate ambiguity independently Strong attention to detail and the ability to prioritize competing demands Strong problem-solving, data analytics and reporting skills"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCBR7UAP/", "title": "Risk Assessment Investigator, Risk and Response", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Risk Assessment team seeks to identify and prioritize emerging external risks, lead investigations probing our systems to evaluate these risks, deliver action-oriented assessments to benefit our partners (advertisers) and users, and conduct post mortem investigations to provide critical insights to our internal cross functional stakeholders. \n\nWe're seeking a Risk Assessment Investigator with a passion for uncovering risks and easily adopt an independent perspective when making evaluations. Our Business Risk Investigators will focus on risks within ads and commerce, while our Community Risk Investigators will focus on content-based risk. Successful candidates will excel at project management, as well as creating and delivering compelling risk assessments to key partners.      RESPONSIBILITIES Conduct investigations to bring deeper understanding and knowledge of potential risk areas to our community and/or ads and commerce Use quantitative & qualitative research methods to perform root cause analyses on investigative findings or high priority escalations Work with key stakeholders to identify community and/or ads risks from a news, policy, communications, and safety perspective Develop a framework for prioritizing perceived community and/or ads risks that need to undergo deeper investigation Shape how we approach offensive investigations as an external actor that pressure tests our community support and/or integrity systems Identify and recommend improvements to policies, processes, systems, and products that mitigates risk to the company Synthesize investigative findings through the creation of reports and presentations that provide a coherent narrative assessing external risk Address sensitive content issues, including but not limited to content relating to offensive images and writings, offensive or derogatory language, or other offensive or controversial material MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 4+ years experience in investigations, content enforcement, online ads, public policy, press management, or internet safety Analytical-thinking and problem-solving experience Experience operating strategic projects with cross-functional partners Experience driving cases through process to resolution Communication: demonstrated experience influencing across functional boundaries and/or globally -Experience communicating results of analyses with partners and leadership teams to influence the strategy of those teams PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in international internet/social media ads or commerce issues Ability to use and learn tools like SQL and Excel to drive analytics and reporting"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MombsUAB/", "title": "Recruiter, Japan", "location": "Tokyo, Japan", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  As \u2018one team\u2019, People@ focuses on three major areas: hire the best people, foster continuous personal growth and enrich the overall Facebook experience. Our culture is our most important asset, and as the keepers of that culture, we\u2019re seeking folks who share our values of moving fast, openness and impact. As a member of our recruiting team, you will conceive practical and creative ways to engage leading talent. We\u2019re passionate about disrupting the typical recruiting process in hopes to move faster. Our team takes an empathetic and transparent approach, driven and motivated to be knowledgeable partners to our candidates and hiring managers. We are collaborative in problem-solving, with high resourcefulness and tenacity in challenging situations. RESPONSIBILITIES Design and execute customized, full cycle staffing plans, partnering closely with hiring managers to achieve the best results possible Find and engage unique and/or passive candidates through creative sourcing techniques, coordinating with our sourcers as needed Facilitate and lead meetings and key initiatives and projects with client groups, and with the recruiting teams, that will continuously improve and scale our recruiting operations and results Regularly manage pipeline activity and maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders Establish and maintain meaningful relationships with management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, Compensation, and HR teams) Collaborate with others on the recruiting team on initiatives and/ or hiring needs that may spike in other areas Leverage and maintain data reports and performance metrics to drive improvements as needed MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 6+ years of relevant recruiting experience with a search agency or an in-house recruiting team Ability to consult, influence, and manage a range of stakeholders Experience in developing complex compensation packages and general HR requirements as related to hiring Self-starter who can operate effectively in a fast-paced environment and navigate ambiguity independently Strong attention to detail and the ability to prioritize competing demands Strong problem-solving, data analytics and reporting skills Must be fluent in Japanese and business fluency in English"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MozfeUAB/", "title": "Security Engineering Manager, Malware Analysis", "location": "Washington, DC", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is in search of the world\u2019s most creative and experienced engineering leaders. We embrace entrepreneurs as well as those who come from more established organizations. Facebook\u2019s Malware Analysis team is seeking an experienced Security Engineering Manager to help keep our two billion users safe from real world threats. You will lead a team of malware reverse engineers to analyze malicious binaries across our entire corporate and product ecosystem, help improve automated analysis, and craft detection for new threats.  We are looking for a candidate with a passion for security and the knowledge that it begins with people.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Manage a team of high-performing security engineers conducting malware analysis Develop a roadmap for future work, track progress against it, and evaluate the team's performance Hold your own in technical discussion, be a subject matter expert, and have strategic influence Identify new techniques and solutions which increase the team's ability to provide solutions for customers Provide mentorship, support, and career development opportunities for team members and enable the team to scale Work with Internal Security, Product Integrity, and Infrastructure teams to divide and conquer challenges related to malware from a broad spectrum of actors Solutions will be required for everything from low-level but persistent actors to nation state actors Build strong relationships with internal partners to identify and facilitate solutions to increase the impact of the team's work Contribute to the growth and development of the Infrastructure organization MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Experience in at least one of PHP, Python, C++, or Java Demonstrated experience in malware analysis, threat detection, forensics, which may include incident response, software development, threat intelligence, or other similar endeavors Demonstrated experience recruiting and managing technical teams, including performance management Experience translating technical concepts into language that is known to audiences, including software engineers, business and technical leaders and external security community members and press BA/BS in Computer Science or 4+ years similar work experience"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoK71UAF/", "title": "Product Manager - Applied Machine Learning (AML)", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  With over 2.1 billion people, our community is growing rapidly, and at this scale, we cannot fulfill our mission without cutting-edge AI systems that operate at unprecedented scale.\n \nFacebook's AML PMs work with industry\u2019s leading researchers, engineers, designers, and data scientists to build deeper and richer understanding of all content and people across Facebook's family of apps. And apply this understanding to solve the company\u2019s hardest problems including showing more relevant content and ads on Facebook and Instagram, keeping people safe by reducing misinformation and hateful content, and powering Facebook\u2019s latest VR/AR products. Be world class with running conclusive experiments quickly to validate hypotheses.\n \nIf you're passionate about driving the next set of AI breakthroughs that will make people lives better, we want to talk to you.\n \n RESPONSIBILITIES Build the vision, strategy, and roadmap of AI big-bets that Facebook should invest in to drive step change impact for our products. Shape the direction of Facebook's core products by applying cutting-edge AI innovations to tackle people problems such as reducing integrity issues, making content and ads more relevant, and improving search amongst many others. Build new AI technologies, services, and platforms for areas such as computer vision, NLP, speech/audio, and personalization that operate at Facebook scale and power all Facebook products. Accelerate time to impact on new technologies through experimentation, prototyping, and strong execution. Have a clear pulse on innovations across the broader AI community and help us identify new opportunities and look around corners. Identify and track key success metrics for all of your products. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Experience in applying ML technologies such as computer vision, NLP, speech/audio knowledge of products or building personalized experiences. Communication experience with experience conveying technical topics to the audience. Execution experience to drive multiple projects. A strategic thinker who can help craft plans to multiple stakeholders. A collaborator who can work across operating styles and can bring together multiple perspectives. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience developing social products, technologies, and platforms Experience building new AI/ML technologies BA/BS"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MozEwUAJ/", "title": "Leadership Recruiter, US Business", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  As a member of our team, the Leadership Recruiter owns and drives the recruiting process from end-to-end. We work consultatively with our hiring managers to partner and develop strategies to find top tier leadership candidates for our Business functions: HR, Legal, Facilities, Security, Partnerships and HR. We\u2019re also passionate about delivering an exceptional candidate experience that lends genuine insight into our culture and what it\u2019s really like to work here. We\u2019re seeking a dynamic recruiter who brings a balance of creativity, focus and determination to our team. RESPONSIBILITIES Design and execute customized, candidate recruiting plans, partnering closely with sourcers, coordinators and hiring managers to achieve the best results possible Find and engage unique and/or passive candidates through creative sourcing techniques, coordinating with our schedulers as needed Regularly manage pipeline activity and maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders Establish and maintain meaningful relationships across management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, HR, Compensation, and Diversity teams) Regularly track pipeline, priorities and performance data to share with internal stakeholders Collaborate with others on the recruiting team on initiatives and/or hiring needs that may spike in other areas Work with leadership recruiting manager to develop and execute a recruitment approach focused on the relevant businesses and candidates Conduct direct market research and develop market and talent updates for management and business owners MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 7+ years of full cycle recruiting experience 4+ years of leadership recruiting experience Experience independently partnering with leadership on hiring initiatives domestically and globally Experience in compensation and general HR requirements as related to hiring Experience working in a team-based environment Knowledge of executive search strategies and talent acquisition Negotiation, influencing and communication experience PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working with or in support of diverse communities"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LC5FlUAL/", "title": "Internal Solutions Engineer, Product & Service Operations", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Product & Service Operations team supports millions of businesses by resolving their product support needs while using our ad products and ensures that businesses have a great experience while advertising on Facebook. The Internal Solutions team within Product & Service Operations is an applications engineering team focused on solving for tools development or back-end infrastructure problems.  We partner with product and software engineering teams to build proprietary tools and techniques to provide support at scale and enforce the quality of support for all of our advertising products. \n \nSuccessful candidates for this team have a bias toward action and enjoy finding patterns amid chaos, making quick decisions, and aren't afraid of being wrong.  This position is located in our Menlo Park, CA office. RESPONSIBILITIES Work on a global team of technical individuals leveraging technical skills such as PHP + Hack, Haskell + Haxl, JavaScript + React to successfully drive infrastructure & tool improvements for new products + existing processes and workflows Use engineering skill sets in a business organization to drive meaningful business impact by looking at problems through an operational lens Partner with cross-functional teams such as Product and Software Engineering to lead or contribute to large scale strategic projects as well as solve ongoing operational problems at scale Self-identify gaps, problems, needs, and come up with robust solutions with relative independence Be the gatekeeper of system integrity by deep-diving into stability issues and coming up with solutions as well as working to enhance overall code quality MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS B.A. or B.S. degree 3+ years of experience in software development Ability to write readable, and self-documented code Ability to assess, analyze and resolve issues using data, and distill that complexity into business insights Ability to communicate with technical and non-technical audiences Experience working with or in support of global communities Experience managing multiple concurrent projects and driving initiatives in a cross-functional environment PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Object oriented experience Quantitative background"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MowsGUAR/", "title": "Operations Lead (Oculus)", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": "As the Marketing organization continues to grow, we're looking for an experienced Operations Lead to join the Oculus Marketing team - the team that designs product and program identities, creates product launch assets, builds marketing campaigns, and develops collateral for internal and external events. The successful candidate must have experience managing product marketing projects, operations, and logistics in a fast-paced Internet or online marketing company; problem-solving capability; and global integrated experience in live action, digital, and animation production (from production to editorial to finishing and delivery). He or she must thrive within cross-functional teams, excel at building and managing relationships with internal partners and stakeholders, and exhibit organizational, communication and financial management skills. Must have a proven track record for instituting tools that teams are bought into and improve workflow. Must be a flexible cross-functional manager comfortable with a fast-paced, often ambiguous, start-up environment.\n \nThis is a full-time position based at headquarters in Menlo Park, and will report to the Director of Production for AR/VR.\n \nThis role will partner closely with the rest of the Oculus leadership team to resource business needs and deliver world-class marketing materials. This is an outstanding opportunity for thought leadership in establishing, implementing, and improving department process.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Build and optimize systems, tools and standards to improve how the marketing organization works together, with cross-functional partners, and external vendors and contractors Create business partnerships with leaders of all levels and departments within the Product Marketing organization Manage inbound and outbound projects to ensure successful delivery of various product launches Facilitate all facets of campaign delivery, from resourcing, brief creation and creative development to production, cross-functional feedback and approvals, launch and reporting Manage production budgets and approvals Help prioritize projects with Marketing Leadership based on impact, company objectives and resources Manage relationship and project management responsibilities for strategic sourcing and procurement Support various marketing/creative operations related work including, but not limited to: recruiting, people programs, learning and development Maintain brand integrity across all project deliverables Manage tight deadlines across multiple teams and projects MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Demonstrated marketing operations and logistics experience in the web technology sector and experience contributing at both strategic and operational levels Track record of driving innovative changes in operational processes Experience working with Product Marketing, Creative Agencies and Production companies Experience in Excel, Oracle, and Keynote PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Is a manager with organization and people skills and the ability to set priorities, problem-solve, multi-task and work in a dynamic, rapidly changing environment BA/BS degree"}
