ng team on initiatives and/or hiring needs that may spike in other areas MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Min. 5+ years of full cycle recruiting experience with a search agency or an in-house recruiting team, with a specific focus on technical fields (e.g software, hardware, networking or related) Experience independently partnering with leadership on hiring initiatives Experience in compensation and general HR requirements as related to hiring Experience working in a team-based environment Self-starter who can operate effectively in a fast-paced environment and navigate ambiguity independently Ability to manage multiple searches through strong project management and prioritization skills Strong attention to detail and the ability to prioritize competing demands Strong problem-solving, data analytics and reporting skills"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LJuIFUA1/", "title": "People Systems Program/Project Manager (LMS)", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Global People Operations team strives to create and deliver a seamless and positive employee experience across the entire employee lifecycle. Leading with care and empathy, we develop efficient and simple people processes, systems, policies, and programs. We deliver data that is useful and accurate to create People-related strategies across the business. We manage people knowledge and build project management capability across our company. Our work also ensures Facebook remains protected and compliant. We strive to ensure employees feel heard and given the resources and support they need during the most important moments during their careers.\n \nThis role is responsible for the successful operation of the company-wide HR systems & Tool.  The successful candidate will work to drive optimum learning efficiency and experience for our employees by working closely with our People Tools & Engineering teams for support, design, development, implementation, delivery, and maintenance of the HR Eco systems. You will guide the product road-map through definition of features, enhancements, fixes and other functionality by understanding our internal stakeholder's needs and defining the future strategy to exceed them!\n RESPONSIBILITIES Manage the Learn Tool priorities and roadmap while working closely with business stakeholders to determine requirements, and prioritize for the development team Collaborate with the Product Manager and Engineers on day to day bugs, features and priorities Lead systems migration, integration, and change management of People Tools Seek out improvements to our processes and activities cross-functionally to create best possible learning experience for users Keep current with HR tool trends and developments and apply learning to improve internal tool and processes Provide support for compliance internal/external audits Develop an adoption, communications, and change management strategy for roll-out and ongoing changes to tools Develop and implement a support structure and recommendations for tool management and ongoing strategy (e.g. data integrity, usability, etc.) Make recommendations on program changes and conduct cost/benefit analysis of potential improvements Develop business and cost justifications for program initiation and funding approval Lead design and review sessions with technical and functional resources at all levels, including members of management Lead the cross-functional Learn project and working groups Consult as the subject matter expert with partners and users to find solutions Investigate and evaluate opportunities to improve work flows and delivery models to increase efficiency and delivery velocity MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 8+ years of project management experience in a HR/Operations/Technology environment Experience in building and driving strategy for People tools, including manager and employee facing solutions Experience working with multiple stakeholder groups to implement tool/system changes Experience with change management specific to a tool implementation Experience resolving any blockers in projects or initiatives underway that are impeding program Experience understanding concepts and make decisions with data Experience working with both engineering and end-user groups to identify, prioritize and scope tool requirements Experience in the PMI Project Management Body of Knowledge (PMBOK) Experience with project methodologies such as Agile, Scrum, Kanban, and Waterfall PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS People management experience Technical background Experience with implementing Learning and Development processes and systems: Workday, Cornerstone, Taleo, Greenhouse, SuccessFactor, SAP , Oracle, and PeopleSoft Experience working with both engineering and end-user groups to identify, prioritize and scope tool requirements Product management experience or experience in an HRIS/HRIT role Experience implementing solutions (out of the box) or custom built tools"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mouq1UAB/", "title": "University Recruiting, Recruiter", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  University Recruiting is in our DNA. From our start in a dorm room at Harvard, Facebook has looked to talent from universities to build the next set of new products for our 1 billion+ users that drive our mission to make the world more open and connected. The result is an opportunity to have tremendous impact at a revolutionary company. If you've ever dreamed about disrupting and revolutionizing the way recruiting and university recruiting is done, we'd love to talk with you about how you might help Facebook do just that. We are looking for someone to leverage our platform and products and to partner with the broader University Recruitment team to help us develop a stronger and more diverse pipeline that represents our global users. We take Facebook's mission of discovering top talent and serving our employees seriously. RESPONSIBILITIES Manage end-to-end recruitment process for both university and intern hiring, ensuring a smooth and positive candidate experience Collaborate with business leaders and hiring managers to understand hiring needs and goals, and to develop, implement, and execute a custom hiring strategy Identify and engage unique and/or passive candidates through creative sourcing techniques Drive offer process - including extending offers, closing candidates, generating offer letters Foster relationships with key stakeholders at targeted universities Regularly manage pipeline activity and maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders Act as an internally and externally-facing representative of Facebook and our talent acquisition team Establish and maintain meaningful relationships with management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, HR, Compensation, and Diversity teams) Collaborate with others on the recruiting team on initiatives and/or hiring needs that may spike in other areas Partner with other university recruiting team members to collaborate on campus recruiting efforts Willingness to work flexible hours as needed Ability to travel during peak recruiting cycles MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Communication experience Experience working cross-functionally Experience communicating across all levels of an organization, as well as externally PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Bachelors Degree or higher 2+ years University Recruiting experience Strong attention to detail Ability to multi-task"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoZSFUA3/", "title": "VP, Vendor & Workforce Management, Community Operations", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is searching for a VP with a proven track record of transformational impact on best-in-class experience and service excellence, risk mitigation and staffing efficiency in large-scale global operations environments. This global operation spans across several thousand staff to lead our vendor and capacity planning/workforce management functions. We are looking for a  leader who can help continue to scale the impact and efficiency of our workforce, drive alignment and advocate for infrastructure and compliance investments across Ops, Engineering, Policy and Security functions  to leadership and has a track record of building and scaling high-performing teams. A successful candidate will deeply connect with Facebook\u2019s commitment to keep our community safe, prevent real-world harm and be able to partner across a wide set of functions to deepen our risk mitigation capabilities through leveraging, scaling and optimizing our global workforce and building a strong leadership bench.  RESPONSIBILITIES Shape vision on how to scale and transform large-scale service, risk and compliance operations including location and business continuity strategy, site expansion, workforce management and CRM tooling. Drive alignment on staffing, infrastructure, tooling and facility investments with leadership across Ops, Engineering, Policy, Security and Finance functions. Define and execute on strategies to maximize impact and efficiency of our global workforce on service and community safety as well as company risk mitigation objectives across a broad set of Ops functions in partnership with Engineering and Ops stakeholders while delivering best-in-class community experience. Forecast and optimize OPEX budget through long-term staffing forecasting and execution of hiring across multiple languages, rep skills, and partner locations. Optimize short-term staffing through interval level forecasting, scheduling, and intraday management and implement mechanisms to maximize schedule adherence and staffing efficiency. Ensure all known projects impacting the workforce are analyzed, assessed, prioritized and accounted for in both long-term and short-term forecasts so they can be launched effectively with minimal disruption to ongoing community support. Partner with resilience experts to ensure best-in-class  support for our global workforce and refine and continue to define effective audit mechanisms for compliance. Lead and develop leaders to foster a culture of integrity, service excellence, accountability, innovation, best practice sharing across sites and functions and build external partner/vendor relationships that mirror this culture. Role requires at least 30% domestic and international travel. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 15+ years experience in leadership roles leading vendor operations and workforce management and capacity planning functions. Experience of working with a scale of greater than ten thousand staff in domains such as compliance, risk, customer service, shared services, business process outsourcing. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Deep domain expertise in all aspects of large-scale operations, specifically vendor management, outsourcing and workforce management/tooling/capacity planning/project management and location strategy. Superior fiscal/budget management, negotiation and contract management expertise. Ability to remain calm and effective under pressure and coach teams to effectively navigate and communicate in a fast-paced and ambiguous environment."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mow2pUAB/", "title": "VP Latin America Sales", "location": "S\u00e3o Paulo, Brazil", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  We are looking for the highest caliber executive leader to manage Facebook\u2019s growth across Latin America, spearheading the company\u2019s strategic relationships with global brands, agencies and partners for Facebook\u2019s advertising platform. We are looking to identify an exceptional people leader with a proven track record of delivering success in a high performing organization. The candidate will have a deep understanding of the market opportunities and will create an inspiring vision to set objectives and run day-to-day operations. The role leads the strategy across a functional team including sales, marketing, measurement, and creative, and reports into the Global VP for Global Marketing Solutions. This role will be located out of our Sao Paulo office.  RESPONSIBILITIES Define and drive Facebook's Latin America strategy with short, medium term and long-term goals Develop and execute Facebook's strategy and operations to ensure growth and achievement of objectives across Latin America Be the face of the company in Latin America by raising public profile and delivering key note speeches at industry conferences and events Represent Facebook externally across a diverse range of strategic interests and matters Lead Facebook's sales teams across multiple locations and cross-functional teams Develop capabilities needed to fuel Facebook\u2019s growth in Latin America anticipating future needs Build long term strategic partnerships with the largest clients, governmental bodies, industry groups and C level leaders Provide strategic business analytic strength to help drive initiatives critical to ongoing growth Establish strategic, financial and operating targets in alignment with long term strategic plan Act as a thought leader to grow Facebook\u2019s footprint in Latin America for our community, our advertisers and our partners Lead a team of diverse experienced leaders playing a critical role in building, leading and inspiring a high performing commercial and business development organization Ensure teams retain functional connection and strength to Facebook headquarters Collaborate with internal and regional teams to ensure product improvement process efficiency, and transfer of knowledge Actively participate in the Leadership Team and global teams where appropriate, embracing the company mission Build a strong Facebook culture centered on our values and setting the highest standards of integrity and compliance MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Experience as MD/CEO and significant divisional leadership is required Reputation as a thought leader running large complex businesses who is already highly regarded as an experienced executive in the market Overall 15+ years of leadership experience with 12+ years\u2019 experience in leading global consultative sales & marketing global organisations and business development teams Track record for managing regional sales and marketing operations, with a preference for experience in media sales A history of executing against aggressive growth strategies and delivering sales targets in excess of company expectations, and a history of growing and developing high growth, scaled operations Influential at C Suite level externally and comfortable influencing at Exec levels internally Deep experience in developing a market for digital solutions and developing strategic partnerships Experience of strategically developing new businesses and new markets for scale Proven record of being creative, resourceful, detail-oriented, highly organized and of effectively influencing and communicating cross-functionally Understanding of business clients and their needs, track record in the acquisition of new clients and entering new markets, experience in managing, developing and monetizing existing customers to the next level Proven leadership ability to influence, develop, and empower employees to achieve their best with a team approach\n#LI-DNI"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LBbEhUAL/", "title": "Controls Specialist, Subject Matter Expert", "location": "Henrico, VA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a Controls Specialist, Subject Matter Expert to join our Data Center Facility Operations team. Our data centers serve as the foundation upon which our software operates to meet the demands of our customers.  This role is responsible for reliability and quality of the Building Management System (BMS).  The candidate will support data center daily operations, and global quality / standardization initiatives. RESPONSIBILITIES Accountable for all Building Management System (BMS) operations, changes, and enhancements on a campus consisting of multiple data center buildings. Diagnose and repair complex control system malfunctions requiring extensive knowledge of a variety of electronic or digital controls systems and ability to test and write modifications in multiple languages of systems software. Troubleshoot and repair controls hardware including controllers, relays, measurement devices, actuators, etc. Review operating equipment data for efficiency improvements, monitor all building systems for abnormal operating trends, and make optimization adjustments accordingly. Manage controls vendors while supporting site operations, including direct oversight to all system configuration and component upgrades. Review quality control of hardware installation and review programming through commissioning process for new construction and retrofits. Provide controls scope and review proposals for retrofits and upgrades. Oversee all system configurations and component upgrades to ensure system integrity is maintained and that all modifications to existing systems are in compliance with best practices, including change control processes. Provide technical controls training and support to all Facility Operations staff. Collaborate with Global Automation and Optimization team to implement initiatives at the data center. Communicate all issues and upcoming controls work with site management. Other duties as required to support the operation of Facebook data centers. Less than ten percent of Occasional travel as required. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years of controls experience in programming development, start up, and commissioning of complex systems - central plants, air handling units, and evaporative cooling/humidification systems. AS/BS degree in Engineering/Technical studies, Military Technical School, or equivalent work experience. Experience in data centers or other critical environments. Working knowledge of mechanical, electrical and life safety systems associated with critical environments. Ability to read and audit blueprints/CAD drawings and controls diagrams. Communication and organizational skills. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Alerton experience Experience with common software programming languages : Python, PHP, SQL. Experience beyond field technician level  - project management, project engineering, operations management. IT/Networking certification"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoRhaUAF/", "title": "Systems Project Manager, Risk and Response (Core Ops)", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Risk & Response team seeks to identify and prioritize emerging external risks, lead investigations probing our systems to evaluate these risks, deliver action-oriented assessments to benefit our partners and users, and conduct post-mortem investigations to provide critical insights to our internal cross-functional stakeholders. We are seeking a Systems Project Manager with a passion for tools and their underlying systems to help Risk & Response scale operations and efficiently mitigate risk. Successful candidates will excel at building and troubleshooting systems to optimize for scalable support, coach and mentor teammates in pinpointing system inefficiencies, and develop technical support frameworks for mitigating risk to Facebook. RESPONSIBILITIES Become a technical expert on all tools and systems utilized by Risk & Response Support the building and debugging of Risk & Response infrastructure as needed Consult with Risk & Response teams to solve workflow problems and ensure internal tools and automation systems are fully leveraged Collaborate with teammates in developing, prioritizing, and delivering comprehensive and data-driven tool improvement requests Analyze trends in tool improvement requests and automation requests and raise core problems to Community Integrity Engineering and the Community Operations Engineering Team Address sensitive content issues, including but not limited to graphic images, videos and writings, offensive or derogatory language, and other objectionable material MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS degree or international equivalent 4+ years of project management experience Analytical-thinking and problem-solving experience Experience collaborating with a variety of individuals and organizations to drive improvements with minimal guidance Experience communicating results of technical analyses with non-technical partners and leadership teams to influence the strategy of those teams Experience breaking down processes and identifying key pain points in order to deliver business improvements at the regional or global level PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience with data analysis or internal tools Technical experience (PHP, SQL) Experience driving solutions for global operational teams"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCMvSUAX/", "title": "Quality Systems Project Manager, Community Operations", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Community Operations' focus is on improving the health of our products and helping people understand how to use them through both direct support interactions as well as scalable solutions. Those who join our teams are very passionate about solving people\u2019s issues, and are strong advocates for the Facebook community. We are looking for a passionate problem solver to develop both a deep and broad understanding of Facebook\u2019s review policies and processes and understand where our people, processes, and systems need to improve in order to give help to the people who need it most.\n \nIn this role, you will work closely with cross-functional partners, subject matter experts, operations managers and our Engineering, Reporting, and Outsourcing teams.  RESPONSIBILITIES Deeply understand the architecture and integration points of Facebook's community support processes, products and policies Partner with cross-functional teams to develop and launch new quality program initiatives that enable Facebook to improve the integrity and effectiveness of its quality systems Analyze existing quality processes and tools to provide recommendations for improvements, and partner with engineering teams to implement change Research new and innovative methods to measure and improve quality Manage complex cross-functional projects and deliver high-quality solutions Travel overnight internationally when needed (<25%) MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree in a quantitative field such as mathematics, statistics, economics or related field 5+ years of experience initiating and driving projects to completion with minimal guidance 5+ years of experience doing business process analysis 4+ years working in an Operations, Analytics, Product, Engineering or equivalent team 4+ years of experience working with Excel PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 2+ years of experience working with SQL Self-starting, intellectually curious and creative individual comfortable operating in ambiguity Ability to communicate with a variety of audiences Open, collaborative and proven team player Ability to initiate and drive projects to completion with minimal guidance Avid Facebook user, a passion for the product and ensuring a good user experience"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mp5WwUAJ/", "title": "Technical Recruiter, Software Engineering - East Coast", "location": "New York, NY", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  As a member of our team, the Technical Recruiter owns and drives the recruiting process from end-to-end. We work consultatively with our hiring managers to partner and develop strategies to find candidates for our Software Engineering organization. We\u2019re also passionate about delivering a candidate experience that lends genuine insight into our culture and what it\u2019s really like to work here. We\u2019re seeking a dynamic Recruiter who brings a balance of creativity, focus and determination to our team. RESPONSIBILITIES Design and execute customized, candidate recruiting plans, partnering closely with sourcers, coordinators and hiring managers to achieve the best results possible Find and engage unique and/or passive candidates through creative sourcing techniques, coordinating with our schedulers as needed Regularly manage pipeline activity and maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders Establish and maintain meaningful relationships across management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, HR, Compensation, and Diversity teams) Collaborate with others on the recruiting team on initiatives and/or hiring needs that may spike in other areas MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 4+ years of full cycle recruiting experience Experience independently partnering with leadership on hiring initiatives Experience influencing and driving toward results Problem solving experience Organizational experience Experience working in a team-based environment PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Software Engineering recruiting"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoqCmUAJ/", "title": "Enterprise Engineering Manager", "location": "Dublin, Ireland", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.\n \nFacebook\u2019s Enterprise Engineering team is responsible for building integrated, scalable, and robust enterprise applications. We are currently looking for an experienced, insightful, forward-thinking Engineer Manager with a strong ability to design and execute products that power the enterprise. As a member of Enterprise Engineering, you will play a key role in reimagining productivity by shipping transformative products that serve diverse aspects of the enterprise. This is a full-time position based in our Dublin office in Ireland.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Lead a team of engineers and product managers in the ideation and technical development of innovative enterprise software to streamline and automate critical business processes Provide strategic and operational oversight for Enterprise software product development Work closely with business leaders to develop short and long-term strategies Manage business expectations, resolve conflicts, and keep businesses aligned Develop and drive execution on 6 month and 1 year road maps Drive innovation, establish new approaches in improving productivity Establish a metrics based organization, develop key operational metrics and push for continuous improvement. Ensure system security, data integrity and accuracy of financial records MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelors degree Experience of leading Software Engineering teams. Experience with programming languages such as Java, PHP, Python, or C++ Experience with agile systems development methodologies Experience managing engineering teams including hiring/termination and performance management PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Bachelors in Computer Science or related field Experience developing Financial Application products (i.e. Order Management, Accounts Receivable, Billing, Revenue Management, Collections, Customer Relationship Management, E-commerce) Ability to understand business logic Organizational and analytical skills"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1200000LTa9wEAD/", "title": "Windows Systems Engineer, Physical Security", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Scalable enterprise infrastructure involves complex mix of databases, applications and infrastructure toolsets. We need our Enterprise applications to be highly secure, available and reliable. Doing this at Facebook-speed involves working on unique ways to improve scalability, robustness and quality of applications running on our Windows infrastructure.\n\nThis role requires you to work on creating/operating Windows infrastructure for applications providing functions for physical security; you will deliver solutions with speed, security and quick turnaround to the needs of the business. A key ingredient for success in this role is a passion around automation and end-to-end optimization of application scalability, health and uptime. RESPONSIBILITIES Inventory, document and create installation/removal runbooks for windows based services Create automated install recipes and implement integrity checks for services (using Chef and Selenium equivalent) Create working system level backups and applications that serve a large and distributed set of sites. -Genetec, CCURE, Traka, BioConnect are some examples. Verify and validate Windows based systems and services -Restoring applications/systems/services from backups Create health monitors for Windows based services -Leveraging monitoring tools such as, but not limited to: Nagios, SCOM Work with Powershell, and homegrown automation tools, to scale the infrastructure, implement continuous monitoring and provide a highly automated application patching/upgrades MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 3+ years within a large enterprise sized heterogeneous environment 5+ years experience in managing complex Microsoft based Windows Infrastructures (operating systems, iis, clustering, DSC, wsus, GPO, authentication/authorization, etc) 3+ years experience in automation/DSC (such as WSH/Powershell/Chef, Choclatey, Python) 5+ years experience in Windows systems administration in VmWare or equivalent environments DR/BCP fundamentals, with practical application Experience troubleshooting systems Experience with TCP/IP networking, PKI/Certificate life cycle management Experience with firewalls and network security Experience working in heterogeneous environments such as Linux/MacOSx use/administration Experience managing distributed, database-backed applications on Windows PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years experience with AD/Exchange Experience with products in Physical Security space (eg. Genetec, CCURE, Traka, BioConnect) Experience working with or in support of diverse communities"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mp5ieUAB/", "title": "Data Scientist, Compliance, Security, and Investigations OpTech Team", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Compliance, Security, and Investigations (CSI) Operations, Partnerships, and Tech Team assists other legal teams by providing deep technical solutions to highly complex and real world impacting problems. We manage the systems that power law enforcement response, transparency reporting, and other front-line outreach and compliance functions. Our group is looking for an experienced data scientist with a focus in operations and a natural curiosity for internal systems. As our primary data emissary, you'll be working on reporting and using data to forecast, build insights, and draw correlations between our external and internal products. You will also be expected to see beyond just the raw data to understand our users' behaviors and interactions, and to explain those behaviors to stakeholders. In this role, you will see a direct link between your work, company growth, and user satisfaction. You will be working with some of the brightest minds in the industry, and you'll get an opportunity to solve some of the most challenging business problems on the web and mobile Internet, at a scale that few companies can match. RESPONSIBILITIES Apply expertise in statistics, machine learning, and data exploration and analysis in leveraging internal operations data to solve critical problems for multiple legal teams Contribute directly to internal reporting and other data visualizations that are used by leadership who need to know the state of the business Work on a team of data analysts, scientists, and engineers responsible for internal reporting, ad-hoc data analysis, and data pipelines and warehouses Build cross-functional relationships with Data Scientists, Product Managers, and Software Engineers, and leverage expertise in data science to influence these partners Drive data quality and integrity across multiple verticals and related business areas Educate partners, stakeholders, and leadership on results of data investigation related to user behavior and long- term trends MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS in Computer Science, Math, Physics, Engineering, Statistics or a related quantitative field 6+ years experience analyzing data stored in various DBMS (MySQL, Oracle) or in Hive 2+ years software engineering experience Experience with statistics (e.g., hypothesis testing, regression) and experimental design Experience with data visualization tools Software development experience in Python or other scripting languages (PHP, Perl) Experience in applying machine learning algorithms to solve real-world business problems Experience in communicating data-driven insights to front-line and leadership teams Experience initiating projects starting with data exploration and driving said projects to completion PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Advanced degree in Computer Science, Math, Physics, or a related quantitative field Ability to obtain and retain a government clearance Experience in the design, deployment, and maintenance of large data pipelines and data warehouses"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LJxPAUA1/", "title": "Product Marketing Analyst, Marketplace", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  With over 60 million active business pages and 6 million active advertisers, Facebook is one of the largest business platforms in the world and this role will play a critical role in helping our product teams understand how we can make meaningful connections between people and small and medium sized businesses. We are seeking a self-motivated, ambitious problem-solver who is knowledgeable and passionate about digital marketing and small businesses. The ideal candidate for this role will be someone who is comfortable making sense of data, who is excited to break down problems and who is passionate about helping small and medium sized businesses grow. This role be an advocate for our customers as they work to gather market feedback and translate that feedback into product requirements. RESPONSIBILITIES Shape our product teams' understanding of how Marketplace can help uniquely meet the needs of small and medium sized businesses through qualitative research and quantitative analysis Develop an ongoing pipeline of businesses within SMB segments interested in participating in alpha and beta testing Scope and execute alpha testing on key products by developing learning objectives, recruiting participants, on-boarding participants to the test, resolving and participant issues and synthesizing feedback to Product Marketing, Product Management, Research, Design and Engineering Partner with cross-functional stakeholders within Marketplace, Sales, Messaging, Business Integrity, Help and Education, and Customer Service to evaluate trends that may help inform how we can better serve small businesses on our platforms Produce ad hoc analyses to aid teams in understanding small and medium sized businesses' behavior, develop points of views, and drive decision-making that informs our product development and product launches MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS Degree 2+ years\u2019 work experience in marketing research, strategy consulting, or digital marketing Proven experience managing cross-functional projects Experience directly using data to derive insights Communication and presentation experience PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS in Math, Statistics, Economics, Computer Science, Physics, Engineering, Sociology, or Business Experience with Small & Medium Businesses Online marketing, advertising or marketplaces experience"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000ModWSUAZ/", "title": "Director of Public Policy, Southeast Asia - Established Countries", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  As Facebook has become part of the daily lives of more than two billion people around the world, policymakers in many countries naturally wish to talk with us, and we wish to facilitate an ongoing dialogue with them as our service offerings grow and change. The Public Policy team manages these conversations, sharing information about the company's products and activities, responding to queries from policymakers and regulators, and providing input into the development of regulation of the internet sector \u2013 with the goal of furthering the company\u2019s mission of helping people to build community. We are looking for superb policy communicators who can combine a passion for Facebook's mission with a deep knowledge of the political and regulatory dynamics in several countries and experience of leading teams across multiple countries. \n \nThe Director of Public Policy SEA (Established Countries) will lead our policy team in countries where we have an office - Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore and Thailand, They will partner with our sales, communications, legal, and other leaders. This role reports directly to the VP of Public Policy for APAC and is part of his leadership team. We anticipate that this position will be located in our Singapore office, but we are open to it being based in a Facebook office in another one of these five countries.\n \n RESPONSIBILITIES Lead a team of policy professionals, enabling them to thrive and to deliver our policy objectives in each country With colleagues on the APAC policy leadership team, devise and implement an APAC-wide policy strategy Monitor the political environment for policy challenges and opportunities for the company Learn from and influence government and non-governmental organizations on issues of privacy, safety and security, intellectual property, election integrity, free expression, and other technology-relevant public policy concerns Represent Facebook in meetings with politicians and policymakers as needed across the region Build coalitions to help advance and support Facebook\u2019s policy agenda Communicate Facebook\u2019s positions in public presentations and with media Advise other Facebook teams on public policy matters MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Passion for emerging technologies, policy work, and Facebook Keen understanding of Asian political systems and institutions as well as policy, politics and communications Impeccable judgment and character Strong analytical and creative thinking on policy issues and programs Well-developed advocacy skills Ability to work in a dynamic, fast-paced environment Willingness and excitement about frequent travel 15+ years of demonstrated experience managing legislation and/or government relations and advocacy work \nExtensive people management experience required Experience in policy work for a multinational corporation preferred Superb communication skills in English and an Asian language preferred Advanced degree in related field or law degree preferred"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MohV2UAJ/", "title": "Leadership Recruiter, Global Marketing Solutions", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  As a member of our team, the Leadership Recruiter owns and drives the recruiting process from end-to-end. We work consultatively with our hiring managers to partner and develop strategies to find leadership candidates for our Global Marketing Solutions organization. We\u2019re also passionate about delivering a candidate experience that lends genuine insight into our culture and what it\u2019s really like to work here. We\u2019re seeking a dynamic recruiter who brings a balance of creativity, focus and determination to our team. RESPONSIBILITIES Design and execute customized, candidate recruiting plans, partnering closely with sourcers, coordinators and hiring managers to achieve the best results possible Find and engage unique and/or passive candidates through creative sourcing techniques, coordinating with our schedulers as needed Regularly manage pipeline activity and maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders Establish and maintain meaningful relationships across management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, HR, Compensation, and Diversity teams) Regularly track pipeline, priorities and performance data to share with internal stakeholders Collaborate with others on the recruiting team on initiatives and/or hiring needs that may spike in other areas Work with leadership recruiting manager to develop and execute a recruitment approach focused on the relevant businesses and candidates Conduct direct market research and develop market and talent updates for management and business owners MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 7+ years of full cycle recruiting experience 4+ years of leadership recruiting experience Experience independently partnering with leadership on hiring initiatives domestically and globally Experience in compensation and general HR requirements as related to hiring Experience working in a team-based environment Knowledge of executive search strategies and talent acquisition Negotiation, influencing and communication experience PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience working with or in support of diverse communities"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoascUAB/", "title": "Strategic Partnerships Manager, Messenger", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking an experienced Strategic Partnerships professional who is passionate about the way Facebook can work with businesses, startups, and developers to build a variety of valuable product experiences for people on Messenger and has an interest in technology, social media and business strategy. \n \nDeveloper Partnerships at Facebook is responsible for establishing and managing strategic relationships with our key Messenger partners and the developer ecosystem. You will work with some of the world\u2019s most exciting companies and startups as well as with our world-class Messenger product and engineering teams. In addition to those teams, you will work cross-functionally with the Policy, Legal, Marketing, PR and the Operations teams to optimize new capabilities, improve user experience, and make our partners successful. \n \nThis position is located in Menlo Park, CA.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Help drive product strategy through strategic partnerships with businesses, developers, and leading consumer product organizations Define market requirements, produce qualitative and quantitative analysis of product performance, aggregate feedback, explore new strategic opportunities, inform the product roadmap with enhanced or new functionality, and ensure product and industry impact Track, analyze and communicate key quantitative metrics and business trends as they relate to partner relationships Represent Facebook in external meetings with executives from other companies Maintain direct and active relationships with developers on our Messenger platform, including on-boarding and contract work, proactively resolving business, technical, and policy issues and serving as an internal advocate Work cross-functionally with product, engineering, business development, partnerships, policy, legal, marketing, and PR to launch products and partnerships Displaying the highest personal integrity and ethics Willingness and ability to travel 25% of the time MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years of work experience with product, partnership, or technical experience in consumer technology companies Experience defining, developing and leading projects Collaboration and relationship-building experience \u2014 with the experience developing working relationships at all levels of management Knowledge of Messenger Platform and their strategic and competitive positions Fluency in English PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years of mobile focused work experience with product, partnership, or technical experience in consumer technology companies A strong curiosity for innovative social products and their potential for transforming businesses and industries"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mp0s7UAB/", "title": "Global Security Strategic Partner", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  As a Strategic Partner you will be required to function with designated Facebook organizations and departments. You will serve as a liaison and thought partner between Global Security and the selected key business partners, in this case: Facebook\u2019s Infra Data Centers (IDC) organization. The ideal candidate should share our excitement for solving complex business and global security opportunities while minimizing friction and maximizing productivity.  RESPONSIBILITIES Provide assistance and guidance, and effectively connect Global Security with designated partners on a broad range of policies, programs, guidelines and practices. Act as an initial point of contact and intermediary for managers and employees in assigned business units. Maintain current understanding of the designated department\u2019s strategy, needs and requirements. Actively partner with business leaders and work with them to collaboratively identify practice improvement. Acts as a thought partner to improve priorities in the business units. Assist leaders with forecasting needs regarding people, assets and processes. Proactively understand and anticipate changes and security risks in the given area. Apply rigorous project management techniques to planning and implementing cross-functional initiatives that support current and future business strategies. Coordinate with Global Security departments and others to deliver on business requests and solve business problems. Work across teams to engage project partners, deeply understand problems, and use data and available information to drive outcomes. Build relationships based on truth, trust, and absolute integrity. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Experience in a role that requires maintaining business partnerships and/or strategic thought. Demonstrated experience taking a view of risks to a business, weigh them against business objectives, and work with the business to form a plan to address these risks. Experience executing on both tactical and strategic level. Knowledge in mediating, influencing, facilitation, presentation, communication, analysis, and problem solving. Experience to communicating ideas and business concepts in accessible terms. Experience exercising judgment."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoejQUAR/", "title": "Logistics Process & Systems Manager", "location": "S\u00e3o Paulo, Brazil", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking an experienced Logistics leader to assist in design and deployment of scalable and efficient processes and tools that support all aspects of our logistics/supply chain operations of goods and services for Facebook infrastructure. This role requires a full understanding of procure to pay, logistics asset management and lifecycle, inventory management, receiving, distribution and transportation of IT goods.  Additionally, the role supports the expansion and operation of Facebook and its apps network within LATAM region, with focus on Brazil. The successful candidate will work closely with cross functional teams and across organizations to gather requirements, define solutions, implement new tools and process, and provide ongoing support to these teams. RESPONSIBILITIES Partner with infrastructure teams and central support teams such as tax, accounting, trade and customs compliance to establish logistics process and systems to enable, scale and automate operations and goods movements across LATAM region, locally and internationally Strategize and manage the logistics aspects of project deployments of new points of presence (POPs) and other network facilities such as miniData Center or Data Centers that may deploy in LATAM region Be actively involved in the daily activities of logistics process, such as supervising the activities of local logistics partners, removing roadblocks with accommodation of legal requirements (i.e. compliance with Nota Fiscal requirements in Brazil and other government systems and reporting requirements for LATAM) Lead sessions to identify process inefficiencies, gather business requirements, partner with development teams to manage deliverables, testing and validation, roll-out and training, and triage and resolution of issues Develop, build, and maintain reports and dashboards that contain actionable metrics to monitor the performance of our operations Maintain data integrity across multiple systems and identify and resolve inconsistencies. Manage task queue to triage and resolve issues and engage with cross-functional teams as needed for resolution Liaise with cross-functional teams to assist with best practices and to ensure end-to-end process and tool consistency Work with internal business groups to acquire a deep understanding of their processes and operations Support global process and systems strategy, design and implementation of supply chain/logistics tools Responsible for proactive implementation of enhancements/modifications as they relate to long term strategies and short term tactical initiatives Responsible for ensuring effective data solutions supporting supply chain management, data base management, and set up requirements relating to Supply Chain and Operations MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree in Logistics, SCM, Management Information Systems or related field 10+ years of experience of Logistics, inventory management, operations management or project management building scalable process and tools Experienced with ERP, PLM, and other systems, tools Ability to collaborate with different individuals across the organization and within other geographies, and \"roll-up the sleeves\" in order to accomplish all necessary tasks Effective communication skills, and ability in explaining technical issues to both technical and business partners Ability to think strategically with a hands-on approach. At Facebook, nothing is someone else's work PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in developing metrics, data sources and reporting Experience in data analytics and capable of digging into data Experience working in operations or operations tooling/ticketing systems Logistics/Supply chain domain expertise"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mok3yUAB/", "title": "Technical Recruiter, FB+ (Oculus, Building 8, Camera, Social VR)", "location": "London, United Kingdom", "description": "Oculus, Building 8, Camera, and Social VR are some of the organizations that make up what we at Facebook call FB+. It is the goal of these teams to create and ship new, category-defining consumer hardware and software products that are immersive, social, and define our consumer\u2019s daily experiences. We want to enable people to experience anything, anywhere. We aim to do this at scale and to power this with a breakthrough innovation engine modeled after DARPA.\n  \nAs a team of world-class experts, we drive innovation in the areas of augmented and virtual reality, artificial intelligence, connectivity, and more -- and operate on aggressive, fixed timelines with extensive use of partnerships in universities, and small-large businesses.\n  \nAs a member of our team, the Technical Recruiter owns and drives the recruiting process from end-to-end. We work consultatively with our hiring managers to partner and develop strategies to find candidates for teams that support Oculus, Building 8, Camera, and Social VR. We are passionate about delivering candidate experiences that lends genuine insight into our culture and what it\u2019s really like to work here. We\u2019re seeking a dynamic Recruiter who brings a balance of creativity, focus and determination to our team. RESPONSIBILITIES Design and execute customized, candidate recruiting plans, partnering closely with sourcers, coordinators and hiring managers to achieve the best results possible Find and engage unique and/or passive candidates through creative sourcing techniques, coordinating with our schedulers as needed Regularly manage pipeline activity and maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders Establish and maintain meaningful relationships across management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, HR, Compensation, and Diversity teams) Collaborate with others on the recruiting team on initiatives and/ or hiring needs that may spike in other areas MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 4+ years of full cycle recruiting experience Experience independently partnering with leadership on hiring initiatives Ability to effectively influence and drive toward results in a fast-paced environment Problem solving skills Demonstrated ability to be detail-oriented, and organizational skills Experience in compensation and general HR requirements as related to hiring Ability to work effectively in a fast-paced, every evolving, and highly team-based environment"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoQ3CUAV/", "title": "Recruiter, Solutions Engineering", "location": "London, United Kingdom", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a Technical Recruiter to work in close partnership with hiring managers and develop strategies to find exceptional talent for our Solutions Engineering team. As a member of our team, the Technical Recruiter owns and drives the recruiting process from end-to-end partnering effectively with Solutions Engineering team to grow our engineering teams. We\u2019re seeking an experienced Recruiter who brings a balance of creativity, focus and determination to our team. We\u2019re also passionate about delivering a candidate experience that lends genuine insight into our culture and what it\u2019s really like to work here. RESPONSIBILITIES Partnering closely with Hiring Managers, Sourcers and Recruiting Coordinators to design and execute customised, recruiting strategies and achieve the best results possible Find and engage relevant candidates through creative sourcing and search techniques Manage recruiting pipeline activity, maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders and recruiting partners Recommend and drive process improvements that impact recruiting effectiveness Establish and maintain meaningful relationships across management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, HR, Compensation, and Diversity teams) Embody Facebook\u2019s culture - Be Bold, Move Fast and Focus on Impact MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Extensive full cycle recruiting experience, ideally within a search firm, recruitment agency or in-house recruiting team Deep expertise in technical recruiting across software engineering disciplines Experience partnering closely with leadership teams on recruiting initiatives Ability to effectively influence and drive results in a fast-paced and highly collaborative environment Interview and assessment skills with ability to screen for both technical and cultural qualities Creative problem solving skills Demonstrated ability to be detail-oriented with exceptional organisational skills Experience in compensation and general HR requirements as related to hiring Excellent interpersonal skills with ability to communicate easily with a diverse range of people and backgrounds"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MomLBUAZ/", "title": "Program Manager, Global Outsourcing", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking an experienced Outsourcing Program Manager to build and run outsourced programs, and to manage vendor relationships on behalf of our Ads & Marketing organizations. This is a unique opportunity to work with a diverse group of internal teams and drive significant impact toward our ongoing company growth.\n \nIdeal candidates will have outsourcing vendor management and consulting experience in the outsourcing or technology industries, with excellent communication and project management skills. This position is based at Facebook\u2019s offices in Austin (TX), and support programs globally, which will require traveling in country and internationally. RESPONSIBILITIES Serve as a consultant to our Ads & Integrity teams by developing customized and scalable outsourcing solutions Strategically manage a portfolio of programs by collaborating with cross-functional stakeholders and third-party vendors to achieve short-term and long-term objectives Guide the vendor selection process and conduct commercial negotiations Drive legal, financial, technological aspects of outsourced programs Ensure program success through strong performance management and governance methodologies Manage complex vendor relationships Prioritize and deliver timely, high quality work Ability to travel in the US and internationally MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years of outsourcing experience Project management experience including planning, development, execution, measurement, and optimization Experience with presentation and communication with peers, management, and cross-functional teams Experience working and building relationships with cross-functional groups and third parties Experience breaking down cost models and knowledge with the drivers of ROI in an outsourced model Knowledge of legal, financial and technology components of outsourcing Experience working in a global remote team PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in a technology or consumer-oriented environment Experience in a business process outsourcing consulting or program management role Experience working with or in support of diverse communities"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LJygLUAT/", "title": "Business Analyst, Compensation", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a Compensation Business Analyst with strong analytical and operational experience to work with recruiting on offers, metrics & reporting, and communication & training related to new hire compensation. This full-time position is located in our Menlo Park office. RESPONSIBILITIES Work with recruiting and business leaders to develop offers Apply your expertise in quantitative analysis, for measurement and tracking of key compensation and recruiting-related metrics to help inform, influence, support, and execute business decisions Participate in the research for, and ongoing development and administration of new hire compensation programs that matches Facebook\u2019s needs Build and maintain reports, dashboards, and metrics and monitor the integrity and validity of the data reported Obtain a thorough understanding of our data sources and collection methods Analyze trends in new hire compensation and build intelligence through reporting Work with large amounts of data and build tools to streamline the offer process Develop and update compensation communication materials and trainings for recruiters and candidates MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BS/BA in Economics, Finance, Statistics, Mathematics, HR, Business or related discipline 1+ years of experience in consulting, finance, compensation, recruiting or a similarly applicable field Experience in Excel, including experience building analyses and models Project management experience"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000K6py6UAB/", "title": "Technical Recruiter, Product", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Recruiting is a core strategic driver of Facebook\u2019s success. We have a world-class team working together to help drive our ambitions and scale to the next level. We conceive practical and creative ways to surface leading talent, and we invest a lot of time activating passive candidates through a highly engaged approach. We\u2019re passionate about delivering an awesome candidate experience, and that starts with the first conversation a candidate has with us. \n\nAs the recruiter focused on Product recruiting efforts, this role will partner with Product teams to evaluate talent, structure deal terms and seamlessly integrate new talent acquisitions. RESPONSIBILITIES Design and execute customized, full cycle staffing plans, partnering closely with hiring managers to achieve the best results possible Find and engage unique and/or passive candidates through creative sourcing techniques, coordinating with our sourcers as needed Facilitate and lead meetings and key initiatives and projects with client groups, and with the recruiting teams, that will continuously improve and scale our recruiting operations and results Regularly manage pipeline activity and maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders Establish and maintain meaningful relationships with management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, HR, Compensation, and Diversity teams) Collaborate with others on the recruiting team on initiatives and/ or hiring needs that may spike in other areas MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 4+ years of full cycle recruiting experience Experience independently partnering with leadership on hiring across time zones Ability to influence and drive toward results in an environment Experience in problem-solving across all stages of the hiring cycle Experience in compensation and general HR requirements as related to hiring PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience partnering with recruiters and hiring partners across different offices Full cycle recruiting experience across multiple tech/product disciplines Ability to work in a team-based environment"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCMuhUAH/", "title": "Quality Operations Project Manager, Community Operations", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Community Operations' focus is on improving the health of our products and helping people understand how to use them through both direct support interactions as well as scalable solutions. Those who join our teams are very passionate about solving people\u2019s issues, and are strong advocates for the Facebook community. We are looking for a passionate problem solver to develop both a deep and broad understanding of Facebook\u2019s review policies and processes and understand where our people, processes, and systems need to improve in order to give help to the people who need it most.\n \nIn this role, you will work closely with cross-functional partners, subject matter experts, operations managers and our Engineering, Reporting, and Outsourcing teams.  RESPONSIBILITIES Ensure timely delivery of day-to-day quality metrics from our outsourced and in-house partners against Service Level targets Ensure integrity of quality metrics by supporting and coaching quality auditors Coach auditors and improve the audit process to ensure clear, timely and actionable feedback is sent to teams to improve their performance Perform weekly qualitative and quantitative analyses of error trends and collaborate with peers supporting other regions to aggregate, prioritize and report on the top quality issues impacting the organization Gather and analyze feedback from auditors to provide recommendations for improvements to Facebook's quality systems Develop and maintain process documentation for the end-to-end quality process to ensure consistency across regions Launch/maintain quality programs for new products and new support sites (vendor locations) Travel overnight internationally when needed (<25%) MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree in a quantitative field such as mathematics, statistics, economics or related field 3+ years of experience working in an Operations, Analytics, Product, Engineering or equivalent team 2+ years experience with Excel (PivotTable, Charts, Statistical functions) 1+ years of Project Management experience PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 2+ years of experience working with SQL Strategic thinker with analytical and problem-solving skills Self-starting, intellectually curious and creative individual comfortable operating in ambiguity Attention to detail Ability to communicate with a variety of audiences Open, collaborative and proven team player Ability to initiate and drive projects to completion with minimal guidance Avid Facebook user, a passion for the product and ensuring a good user experience"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoMFkUAN/", "title": "Data Center Security Manager", "location": "Fort Worth, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Data Center Security Manager is responsible for reducing risk, responding to incidents and overall direction & leadership of the on-site security team. Supports and executes global physical security programs, initiatives, processes and best practices to build a safe and secure environment. Builds strong cross-functional partnerships across the data center team and Facebook by communicating team goals, wins and opportunities to maximize safe and secure work environments. Cultivates external partnerships with local and state law enforcement, federal agencies, third party vendors and community organizations. \n \nThis position will be located in Fort Worth and will be responsible for security at other Infrastructure locations within the region and may take on other responsibilities based on subject matter expertise. RESPONSIBILITIES Directly leads the on-site security team at the data center Develops and maintains local standards and procedures to ensure execution of Global Physical Security strategies to include enforcement of business conduct and integrity standards, employee safety and security, investigations, crisis response, business continuity and security and government partnerships Regularly communicates updates to key partners on incidents, emerging risks, and other issues that may impact Facebook\u2019s data center operations, employees, or vendors Works closely with the Global Security Operations Center and the Global Security Investigations and Intelligence Team to anticipate, identify and evaluate risks that carry a significant risk to Facebook\u2019s data center(s) Establishes and monitors performance metrics to determine team effectiveness: budget management, performance metrics and contract management Deliver training on security topics, assist in the coordination of security services to support planned and unplanned operations, and support incident investigation efforts MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years of site/campus security management experience Planning, organizational, and motivational experience Experience drafting in technical and non-technical formats Experience presenting both extemporaneously and in formal settings Experience in root cause analysis, industry benchmarking, survey evaluation and data interpretation Experience in the areas of emergency/disaster management, physical security, critical incident stress management, risk management and business resiliency Experience with emergency procedure protocols and regulatory interfaces Knowledge in physical security strategies, principles, standards, policies, and procedures Experience with security technologies including Video Surveillance, Access Control, and Incident Management Systems, Security Operations Centers PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor\u2019s degree. ASIS Certified Protection Professional (CPP) and/or Physical Security Professional (PSP) certifications. Previous Safety & Security management experience in a Data Center environment. Experience working with or in support of diverse communities."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCBcyUAH/", "title": "Risk Assessment Analyst, Risk and Response", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Risk Assessment team seeks to identify and prioritize emerging external risks, lead investigations probing our systems to evaluate these risks, deliver action-oriented assessments to benefit our partners and users, and conduct post-mortem investigations to provide critical insights to our internal cross functional stakeholders. \n\nWe're seeking a technically-minded Risk Assessment Analyst with a passion for uncovering risks and utilizing data to formulate an independent perspective when making evaluations. Our Business Risk Analyst will focus on risks within ads and commerce, while our Community Risk Analyst will focus on content-based risk. Successful candidates will excel at building and implementing frameworks, as well as creatively utilizing data to create and deliver compelling risk assessments to key partners. RESPONSIBILITIES Conduct investigations to bring deeper understanding and knowledge of potential risk areas in ads, commerce and/or our community Use data and internal tools to identify and investigate potential risk areas and patterns at scale and across abuse types Create a framework using internal data for a quantitative model of measuring risk Use quantitative & qualitative research methods to perform root cause analyses on investigative findings or high priority escalations Partner with internal experts to build a deep understanding of how, where, and why diverse forms of abuse are experienced across the platform Develop programs and methodologies that shape how we approach offensive investigations as an external actor that pressure tests our community support and/or advertisement integrity systems Synthesize investigative findings through the creation of reports and presentations that provide a coherent narrative assessing external risk Identify data and tooling requirements in order to influence project prioritization and roadmaps MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 4+ years experience in investigative, data analysis, or technical systems work 4+ years experience using SQL or R to perform advanced analysis Problem solving and analytical experience Experience communicating results of technical analyses with non-technical partners and leadership teams to influence the strategy of those teams Experience driving cases through process to resolution Experience operating strategic projects with cross-functional partners PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in one of more of the following programming languages: Python, PHP or Haskell Experience working with data visualization tools (e.g.  Tableau)"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MosJVUAZ/", "title": "Program Manager, Watch and Video, Media Operations", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  We are seeking an individual who is passionate about Facebook's video products and our mission, and is relentless in finding smarter, better, faster ways of getting things done. The ideal candidate has experience driving large and complex projects or programs, and can lead discussions with cross-functional teams across the company.  This individual will serve as the voice of media publishers internally, working directly with Product Managers, Engineers, Legal, Policy, Partner Managers, Intellectual Property and Community Operations to ensure an amazing support experience for our partners. \n \nThis individual will spend at least 50% of his or her time focused on our suite of Video products, including Watch, to ensure that its users have access to exceptional support experiences and that the team is in lock step with Facebook\u2019s Product, Policy, Legal, Policy, and Partnerships teams. This is a full-time position located in Menlo Park, California. RESPONSIBILITIES Become an expert in the support experience for media companies and emerging creators on Facebook, and in funded content program requirements, specifically as it relates to video Serve as a key point of contact for Media Operations, joining recurring Watch and Video Integrity team meetings and maintaining expertise in Facebook product experiences for partners Develop scaled solutions, specifically for video products, that address publishers' and creators' Facebook experiences and product opportunities Collaborate with Product, Legal, Policy, Partner Managers, other Operations teams, and partners to create exceptional support experiences Understand policies and risks with the ability to effectively translate them into sound processes or communications Create strategic solutions for tracking, quality, and enforcement models for emerging funded content programs Analyze creator interaction with our video products, and communicate insights to Product Management, Engineering, Partnerships, Marketing, and other partners within the company Drive product adoption and usage by supporting partner facing programs and effective product launch support MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA or BS Degree 3+ years of experience in online operations, product management, consulting, partnerships or account management Analytical and problem solving experience Experience defining, developing, and leading programs Knowledge of digital video business models and solutions Knowledge of how the content distribution landscape is changing Relationship management experience and experience working within a global organization Experience with identifying, utilizing and communicating performance metrics Demonstrated experience thinking strategically about issues, leading to thoughtful recommendations and action plans Proven experience influencing others without having positional authority Knowledge of Facebook's video product suite PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 2+ years spent working in the internet technology, media-entertainment, or digital marketing space Experience with video content consumption products or platforms"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LBqfFUAT/", "title": "Data Scientist - Online Safety, Security", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Online Safety is a team that works to protect Facebook's most vulnerable groups. We want to make sure that people are not placing themselves in danger as a result of their activity on Facebook, and on the flip side, people are not using Facebook as a means of threatening or carrying out threats against others. We're looking for a Data Scientist to help us get a deep understanding of how these groups of people use Facebook, analyze current safety trends and develop solutions to detect and mitigate risk. You will enjoy working with one of the strongest data sets in the world, cutting edge technology, and the ability to see your insights being used to protect people. The perfect candidate will have a background in a quantitative or technical field and experience in data-driven decision making. Beyond technical skills, you need to pay attention to detail and the ability to effectively present results. You need to be focused on impact, a self-starter, and have demonstrated success in using analytics to drive the understanding, growth, and success of a product. This is a full-time position located at our headquarters in Menlo Park, CA. RESPONSIBILITIES Conduct exploratory analysis of safety cases in order to identify trends in abuse ecosystems by defining and evaluating metrics of user behavior Lead quantitative analysis projects from start to finish including all aspects of data analysis (e.g. processing, cleaning, verifying the integrity of data used for analysis, statistical analysis, visualizations) and communicating results Partner with engineers and cross-functional teams to turn analyses into opportunities to detect and mitigate future safety risk Support the creation of predictive models for automated detection systems (from feature selection to building and optimization of machine-learning models) Measure the performance of safety campaigns and programs by building dashboards and reports Explore additional data sources that can be used to help identify new opportunities to signal bad actor behavior MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS in Computer Science, Math, Physics, Engineering, Statistics or other technical field 2+ years of post-college work in a quantitative role Experience in SQL or other programming languages. Some development experience in at least one scripting language (PHP, Python, Perl, etc.) Understanding of statistical analysis Experience with a statistical package such as R, Python, etc. Experience working cross-functionally and is able to translate technical content to a general audience PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in a similar role and at an Internet-based company Advanced degrees Passion for protecting the most vulnerable users on Facebook with deep interest in understanding user behavior and utilizing data to mitigate safety risk"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoMGOUA3/", "title": "Analyst, Insights & Operations, Recruiting", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Recruiting is a core strategic driver of Facebook's success.  We have a world-class team working together to help drive our ambitions and scale to the next level. We are looking for an Analyst, Insights & Operations, Recruiting based in either Menlo Park or San Francisco (CA). \n \nThis full-time position reports into the Lead, Insights & Operations and will be responsible for leveraging data and analytics to identify opportunities to increase the efficiency of the Global Recruitment; identifying processes, resources and tools that improve productivity, performance and compliance.  \n RESPONSIBILITIES Support the Global Business Recruiting teams to analyze recruiting data and metrics, identify trends, evaluate effectiveness of recruiting strategies and measure ROI Design reporting capabilities to enable school and company insights - including reporting ability for different teams, regions, and process areas Communicate trends and insights to leaders as well as communicate data integrity issues or process gaps to individual team members and leads Evaluate additional information needs and recommend appropriate system changes or enhancements to meet the needs Draft, maintain and support a variety of reports or queries utilizing appropriate reporting tools, assists recruiting/Business Intelligence team in the development or customization of standard reports for ongoing customer needs, generates ad-hoc reports as required Identify and remediate recruiter practices which put at risk data integrity, as well as provide solutions to prevent such risks in the future Conduct analysis of current business processes and functional requirements Demonstrate Metrics & Analytics capability to streamline reporting across all regions and pipelines and introduce predictive capabilities around the end-to-end recruitment cycle Provide on-going training to team leads and individuals on analytic tools and dashboards, including but not limited to MS Excel, Salesforce, Tableau, and others Establish and maintain relationships to continually improve collaboration with Business stakeholders, including Global Recruiting, People Engineering, Recruiting Operations and related teams MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree or equivalent experience in recruitment operations, business intelligence, and/or project management 1+ years reporting and analytics experience Track record of partnering with business, engineering, and data science teams to deliver data-driven insights and translating those into process improvement recommendations Experience with recruiting data and data visualization tools PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 2+ years' experience in recruitment operations, business intelligence, and/or project management Interpersonal, communication and leadership skills Demonstrated track record of building strong working relationships at all levels, across functions and geographic boundaries Flexibility to adapt to changing business situations Ability and desire to collaborate and work with recruiting stakeholders across different time zones Effective problem-solving capabilities and refined analytical skills Flexibility to handle multiple tasks concurrently with acute attention to detail Aptitude for learning new technologies extemporaneously Experience in Tableau"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCRJBUA5/", "title": "Quality Operations Project Manager, Community Operations", "location": "Dublin, Ireland", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Community Operations' focus is on improving the health of our products and helping people understand how to use them through both direct support interactions as well as scalable solutions. Those who join our teams are very passionate about solving people\u2019s issues, and are strong advocates for the Facebook community. We are looking for a passionate problem solver to develop both a deep and broad understanding of Facebook\u2019s review policies and processes and understand where our people, processes, and systems need to improve in order to give help to the people who need it most.\n \nIn this role, you will work closely with cross-functional partners, subject matter experts, operations managers and our Engineering, Reporting, and Outsourcing teams.  RESPONSIBILITIES Ensure timely delivery of day-to-day quality metrics from our outsourced and in-house partners against Service Level targets Ensure integrity of quality metrics by supporting and coaching quality auditors Coach auditors and improve the audit process to ensure clear, timely and actionable feedback is sent to teams to improve their performance Perform weekly qualitative and quantitative analyses of error trends and collaborate with peers supporting other regions to aggregate, prioritize and report on the top quality issues impacting the organization Gather and analyze feedback from auditors to provide recommendations for improvements to Facebook's quality systems Develop and maintain process documentation for the end-to-end quality process to ensure consistency across regions Launch/maintain quality programs for new products and new support sites (vendor locations) Travel overnight internationally when needed (<25%) MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree in a quantitative field such as mathematics, statistics, economics or related field 3+ years of experience working in an Operations, Analytics, Product, Engineering or equivalent team 2+ years experience with Excel (PivotTable, Charts, Statistical functions) 1+ years of Project Management experience PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 2+ years of experience working with SQL Strategic thinker with analytical and problem-solving skills Self-starting, intellectually curious and creative individual comfortable operating in ambiguity Attention to detail Ability to communicate with a variety of audiences Open, collaborative and proven team player Ability to initiate and drive projects to completion with minimal guidance Avid Facebook user, a passion for the product and ensuring a good user experience"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mp6G1UAJ/", "title": "Risk Assessment Analyst, Risk and Response", "location": "Dublin, Ireland", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Risk Assessment team seeks to identify and prioritize emerging external risks, lead investigations probing our systems to evaluate these risks, deliver action-oriented assessments to benefit our partners and users, and conduct post-mortem investigations to provide critical insights to our internal cross functional stakeholders.\n \nWe're seeking a technically-minded Risk Assessment Analyst with a passion for uncovering risks and utilizing data to formulate an independent perspective when making evaluations. Our Business Risk Analyst will focus on risks within ads and commerce, while our Community Risk Analyst will focus on content-based risk. Successful candidates will excel at building and implementing frameworks, as well as creatively utilizing data to create and deliver compelling risk assessments to key partners. RESPONSIBILITIES Conduct investigations to bring deeper understanding and knowledge of potential risk areas in ads, commerce and/or our community Use data and internal tools to identify and investigate potential risk areas and patterns at scale and across abuse types Create a framework using internal data for a quantitative model of measuring risk Use quantitative & qualitative research methods to perform root cause analyses on investigative findings or high priority escalations Partner with internal experts to build a deep understanding of how, where, and why diverse forms of abuse are experienced across the platform Develop programs and methodologies that shape how we approach offensive investigations as an external actor that pressure tests our community support and/or advertisement integrity systems Synthesize investigative findings through the creation of reports and presentations that provide a coherent narrative assessing external risk Identify data and tooling requirements in order to influence project prioritization and roadmaps MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 4+ years experience in investigative, data analysis, or technical systems work 4+ years experience using SQL or R to perform advanced analysis Problem solving and analytical experience Experience communicating results of technical analyses with non-technical partners and leadership teams to influence the strategy of those teams Experience driving cases through process to resolution Experience operating strategic projects with cross-functional partners PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in one of more of the following programming languages: Python, PHP or Haskell Experience working with data visualization tools (e.g.  Tableau)"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoKtkUAF/", "title": "Global Security Event Manager", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook\u2019s Global Security Services Team is seeking a Global Security Events Manager to coordinate across all facets of the Global Security Team and will coordinate and work closely with Event Managers (non-security) across the company. This dynamic leader will work with multiple cross-functional entities to ensure comprehensive support of executives and employees at highly-visible events and conferences. The role requires strong operational, strategic, and interpersonal skills. The ideal candidate will have an understanding of the Principles of Protection, that will allow them to think independently, make constructive recommendations for program improvements, and problem solve quickly. We are looking for a customer service oriented individual that is diligent, detail-oriented, proactive, works very well both independently and in a team, and has demonstrated excellent judgment and decision-making skills. This is a full-time position with global responsibility reporting to the Director, Global Security Services and will be located at our headquarters in Menlo Park, CA office.\n \n RESPONSIBILITIES Maintain close partnerships with Facebook Global Events, Global Security Intelligence and Travel team(s). Strategically and holistically plans security support for events in coordination with non-security groups responsible for global events. Conduct security advances, and gives clear, concise security recommendations. Prepare briefings on events for Security and Business leaders. Adhere to company privacy and confidentiality guideline and policies. Engages, influences and inspires others, and should be sought out for expertise, assistance and mentorship. Inclusive and respectful in working with others, and conveys a sense of trust and integrity. Effectively interfaces with cross-functional teams on questions regarding the support of executives and employees. Can bring forward ideas to improve the program and, with limited oversight, can effectively execute. National and international travel will be required, in addition to some night and weekend assignments. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years of experience in managing event security for large (5000 plus) attendees, executive protections, protection of individuals, or similar assignment(s). Experience in protection strategies, tactics, and technology. Experience in solving logistical problems, and leading a teams of security professionals. Experience in multi-tasking. Experience in analyzing information, determining contexts, taking appropriate action, and choosing the correct course of action. Experience in adapting and maintaining productivity. Experience working in cross-functional teams. Project management experience including: organization, communications, documentation, and cross group collaboration."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoabyUAB/", "title": "University Recruiter, Product", "location": "London, United Kingdom", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook was built to help people connect and share, and over the last decade our tools have played a critical part in changing how people around the world communicate with one another. With over a billion people using the service and more than fifty offices around the globe, a career at Facebook offers countless ways to make an impact in a fast growing organization. \n \nUniversity Recruiting is in our DNA. From our start in a dorm room at Harvard, Facebook has looked to talent from universities to build the next set of new products for our 1 billion+ users that drive our mission to make the world more open and connected. The result is an opportunity to have tremendous impact at a revolutionary company. If you\u2019ve ever dreamed about disrupting and revolutionizing the way recruiting and university recruiting is done, we\u2019d love to talk with you about how you might help Facebook do just that. We are looking for someone to leverage our platform and products and to partner with the broader University Recruitment team to help us develop a stronger and more diverse pipeline that represents our global users. We take Facebook\u2019s mission of discovering top talent and serving our employees seriously. RESPONSIBILITIES Design and execute customized, full cycle staffing plans, partnering closely with analytics hiring managers to achieve the best results possible Find and engage unique and/or passive candidates through creative sourcing techniques Facilitate and lead meetings and key initiatives and projects with partner groups, and with the recruiting teams, that will continuously improve and scale our recruiting operations and results Regularly manage pipeline activity and maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders Establish and maintain meaningful relationships with management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, HR, Compensation, and Diversity teams) Collaborate with others on the recruiting team on initiatives and/ or hiring needs that may spike in other areas MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BS/BA 4+ years of Recruiting experience Excellent communication skills Ability to work cross-functionally Strong attention to detail and ability to multi-task Willingness to work flexible hours as needed Ability to travel internationally during peak recruiting cycle PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS University Recruiting experience preferred"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LJtqGUAT/", "title": "Lead Controls Specialist, Subject Matter Expert", "location": "Forest City, NC", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a Lead Controls Subject Matter Expert for our Forest City, North Carolina data center. Our data centers serve as the foundation upon which our software operates to meet the demands of our customers. The Lead Controls Subject Matter Expert will be a part of the Facility Operations team. The candidate will lead and manage a team of Controls SMEs who are the data center control system technical operations experts. This role is responsible for reliability and quality of the Building Management System (BMS). This candidate will also need exceptional leadership and management experience that will be essential for team alignment to global strategies. RESPONSIBILITIES Develop, mentor, and manage an onsite controls subject matter experts team. Be accountable for all Building Management System (BMS) operations, changes, and enhancements on a campus consisting of multiple data center buildings. Diagnose and repair complex control system malfunctions requiring extensive experience in a variety of electronic or digital controls systems, which will require an ability to test and create modifications in multiple languages of systems software. Troubleshoot and repair controls hardware including controllers, relays, measurement devices, actuators, etc. Review operating equipment data for efficiency improvements, monitor all building systems for abnormal operating trends, and make optimization adjustments accordingly. Manage controls vendors while supporting site operations, including direct oversight to all system configuration and component upgrades. Review quality control of hardware installation and review programming through commissioning process for new construction and retrofits. Provide controls scope and review proposals for retrofits and upgrades. Oversee all system configurations and component upgrades to ensure system integrity is maintained and that all modifications to existing systems are in compliance with best practices, including change control processes. Provide technical controls training and support to all Facility Operations staff. Collaborate with Global Automation and Optimization team to implement initiatives at the data center. Communicate all issues and upcoming controls work with site management. Other duties as required to support the operation of Facebook data centers. Less than twenty percent of occasional travel as required. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years of controls experience in programming development, start up, and commissioning of facility systems - central plants, air handling units, and evaporative cooling/humidification systems. Experience in data centers or other critical environments. Experience working with mechanical, electrical and life safety systems associated with critical environments. Experience interpreting and auditing blueprints/CAD drawings and controls diagrams. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Alerton experience. Experience with software programming languages: Python, PHP, SQL. Experience beyond field technician level - project management, project engineering, and operations management. IT/Networking certification."}
