ns and results Regularly manage pipeline activity and maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders Establish and maintain meaningful relationships with management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, HR, Compensation, and Diversity teams) Collaborate with others on the recruiting team on initiatives and/or hiring needs that may spike in other areas MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 4+ years of full cycle recruiting experience Experience independently partnering with leadership on hiring across time zones Experience influencing and driving toward results Experience in problem-solving across all stages of the hiring cycle Experience in compensation and general HR requirements as related to hiring PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience partnering with recruiters and hiring partners across different offices Full cycle recruiting experience across multiple tech/product disciplines Ability to work in a team-based environment"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCRJkUAP/", "title": "Technical Recruiter", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook was built to help people connect and share, and over the last decade our tools have played a critical part in changing how people around the world communicate with one another. With over a billion people using the service and more than fifty offices around the globe, a career at Facebook offers countless ways to make an impact in a fast growing organization. \n\nAs \u2018one team\u2019, People@ focuses on three major areas: hire the best people, foster continuous personal growth and enrich the overall Facebook experience. Our culture is our most important asset, and as the keepers of that culture, we\u2019re seeking folks who share our values of moving fast, openness and impact. \n\nAs a member of our recruiting team, you will conceive practical and creative ways to engage leading talent. We\u2019re passionate about disrupting the typical recruiting process in hopes to move faster. Our team takes an empathetic and transparent approach, driven and motivated to be knowledgeable partners to our candidates and hiring managers. We are collaborative in problem-solving, with high resourcefulness and tenacity in challenging situations. RESPONSIBILITIES Design and execute customized, full cycle staffing plans, partnering closely with hiring managers to achieve the best results possible Find and engage unique and/or passive candidates through creative sourcing techniques, coordinating with our sourcers as needed Facilitate and lead meetings and key initiatives and projects with client groups, and with the recruiting teams, that will continuously improve and scale our recruiting operations and results Regularly manage pipeline activity and maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders Establish and maintain meaningful relationships with management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, Compensation, and HR teams) Collaborate with others on the recruiting team on initiatives and/ or hiring needs that may spike in other areas Leverage and maintain data reports and performance metrics to drive improvements as needed MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 6+ years of relevant recruiting experience with a search agency or an in-house recruiting team Experience in full cycle recruiting experience across multiple technical & product disciplines PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Ability to consult, influence, and manage a range of stakeholders Experience in developing complex compensation packages and general HR requirements as related to hiring Consultative qualities and interpersonal skills with ability to communicate across all levels of the organization as well as externally Self-starter who can operate effectively in a fast-paced environment and navigate ambiguity independently Strong attention to detail and the ability to prioritize competing demands Strong problem-solving, data analytics and reporting skills"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LC5FgUAL/", "title": "Internal Solutions Engineer, Product & Service Operations", "location": "Austin, TX", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Product & Service Operations team supports millions of businesses by resolving their product support needs while using our ad products and ensures that businesses have a great experience while advertising on Facebook.  The Internal Solutions team within Product & Service Operations is an applications engineering team focused on solving for tools development or back-end infrastructure problems.  We partner with product and software engineering teams to build proprietary tools and techniques to provide support at scale and enforce the quality of support for all of our advertising products. \n \nSuccessful candidates for this team have a bias toward action and enjoy finding patterns amid chaos, making quick decisions, and aren't afraid of being wrong.  This position is located in our Austin, TX office. RESPONSIBILITIES Work on a global team of technical individuals leveraging technical skills such as PHP + Hack, Haskell + Haxl, JavaScript + React to successfully drive infrastructure & tool improvements for new products + existing processes and workflows Use engineering skill sets in a business organization to drive meaningful business impact by looking at problems through an operational lens Partner with cross-functional teams such as Product and Software Engineering to lead or contribute to large scale strategic projects as well as solve ongoing operational problems at scale Self-identify gaps, problems, needs, and come up with solutions with relative independence Be the gatekeeper of system integrity by deep-diving into stability issues and coming up with solutions as well as working to enhance overall code quality MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS B.A. or B.S. degree 3+ years of experience in software development Ability to write readable, and self-documented code Ability to assess, analyze and resolve issues using data, and distill that complexity into business insights Ability to communicate with technical and non-technical audiences Experience working with or in support of global communities Experience managing multiple concurrent projects and driving initiatives in a cross-functional environment PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Object oriented programming Quantitative background"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCLO6UAP/", "title": "Storage Hardware Engineer, Archival", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is looking for a Storage Hardware Engineer that is passionate about technology, about solving complex storage archival challenges, and ready to redefine storage infrastructure to meet the scale-out storage needs. The ideal candidate will have experience designing and building archival storage hardware while translating products requirements from infrastructure customers, working with Tape media, drives and libraries, developing hardware roadmaps, and working with qualification teams to develop and execute test plans. RESPONSIBILITIES Design backup storage infrastructure while considering many aspects, including, but not limited to: performance, cost, capacity, endurance, durability, data integrity, power efficiency and data center compatibility. Collaborate with cross-functional teams to develop specifications for tape storage libraries. Understand requirements from storage application teams and translate those to viable hardware solutions. Work closely with tape media, tape drive and library vendors to propose, develop, test and deploy technology optimized for Facebook data centers. Understand the underlying technologies of Tape Media, Tape Drive and Automated libraries. Evaluate various storage technology archival solutions, from HW components and architecture to data transport protocols and topologies. Design and assist development of automatic infrastructure to allow all diagnosis of HW faults and tools for inducing faults. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree in Electrical Engineering or closely related field. 3+ years of experience with Magnetic media data storage and related technologies. 3+ years of experience with Linear Tape Open (LTO) / Enterprise Tape Media and Drives. 2+ years of experience working with Linear Tape File Systems (LTFS) or related file systems. 2+ years of experience working in Linux/Unix storage environment. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience with storage and network interfaces (FiberChannel, Ethernet, SAS, SATA, PCIe). Experience with Tape media/Drive qualification processes. Experience in tape library operations in data center environments. Familiar with object and block storage applications and protocols."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mofu9UAB/", "title": "FB+ Product Recruiter (Oculus, Building 8, Camera, Social VR)", "location": "London, United Kingdom", "description": "Oculus, Building 8, Camera, and Social VR are some of the organizations that make up what we at Facebook call FB+. It is the goal of these teams to create and ship new, category-defining consumer hardware and software products that are immersive, social, and define our consumer\u2019s daily experiences. We want to enable people to experience anything, anywhere. We aim to do this at scale and to power this with a breakthrough innovation engine modeled after DARPA.\n  \nRecruiting is a core strategic driver of Facebook\u2019s success. We have a world-class team working together to help drive our ambitions and scale to the next level. This Technical Recruiter will work closely with our managers hiring for product roles to develop strategies to hire candidates within the FB+ organization. We\u2019re seeking a dynamic Recruiter who brings a level of motivation, curiosity and scrappiness to our team. RESPONSIBILITIES Design and execute customized, full cycle staffing plans, partnering closely with hiring managers to achieve the best results possible Find and engage unique and/or passive candidates through creative sourcing techniques, coordinating with our sourcers as needed Facilitate and lead meetings and key initiatives and projects with client groups, and with the recruiting teams, that will continuously improve and scale our recruiting operations and results Regularly manage pipeline activity and maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders Establish and maintain meaningful relationships with management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, HR, Compensation, and Diversity teams) Collaborate with others on the recruiting team on initiatives and/ or hiring needs that may spike in other areas MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 4+ years of full cycle recruiting experience Knowledge of recruiting funnel metrics Experience independently partnering with leadership on hiring Organizational experience Experience working in a team-based environment Experience using Microsoft Suite"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mp1H3UAJ/", "title": "Resume Review Lead", "location": "Chicago, IL", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  We are looking for a data driven, self-motivated, and self-dedicated individual to join as a Lead on our centralized Resume Review Team. We are passionate about disrupting the typical recruiting process, and we're always looking for ways to become more efficient. This role will be located in our Chicago office. RESPONSIBILITIES Plan and recommend resource alignment and workload across the team. Remove obstacles and roadblocks for the team as needed. Maintain and utilize our existing Recruiting dashboard. Communicate data trends, insights, integrity issues or process gaps. Hire, onboard, and train new teammates as needed. Provide on-going training to team on the pipelines, ATS and dashboards. Build strong relationships and work closely with Recruiting Leads to identify roles and to help prioritize the needs. Generate weekly and monthly reports and insights to present to stakeholders. Develop a deep understanding of the open role requirements to train the team to be able to quickly identify talent to meet the needs of the business. Be flexible: Think creatively. Solve problems. Pivot topics. Ruthlessly prioritize. Focus on business need. We are constantly changing and evolving, and you will need to be able to grow and evolve to meet the ever-changing needs of our business partners. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's Degree 3+ years' experience in Recruitment or People Operations Demonstrated analytical and problem-solving experience Interpersonal, communication and leadership experience Experience holding people accountable for deliverables without a formal reporting structure Process implementation or process evolution experience PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 2+ years\u2019 of experience in a people management role and/or equivalent related experience Experience building or starting up a team Demonstrated ability to work cross-functionally and strengthen relationships with clients and partners Flexibility to handle multiple tasks concurrently with attention to detail Flexibility to adapt to changing business situations Experience analyzing trends and consolidating data/information to present for review with primary stakeholders Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and deal with ambiguity Aptitude for learning new technologies"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MovGyUAJ/", "title": "Product Design Engineer", "location": "Seattle, WA", "description": "The mission of the Oculus Product Design Engineering team is to develop and launch world-class hardware that enables next-generation VR experiences.  We work closely with a wide array of creative, technical and operations partners as we push the boundaries of what is possible.\n  \nAs a Product Design Engineer at Oculus, you will take a critical role in bringing VR to our customers. You will develop structures, mechanisms, and solutions for next-generation consumer virtual reality hardware. As a member of our team, you will take the lead exploring and refining major elements of the consumer Rift through hands-on, iterative prototyping, while working with a team of diverse, top engineers. You will refine selected designs and coordinate with manufacturing experts during the production process. We are looking for someone with a productive mindset who can apply their mechanical engineering expertise to solve problems in creative, insightful ways. Our ideal candidate has strong a mechanical background, excellent prototyping skills, expert 3D CAD capability, and experience in designing and manufacturing consumer technology products.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Design and develop new Oculus hardware products. Lead small to large teams of engineers to deliver project goals with an emphasis on quality, innovation and collaboration. Own engineering activities for a major assembly or entire product throughout the entire product lifecycle, from definition and creation, through design, production, and next-gen improvements. Implement sound engineering processes and systematic approaches, while solving diverse design and manufacturing challenges. Serve as a resident expert in design engineering and design for manufacture processes. Contribute to the creation of technical specifications and product definition. Engineer parts and mechanisms that retain design intent and function according to specs. Test and evaluate design components for manufacturability and structural integrity. Coordinate with manufacturing experts to optimize part design and production processes, including assembly line set-up.  Support production throughout the manufacturing process to realize your designs. Collaborate with designers and other engineering disciplines to identify challenges and offer solutions. A desire to mentor others, lead by example, and elevate the engineering excellence of your team. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BS or higher in Mechanical Engineering 8+ years of experience in the mechanical engineering of mass-produced consumer electronics 8+ years of experience in 3D modeling in SolidWorks, ProE or NX Knowledge in mechanical design fundamentals for a variety of manufacturing methods (injection molding, stamping, casting, MIM, machining, etc.) 3+ years experience leading engineering teams Design analysis (FEA/Simulation experience) Manufacturing experience and proven record of shipping quality products Experience working with China-based vendors remotely and in-person, including a variety of engineering engagement models (CM, JDM and ODM) Experience building parts and assembling prototypes in the shop PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS History of shipping products in a new product category Mandarin and/or Cantonese language skills Experience with optical systems, depth sensors, image sensors Experience with human factors, wearable technologies and technical soft goods Experience designing products with complex thermal systems"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LJmdEUAT/", "title": "People Systems Program/Project Manager Workday HCM, Payroll & Security", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Global People Operations team strives to create and deliver a seamless and positive employee experience across the entire employee lifecycle. Leading with care and empathy, we develop efficient and simple people processes, systems, policies, and programs. We deliver data that is useful and accurate to create People-related strategies across the business. We manage people knowledge and build project management capability across our company. Our work also ensures Facebook remains protected and compliant. We strive to ensure employees feel heard and given the resources and support they need during the most important moments during their careers.\n \nThis role is responsible for the successful operation of the company-wide HR systems & Tool.  The successful candidate will work to drive optimum learning efficiency and experience for our employees by working closely with our People Tools & Engineering teams for support, design, development, implementation, delivery, and maintenance of the HR Eco systems. You will guide the product road-map through definition of features, enhancements, fixes and other functionality by understanding our internal stakeholders' needs and defining the future strategy to exceed them!\n RESPONSIBILITIES Design & Manage the Workday HCM security while working closely with business stakeholders to determine requirements, and prioritize for the People Engineering (development) team Collaborate closely with the product manager and engineers on day to day bugs, features and priorities Lead systems migration, integration, and change management of people tools Continuously seek out improvements to our processes and activities cross-functionally to create best possible learning experience for users Keep current with HR tool trends and developments and apply learning to improve internal tool and processes Provide support for compliance internal/external audits Develop an adoption, communications, and change management strategy for roll-out and ongoing changes to tools Develop and implement a support structure and recommendations for tool management and ongoing strategy (e.g. data integrity, usability, etc.) Leverage best practices from industry in influencing and driving People systems strategy Make recommendations on program changes and conduct cost/benefit analysis of potential improvements Develop business and cost justifications for program initiation and funding approval Lead design and review sessions with technical and functional resources at all levels, including members of management Lead the cross-functional Learn project and working groups Consult as the subject matter expert with partners and users to find solutions Investigate and evaluate opportunities to improve work flows and delivery models to increase efficiency and delivery velocity MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years of project management experience in an HR/Operations/Technology environment Experience in building and driving projects/program for people tools, including manager and employee facing solutions Experience working with multiple stakeholder groups to implement tool/system changes Experience with change management specific to a new tool implementation Experience resolving any blockers in projects or initiatives underway that are impeding program success Experience working with both engineering and end-user groups to identify, prioritize and scope tool requirements Experience with PMI Project Management Body of Knowledge (PMBOK) Experience with project methodologies such as Agile, Scrum, Kanban, and Waterfall Experience with various systems solutions and Technical requirements associated with various tools in large enterprises PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Workday HCM configuration, Workday Security design, Payroll background, SAP, Workday, PeopleSoft product or custom built solutions and program management experience Experience with implementing and designing HCM Security: Workday, SuccessFactor, SAP, Oracle, and PeopleSoft Payroll business process experience Product management experience or experience in an HRIS/HRIT role Experience implementing solutions (out of the box) or custom built tools"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LCgWKUA1/", "title": "Business Process Controls Manager", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking an experienced Program Manager to manage various aspects of business process control operations. The Business Process Controls team is chartered with the critical mission to ensure sufficient process controls are established in all material management activities performed at our data centers globally. Program management activities involve continuous and ongoing stakeholder engagement, KPI management, continuous improvement, design and implementation of scalable and efficient processes, developing the roadmap, executing the roadmap and providing critical inputs to process automation. This role requires a full understanding of procure to pay and its impacts to receiving, asset lifecycle management, inventory management, transportation, tax and trade compliance.  RESPONSIBILITIES Responsible for developing and maintaining process workflows to support various programs in Business Process Controls space including Material intake, Material life cycle management, Material disposals, Material transfers, New Product Introduction, System of record, Inventory control, Fixed asset audits, Trade compliance, and Tax Collaborate closely with cross-functional teams including data center site operations, Sourcing, Accounting, Finance, Trade Compliance and Tax teams to implement logistics/business processes in a global environment Responsible for developing required process documentation for business process implementation and rollout Responsible for establishing appropriate KPIs to measure process performance and identifying process improvement opportunities Responsible for stakeholder engagement, assessment of ongoing business needs and building short-term and long-term roadmap to support business needs Responsible for developing standard processes and tooling needs to support program requirements for Infrastructure material management focusing on scale and efficiency Responsible for supporting implementation of technology solutions and process automations efforts to improve material visibility, enhance controls and to improve process efficiency Maintain data integrity across multiple systems, identify root causes and resolve data inconsistencies MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA or BS degree in Supply Chain Management, Business, Operations, or equivalent experience 5+ years of work experience related to logistics, materials management, supply chain management or similar experience Experience designing end-to-end processes that scale, particularly with respect to supply chain management and logistics Experience collaborating with cross-functional teams to implement logistics or business processes in a global environment Experience in data collection and data analysis Analytical and problem-solving experience"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LJk1XUAT/", "title": "Managing Director and Vice President, India", "location": "Gurgaon, India", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  As we continue with our commitment to invest in the company\u2019s strategic relationships and growth in India, we are seeking the highest caliber executive leader to spearhead this evolution. \nThis exceptional people leader will have a proven track record of delivering success in a high performing organization and will have responsibility for all market facing functions.  This includes Partnerships, Policy, Communications, and Global Marketing Solutions.  This role will empower these cross-functional leaders during a pivotal time as we transform our business to achieve our objectives globally and in country. This candidate should have a deep understanding of the market opportunities and will create an inspiring vision to set objectives and run day to day operations. This position reports into the Global Head of our Global Marketing Solutions Team and will be based in our Gurgaon, India office.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Define and drive Facebook's India strategy with short, medium term and long-term goals Lead Facebook\u2019s business in India including Sales & Marketing, Partnerships, Corporate and Government engagement Represent Facebook externally across a diverse range of strategic interests and matters Represent the needs of India, our business, external market dynamics and strategic opportunities globally within Facebook and lead the company's planning for India Lead Facebook's organization across multiple locations and cross-functional teams Develop capabilities needed to fuel Facebook\u2019s growth in India anticipating future needs Build long term strategic partnerships with the largest clients, governmental bodies, industry groups and C level leaders Provide strategic business analytic strength to help drive initiatives critical to ongoing growth Establish strategic, financial and operating targets in alignment with long term strategic plan Act as a thought leader to grow Facebook\u2019s footprint in India for our community, our advertisers and our partners Lead a team of diverse senior leaders playing a critical role in building, leading and inspiring a high performing commercial and business development organization Ensure teams retain functional connection and strength to Facebook headquarters Driving and ensuring collaboration amongst cross-functional teams in India, developing a One-India narrative and creating an inclusive organization Build a strong Facebook culture centered on our values and setting the highest standards of integrity and compliance MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Previous MD/CEO and significant divisional leadership is required Reputation as a thought leader running large complex businesses who is already highly regarded as a senior executive in the market Overall 15-20 years of senior leadership experience with a minimum of 12-15 years\u2019 experience in leading global consultative sales & marketing global organisations and business development teams Influential at C Suite level externally and comfortable influencing at Exec levels internally Deep experience in developing a market for digital solutions and developing strategic partnerships Experience of strategically developing new businesses and new markets for scale A proven record of government, industry body and partner engagement on strategic matters Proven and consistent track record of executing against high growth targets, operating a P&L and leading large-scale investment programs Proven experience managing multiple functions across diverse business areas at scale Understanding of business clients and their needs, track record in the acquisition of new clients and entering new markets, experience in managing, developing and monetizing existing customers to the next level Previous experience successfully leading larger teams of 100 professionals or more: Will need to be comfortable in leading experienced leadership teams, growing talent and developing organisational culture PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Excellent education: University diploma or MBA in marketing or business-related subject preferred Passionate about diversity and its value to teams, culture, leadership, business"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MouqGUAR/", "title": "University Recruiting, Recruiter", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  University Recruiting is in our DNA. From our start in a dorm room at Harvard, Facebook has looked to talent from universities to build the next set of new products for our 1 billion+ users that drive our mission to make the world more open and connected. The result is an opportunity to have tremendous impact at a revolutionary company. If you've ever dreamed about disrupting and revolutionizing the way recruiting and university recruiting is done, we'd love to talk with you about how you might help Facebook do just that. We are looking for someone to leverage our platform and products and to partner with the broader University Recruitment team to help us develop a stronger and more diverse pipeline that represents our global users. We take Facebook's mission of discovering top talent and serving our employees seriously.\n \n \n \n RESPONSIBILITIES Manage end-to-end recruitment process for both university and intern hiring, ensuring a smooth and positive candidate experience Collaborate with business leaders and hiring managers to understand hiring needs and goals, and to develop, implement, and execute a custom hiring strategy Identify and engage unique and/or passive candidates through creative sourcing techniques Drive offer process - including extending offers, closing candidates, generating offer letters Foster relationships with key stakeholders at targeted universities Regularly manage pipeline activity and maintain data integrity, and proactively share data-centric updates with internal stakeholders Act as an internally and externally-facing representative of Facebook and our talent acquisition team Establish and maintain meaningful relationships with management and key cross-functional stakeholders internally (e.g. Recruiting, HR, Compensation, and Diversity teams) Collaborate with others on the recruiting team on initiatives and/or hiring needs that may spike in other areas Partner with other university recruiting team members to collaborate on campus recruiting efforts Willingness to work flexible hours as needed Ability to travel during peak recruiting cycles MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Communication experience Experience working cross-functionally Experience communicating across all levels of an organization, as well as externally PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Bachelors Degree or higher 2+ years University Recruiting experience Strong attention to detail Ability to multi-task"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1200000KujbCEAR/", "title": "Data Center Controls Engineer", "location": "Odense, Denmark", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a Controls Engineer to join our Odense, Denmark Data Center facility operations team. Our data centers serve as the foundation upon which our software operates to meet the demands of our customers.  This role is responsible for reliability and quality of the Building Management System (BMS).  The candidate will support data center daily operations, and global quality / standardization initiatives. RESPONSIBILITIES Accountable for all Building Management System (BMS) operations, changes, and enhancements on a campus consisting of multiple data center buildings. Diagnose and repair complex control system malfunctions requiring extensive knowledge of a variety of electronic or digital controls systems and ability to test and write modifications in multiple languages of systems software. Troubleshoot and repair controls hardware including controllers, relays, measurement devices, actuators, etc. Review operating equipment data for efficiency improvements, monitor all building systems for abnormal operating trends, and make optimization adjustments accordingly. Manage controls vendors while supporting site operations, including direct oversight to all system configuration and component upgrades. Review quality control of hardware installation and review programming through commissioning process for new construction and retrofits. Provide controls scope and review proposals for retrofits and upgrades. Oversee all system configurations and component upgrades to ensure system integrity is maintained and that all modifications to existing systems are in compliance with best practices, including change control processes. Provide technical controls training and support to all Facility Operations staff. Collaborate with Global Automation and Optimization team to implement initiatives at the data center. Communicate all issues and upcoming controls work with site management. Other duties as required to support the operation of Facebook data centers. Occasional travel as required. <10% MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5 years of controls experience in programming development, start up, and commissioning of complex systems central plants, air handling units, and evaporative cooling/humidification systems.  Alerton experience preferred. Bachelors/Associates degree in Engineering/Technical studies, Military Technical School, or equivalent work experience. Experience in data centers or other critical environments. Working knowledge of mechanical, electrical and life safety systems associated with critical environments. Ability to read and audit blueprints/CAD drawings and controls diagrams. Strong communication and organizational skills. Experience with common software programming languages is preferred python, PHP, SQL. Experience beyond field technician level is preferred project management, project engineering, and operations management. IT/Networking certification is preferred."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MohmwUAB/", "title": "Director, Vendor Management, Community Operations", "location": "Dublin, Ireland", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is searching for an Operations Leader with a track record of transformational impact on customer experience managing global vendor operations across several thousand staff in customer support, compliance or risk operations. We are looking for a  leader who can help continue to scale our global fooptrint rapidly to provide around the clock support to our community of 2B+ people in multiple dozen languages while challenging industry standards to provide a unique and supportive work environment to retain top talent and connect our global teams with a deep sense of purpose to keep our community safe. We are looking for a self-starter with an entrepreneurial and strategic mindset who proactively anticipates risks and opportunities and partners cross-functionally to address these and influences investments. \n \nThe leader will be responsible for location strategy, site expansion, global service delivery and all compliance and relationship mgmt aspects of our vendor operations. A successful candidate will have to be decisive and make data-backed decisions based on deep understanding of Facebook\u2019s operations combined with openness to adapt to a constantly changing product landcape and external environment. We are looking for a leader who intrinsically connects with Facebook\u2019s committment to keep our community safe and is equally a strong advocate for our vendor staff who is able to represent our operations externally in partnership with communications and policy teams. \n RESPONSIBILITIES Shape vision on how to scale and transform large-scale service, risk and compliance operations including vendor and location strategy, site expansion and compliance Drive alignment on staffing, infrastructure, tooling and facility investments with leadership across Ops, Engineering, Policy, Security and Finance functions. Define and execute on strategies to maximize impact and efficiency of our global workforce on service and community safety as well as company risk mitigation objectives across a broad set of Ops functions in partnership with Engineering and Ops stakeholders while delivering best-in-class community experience . Drive continuous improvement through effective feedback processes to address policy, product, tooling challenges based on prioritized feedback from frontline staff Partner with resilience experts to ensure best in class  support for our global workforce and refine and continue to define effective audit mechanisms for compliance Lead and develop senior leaders to foster a culture of integrity, service excellence, accountability, innovation, best practice sharing across sites and functions and build external partner/vendor relationships that mirror this culture Role requires at least 30% domestic and international travel. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Significant experience in senior leadership roles leading vendor operations for relevant scale in domains such as compliance, risk, customer support, shared services, business process outsourcing Deep domain expertise in all aspects of large scale operations, specifically vendor management, outsourcing, location strategy and program management Superior fiscal, negotiation and contract management expertise Ability to remain calm and effective under pressure and coach teams to effectively navigate and communicate in a fast paced and ambiguous environment. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Strong communicator who can represent Facebook externally in partnership with policy and communication team"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MotDrUAJ/", "title": "Recruiting Program Specialist, Biz", "location": "Dublin, Ireland", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a highly organized and detail-oriented Recruiting Program Coordinator. The role will support the EMEA Business Pod Recruiting Teams by coordinating projects for Interviewer capacity, calibration & training across EMEA.The Business Pod includes teams as Online Operations, Partnerships, General & Admin (G&A), Policy & Comms, People@. Additionally, this position will support our Candidate Care Team projects and programs such as building operational review models, support structures and our candidate care survey. A small percentage of recruiting coordination is part of the role and to partner closely with the Recruiting Coordination Lead and Recruiting Managers to drive a top class interview experience for all those involved in the process. This includes analyzing interview declines, reschedules, candidate care scores, room availability, swag, recruiter/coordinator partnerships and anything else that impacts the candidate experience. This regular employment position is Full-Time and based in Dublin or London RESPONSIBILITIES Develop, execute and maintain consistent programs for the Biz team ensuring cross collaboration with other EMEA program specialists. Program manage interviewer capacity planning, calibration and trainings by collaborating with recruiting coordinators, leads and business sponsor. Attending weekly meetings with recruiting leads and business managers who are responsible for site/business growth to understand impact on interview pools. Compile, forecast, analyze & report on data and metrics on interviewer capacity and calibration with interviewing activity to inform the recruiting strategy and work with Recruiting Leads to remove bottlenecks to support business growth. Partner with Recruiting teams on cross-functional projects relating to enhancing the candidate experience and scalable scheduling solutions across Biz, this includes interviewer training, reschedules, candidate care scores, recognition etc. Growing and maintaining the interviewer pools for Biz and assisting with batch day interviewer planning. Monitor interview feedback, driving improvements to ensure it is submitted within SLA and is high quality. Upkeep of interviewer dashboard integrity, pulling reports and data ownership. Reviewing the candidate care survey and highlighting trends, training and project opportunities. Collaborating with the Coordinator and Tools teams to recommend and drive any system or tool improvements & efficiencies. Liaise with University Recruiting to understand their hiring targets, how it will impact existing interviewer pools and plan accordingly with recruiting and business leads. Identify and remove bottlenecks as well as forecasting for peak interview seasons Develop and maintain an effective Communication plan for our candidate care team in EMEA. Develop and maintain a project roadmap for all projects within Biz. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 1+ years\u2019 experience with recruiting programs driving change and operational excellence in a fast-paced, constantly evolving environment 3+ years\u2019 experience scheduling and coordinating complex interview loops Highly organized with the ability to prioritize multiple functions and tasks while managing your work time efficiently and maintaining great attention to detail. Ability to work autonomously and partner with senior level recruiting partners and business leaders. Self-directed, proactive and detailed orientated problem solver with demonstrated experience and creativity in developing and improving processes Demonstrated project management skills and and ability to effectively influence and communicate cross-functionally and regionally Communication, collaboration and interpersonal skills Experience working with or in support of diverse communities. Working knowledge of Facebook Recruiting Team organizational structure, roles, tools, processes and procedures helpful but not essential Highly proficient in Word, Excel, Outlook and/or PC based calendar applications Comfortable developing and delivering presentations to large groups Strategic thinker with data analysis and analytical skills."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LBfhHUAT/", "title": "Global Partner Lead", "location": "Dublin, Ireland", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a motivated, highly-organized, detail-oriented candidate with impeccable judgment to join the Payments Compliance Team in Dublin. Reporting to the Compliance Operations Manager the role will be responsible for ensuring the development of a scalable and efficient compliance operations team. \nYou will work collaboratively with a dynamic group of XFN stakeholders including but not limited to Vendors, Legal, Product, Engineering, Finance and Marketing. You will help Facebook Payments ensure that its compliance policies, internal controls and systems help Facebook in its mission to \"bring the world closer together.\" \nThe successful candidate will be primarily responsible for the management of our growing outsourcing vendors and ensuring that the resulting assets are delivered on schedule, to budget and meet the quality goals set by Facebook and Payments Compliance Leadership. RESPONSIBILITIES Provide mentorship, guidance and career development to members of your team Lead and enable a high-performing team to deliver on operational goals by providing superb 1:1 support, and enabling deeper, more scalable solutions Ensuring the team are actively maintaining system integrity by processing updates in WFM systems and tools, including, but not limited to: historical and seasonal trending updates for forecasts, weekly BU service level files, schedule updates, and user data in WFM system Proactively identifying and reporting issues impacting Teammate productivity \u2013 partnering with Operations and other Support Functions in communicating and managing the impacts to both our Customers and Teammates Partnering with the business to make judgment calls and decisions to deliver the optimal levels of service and productivity - demonstrating responsibility and professionalism in balancing customer and shareholder needs Preparing analysis and insights for the business to enable robust decision making that will ultimately improve efficiency and performance in a customer focused way Analyzing and understanding Productivity, Shrinkage, Occupancy, Attrition and Staffing trends in partnership with other members of the WFM team Create and deliver analysis recommendations and findings to the Global Ops Manager, Planning Manager, executive staff, and key stakeholders Understand top payments compliance concerns and other quality or customer insight data, and support your team in making recommendations to improve our product, policies, and procedures to keep the platform safe Oversight of a growing vendor team to ensure that TATs and SLAs are maintained Supporting the scaling of operations through diligent resource planning, volume forecasting and upstream risk management MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Relevant BA/BS qualification \nSignificant experience working in tech, consulting, or an operational capacity\nStrong people management experience leading an operations team related to Fraud, Anti-Money Laundering, Customer/Enhanced Due Diligence investigation or verifications\nIndependent decision making and follow through\nStrong analytical skills and unwavering attention to detail\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills\nPassion for ensuring a good user experience\nPrior experience with analytical tools (like Excel, SQL, or R) is a plus\nMust possess and maintain an ACAMS certification, or be able to do so within one year."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mp1GHUAZ/", "title": "Electrical Engineer, Building 8", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Building 8 brings together world-class experts to develop and ship groundbreaking products at the intersection of hardware, software, and content. We have a clear mandate to ship products at scale. In particular, seemingly impossible products that define new categories that advance Facebook's mission of connecting the world. The B8 team will apply DARPA-style breakthrough development at the intersection of ambitious science and product development. It will operate on aggressive, fixed timelines, with extensive use of partnerships in universities, small and large businesses. The Product Launch Team has the responsibility for taking breakthroughs and delivering them to market at scale. Building 8 seeks an Electrical Engineer who has experience in consumer electronics and mobile products. We are looking for a slightly impatient individual willing to face down their fear of failure to accomplish bold things. This is a full-time position based in our Menlo Park office. RESPONSIBILITIES Transform vendor reference designs, or block diagrams into custom solutions Design, implement, debug and characterize embedded systems with end-to-end ownership of EE product design from concept to launch Design schematics, complete board layouts, assembly, test, debug, and integrate designs into opto electro-mechanical systems Collaborate closely with cross-functional teams such industrial design, architecture, product design, NPI, and supply chain Work closely with CM/JDM resources to leverage their engineers and maximize the focus of our internal resources on adding value to and differentiating our product Drive the resolution of technical issues by working with the cross-functional teams: Electrical, Mechanical, SW, Quality, Reliability as well as the various CM/JDM teams Perform lab measurements, and factory tests as needed to validate the design and resolve any issues Track test progress, bugs, and fixes and produce regular progress reports MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BS or MS in Electrical Engineering or related fields 5+ years of experience in consumer electronics or related fields 5+ years of experience in embedded or mobile system design, hardware architecture, board design, board bring-up and product NPI experience Experience and knowledge of printed circuit board (PCB) technologies, such as rigid, flex, hybrid, HDI, etc. Experience leading technical teams, cross-functional groups and vendors against plans PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Knowledge of the relationship between physical layout and electrical performance Ability to run signal integrity simulations"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MotVyUAJ/", "title": "Electrical Engineer, Systems (Oculus)", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": "The Oculus team at Facebook is helping more people around the world come together and connect through excellent VR hardware and software. With global departments dedicated to VR research, computer vision, haptics, social interaction, and more. Oculus is committed to driving the state-of-the-art forward through relentless innovation. VR\u2019s potential to change the world is immense\u2014and we are just getting started. \n \nAs the Product Development team, we are builders who break down barriers to what is possible. Together we design hardware that transforms technology into product.\n \nAs an Electrical Engineer at Oculus you will design, simulate, implement, and debug systems and circuits used in virtual reality hardware. You will experiment with and develop novel solutions to the myriad of complex electrical problems sitting between reality and virtual reality. You will work closely with mechanical, optical, computer vision and software engineers on exploration and definition of advanced virtual reality systems. You will own the electrical design from prototype to production. You should have deep experience in complex PCBA development integrating processors, cameras, sensors and video/data interfaces.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Design electrical hardware systems in Oculus products that may include application and signal processing chipsets, motion and image sensors, displays, wireless, power supplies, and other support circuitry - from concept to production. Participate in technical discussion and collaborate with the cross-functioning teams such as product design, firmware, core tech, and program management during the product development phase. Support products development from initial concept through mass production. Specify, evaluate, define and select key components. Develop relationships with key technology vendors and partners, driving roadmaps and custom solutions. Analyze, validate, and characterize hardware design. Own PCB schematic and drive board layout. Travel both domestically and internationally up to 15% time. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor of Science degree in Electrical Engineering or equivalent. 5+ years of experience in electrical hardware development. Experience with system level integration of products using SoCs and micro-controllers, data and video interfaces such as USB, HDMI, DisplayPort, and MIPI. Experience with high density and high speed circuit board design and validation. Experience working with JDM, ODM, CM partners. Experience with schematic and PCB design using Cadence OrCAD/Allegro or equivalent. Experience analyzing root cause, design debugging, and problem solving with engineering test equipment. Experience working independently with minimal guidance and experience in handling multiple tasks. Experience working cross\u2010functionally, communicating technical ideas. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 7+ years of experience in electrical hardware development. Experience in any of following areas: latest wireless technology, product compliance, and Signal/Power Integrity analysis. Experience in hardware product development with organization developing consumer electronics."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MopmwUAB/", "title": "Network Hardware Engineer", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Driven by our rapid growth, Facebook is looking to take advantage of the efficiency gained by optimizing our network hardware for our data centers. Our network platform is industry-leading for its efficiency, throughput, scalability, reliability and intelligence. Facebook is looking for a Network Hardware Engineer to support the development of the overall network equipment of Facebook and shape the next generation of network that goes into our massively scalable data centers. RESPONSIBILITIES Develop systems for Facebook\u2019s next generation network across a broad range of technologies including switch, router, and transport. Drive new design ideas and develop solutions for Facebook data center networking, bringing them from concept to operations. Design the next generation of open network devices and integrate these into highly scalable, deplorable and maintainable systems. Support the hardware design, debug, validation and optimization of the products. Work in a collaborative environment across Facebook and with ODM's & OEM's and suppliers to drive Facebook's requirements for development, planning, operation and deployment. Work with ODM and CM suppliers to evaluate existing designs and work towards developing cost-effective and innovate custom designs that meet Facebook networking requirements. Involvement in projects from concept through production, perform the design review across different cross-functional teams, gaining exposure to the complete design life cycle. Support the engineering builds with high volume manufacturing. Support production operation of Facebook's network platform across our data center, develop efficient automation tools to improve operation efficiency. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 7+ years of experience with PCB board level design and layout, high speed interconnect and switching using merchant silicon ASICs. 7+ years of hardware development experience, with emphasis in network equipment field, such as switch, router, or transport. Proven track record of conceptualizing and delivering engineering solutions to customers. 7+ years of experience working with ODM and CM suppliers. 7+ years of experience with environmental testing and electrical certifications. 7+ years of programming experience in test/measurement automation and/or simulation. PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Strong knowledge of data center switching, routing, and network protocols. Advanced knowledge in signal integrity and high-speed design. Knowledge or experience in semiconductor devices, VLSI design, microelectronic device. Programming experience in test/measurement automation and/or simulation. Experience with open-source software tools. Linux knowledge or other embedded environments."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MozDHUAZ/", "title": "Strategic Partner Manager, Community Partnerships", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is building a partnerships team to focus on the second half of our mission \u201cbringing the world closer together.\u201d This team will be focused on the ways that our products and programs can we used to help people build common ground and bridge divides. You should be passionate about building products and programs that empower communities to be civil, empathetic, informed, and healthy.\n \nYou will work with some of the world\u2019s best academic, expert, and influential civil society organizations, as well as our world class Product, Engineering, Policy, Legal, Marketing, and PR teams to develop products, experiences, and programs that improve the societal problems that manifest on Facebook. A qualified candidate will have a strong passion and curiosity for the role of technology in society, the impact Facebook can have to bridge divides, and the potential for partnerships to better society. \n \nThis position is located in our Menlo Park, CA office.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Manage relationship with community of experts, academics, and community leaders to partner with Facebook Host co-learning workshops between partners and product teams, and develop new models for collaborative product development Develop content and lead trainings for partners on how to use Facebook to build common ground Help develop a framework and criteria for partner selection, and serve as primary owner of influential external relationships Collaborate with product teams to translate product learnings and insights into product solutions Lead all elements of multiple complex high-visibility collaboration deliverables for internal and external stakeholders Willingness and ability to travel 20% of the time MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 7+ years of work experience with product and/or partnerships in consumer technology, news media, political organizations, or start ups Experience engaging with C-level of any partner organization Knowledge of the Facebook Platform and how its products could be leveraged to build community and build common ground Organizational, project management, and people management experience Experience presenting in public, and communicating to internal and external audiences Experience navigating and working with cross-functional teams PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience studying or working on bridging divides, polarization, or reconciliation Experience leading a partnerships team Experience in a product training and/or product adoption role Comfort with fast-paced start-up environment with little supervision and appetite for intensity Fluency in any other language International experience Displaying the highest personal integrity and ethics"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoqPfUAJ/", "title": "Program Manager, Developer Programs, North America", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking an experienced Program Manager who is passionate about the way Facebook can work with startups and developers to drive real-world outcomes. You will focus on building and scaling programs to help developers and startups in the region to build and grow their businesses. You will engage with some of the region's most exciting companies, VCs, Accelerators/Incubators, and developer ecosystem as well as with our world-class Facebook Platform product and engineering teams. In addition, you will work cross-functionally with the Policy, Legal, Marketing and Operations teams to help startups and our partners succeed. This role is based in Menlo Park.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Help drive and execute the North America strategy for Developer Circles and FbStart Maintain direct and active relationships with  developers and startups on our platform, including on-boarding and contract work, proactively resolving business, technical, and policy issues and serving as an internal advocate Manage high-touch and low-touch engagement programs and events Set, track, analyze, communicate, and execute against key program performance metrics Work cross-functionally with product, engineering, business development, partnerships, policy, legal, marketing, and PR to launch programs and execute them Willingness and ability to travel 25-50% of the time MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA or BS Degree 5+ years experience in program management, partner management, or equivalent work experience Software development with experience building software developed in (at least one) Python, Node.js, PHP, C/C++, Ruby, C#, or Java 3+ years experience in engaging with the developer and/or startup community in North America Developer and/or startup event organizing experience Presentation experience Experience translating developer and startup needs into strategic plans and vice versa PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS in Computer Science or equivalent degree/experience Proven track record of launching, leading and scaling programs in a fast-paced, rapidly changing environment Exceptional collaboration and relationship-building skills \u2014 with the ability to develop strong working relationships at all levels of management, both inside and outside Facebook Displaying the highest personal integrity and ethics Fluency in English, any other languages"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoqPQUAZ/", "title": "Program Manager, Developer Programs,  Content", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking an experienced Program Manager who is passionate about the way Facebook can work with startups and developers to drive real-world outcomes. You will focus on working with internal teams at Facebook as well as external partners to collate and develop content that will improve the learning experiences of the developers and startups that make up our developer program communities. In addition, you will work cross-functionally with the Policy, Legal, Marketing and Operations teams to help startups and our partners succeed. This role is based in Menlo Park.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Help drive and execute the content strategy for Developer Circles and FbStart Create, maintain and execute a content calendar for Developer Circles and FbStart online and offline programs Maintain direct and active relationships with startups and developers on our platform, to gather feedback on how to improve their learning experience in both programs Engage with external content partners Author engaging developer-facing communication such as social posts, guides, keynote presentations and more Set, track, analyze, communicate, and execute against key program performance metrics Work cross-functionally with product, engineering, business development, partnerships,  legal  and marketing launch develop, curate and deploy content to Developer Circles and FbStart communities Willingness and ability to travel 25-50% of the time MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA or BS Degree 5+ years experience in program management, partner management, or equivalent work experience Software development with experience building software developed in (at least one) Python, Node.js, PHP, C/C++, Ruby, C#, or Java 1+ years of experience using SQL or equivalent and Excel 1+ years experience in engaging with the developer and/or startup community Developer and/or startup event organizing experience Presentation experience Experience translating developer and startup needs into strategic plans and vice versa PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS BA/BS in Computer Science or equivalent degree/experience Proven track record of launching, leading and scaling programs in a fast-paced, rapidly changing environment Exceptional collaboration and relationship-building skills \u2014 with the ability to develop strong working relationships at all levels of management, both inside and outside Facebook Displaying the highest personal integrity and ethics Fluency in English, any other languages"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mok7wUAB/", "title": "Strategic Partner Manager, Community Programs", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  For the past decade, Facebook has focused on connecting friends and families. With that foundation, our next focus will be developing the social infrastructure for community \u2013 for supporting us, for keeping us safe, for informing us, for civic engagement, and for inclusion of all. We are at the beginning of this journey and are looking for someone who is interested in shaping our strategies through work with external partners. \n\nFacebook is building an experienced programs team that is passionate about the way Facebook can break the barriers community leaders face - funding, support, belief, and tools.  You should be obsessed with technology, social media and business strategy to build a variety of valuable program experiences for people to become part of such communities. \n\nYou will work with some of the world\u2019s best organization and as well as community leaders as well as our world class product and engineering teams. In addition to those teams, you will work cross-functionally with the Policy, Legal, Marketing, PR and the Operations teams to optimize new capabilities, improve user experience, and make our partners successful. A qualified candidate will have a strong passion and curiosity for innovative social products and their potential for transforming communities. This position is located in our Menlo Park, CA office.\n\n\n\n RESPONSIBILITIES Lead Programs and Operations team so that the team can scale work and support to Community Leaders globally Drive program strategy through strategic partnerships with community leaders - both people and organizations Define market requirements, produce qualitative and quantitative analysis of program performance, explore new strategic opportunities, inform the future roadmap with enhanced or new program, and ensure program and industry impact Build operational processes for programs to be able to scale and define and execute measurement processes and tools Maintain direct and active relationships with partners, including proactively resolving business, technical, and policy issues and serving as an internal advocate Work cross-functionally with product, engineering, business development, partnerships, policy, legal, marketing, and PR to launch products and partnerships - to develop, implement and deliver value-add initiatives for community leaders Manage multiple complex project deliverables for multiple internal and external stakeholders Provide guidance to community leaders in defining, analyzing, and measuring of their community management problems Represent Facebook in external meetings with executives from other companies,  including proactively resolving technical and policy issues and serving as an internal advocate Willingness and ability to travel 20% of the time MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Experience building communities 10+ years of work experience with programs, product, partnership, or technical experience in consumer technology companies Knowledge of the Facebook Platform and how its products could be leveraged to build community Leadership building experience PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Proven track record of organizational, creative, and strategic-thought leadership Fluency in any other language Ability to define, develop and lead large programs in a fast-paced, rapidly changing environment Exceptional collaboration and relationship-building skills \u2014 with the ability to develop strong working relationships at all levels of management A strong passion for innovation and collaboration with startups and early stage entrepreneurs and developers Displaying the highest personal integrity and ethics"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MozWMUAZ/", "title": "Program Manager, Indonesia", "location": "Jakarta, Indonesia", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking an experienced Program Manager who is passionate about the way Facebook can work with developers and startups in Indonesia to drive real-world outcomes. You will focus on building and scaling programs to help developers in Indonesia engage in meaningful communities, expand their skill sets and enable their success. You will engage with exciting companies, VCs, Accelerators/Incubators,  and tech ecosystem as well as with our world-class Facebook Platform product and engineering teams. In addition, you will work cross-functionally with the Policy, Legal, Marketing and Operations teams to help developers, startups, and our partners succeed. \nThis role is based in Jakarta.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Help drive and execute the program and product strategy for the startup ecosystem in APAC by gathering aggregated feedback from startups and developers Maintain direct and active relationships with startups and developers on our platform, including on-boarding and contract work, proactively resolving business, technical, and policy issues and serving as an internal advocate Manage high-touch and low-touch engagement programs Set, track, analyze, communicate, and execute against key program performance metrics Work cross-functionally with product, engineering, business development, partnerships, policy, legal, marketing, and PR to launch programs and execute them MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BA or BS Degree 5+ years experience in program management, partner management, or equivalent work experience Fluency in English and Bahasa Indonesia PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Programming experience in one or more of the following languages: Java, PHP, JavaScript, Objective-C, Ruby, Python, React, React Native Exceptional collaboration and relationship-building skills \u2014 with the ability to develop strong working relationships at all levels of management, both inside and outside Facebook. Displaying the highest personal integrity and ethics Proven track record of launching, leading and scaling programs in a fast-paced, rapidly changing environment Willingness and ability to travel 25-50% of the time"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Lgo0VUAR/", "title": "Strategic Partner Manager, Core Platform", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking an experienced Strategic Partnerships professional who is passionate about the way Facebook can work with businesses, startups, and developers to build a variety of valuable product experiences for people and has an interest in technology, social media and business strategy. \n \nDeveloper Partnerships at Facebook is responsible for establishing and managing strategic relationships with our key product partners and the developer ecosystem. You will work with some of the world\u2019s most exciting companies and startups as well as with our world-class Facebook Platform product and engineering teams. In addition to those teams, you will work cross-functionally with the Policy, Legal, Marketing, PR and the Operations teams to optimize new capabilities, improve user experience, and make our partners successful. This position is located in Menlo Park, CA.  RESPONSIBILITIES Help drive product strategy through strategic partnerships with businesses, developers, and leading consumer product organizations Define market requirements, produce qualitative and quantitative analysis of product performance, aggregate feedback, explore new strategic opportunities, inform the product roadmap with enhanced or new functionality, and ensure product and industry impact in region Track, analyze and communicate key quantitative metrics and business trends as they relate to partner relationships Represent Facebook in external meetings with executives from other companies Maintain direct and active relationships with developers on our platform, including on-boarding and contract work, proactively resolving business, technical, and policy issues and serving as an internal advocate Work cross-functionally with product, engineering, business development, partnerships, policy, legal, marketing, and PR to launch products and partnerships Willingness and ability to travel 25% of the time MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years of work experience with product, partnership, or technical experience in consumer technology companies Experience defining, developing and leading projects Collaboration and relationship-building experience \u2014 with the experience developing working relationships at all levels of management Knowledge of Facebook Platform and their strategic and competitive positions Displaying the highest personal integrity and ethics Fluency in English PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 5+ years of mobile focused work experience with product, partnership, or technical experience in consumer technology companies A strong curiosity for innovative social products and their potential for transforming businesses and industries"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MofLsUAJ/", "title": "Camera and Depth Modules Lead", "location": "Redmond, WA", "description": "Facebook Reality Labs(FRL), the research division for AR/VR for Facebook, is looking for a world-class Camera and Depth Modules Lead to develop the next generation imaging and depth sensor modules for AR and VR devices. The successful candidate will be part of the sensing team innovating, developing and integrating hardware and algorithms for future generations of HMD devices.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Drive definition, design, development, and integration of mobile high-quality camera and depth modules including sensors, optics, light sources, image processing and depth processing Execute module development and system integration with internal research and engineering teams, and third-party vendors Define and develop depth processing algorithms Create technology road map from proof of concepts to final form factor, low power, high performance imaging and depth modules to be incorporated into HMDs Define testing and qualification plans of the modules at different stages of the development, from concept to product ramp Managing all technical aspect of external partnerships. Oversee technology and product development with external partners throughout all phases of execution International and domestic travel is required MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BS/MS/PhD in Optics, Electrical Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, Imaging Science, Physics or related field 7+ years of experience in imaging camera (RGB, IR) and depth camera (stereo, structured light, ToF) development, sensing system design and integration 5+ years experience in light projector and illumination system design 5+ years experience in depth imaging system signal processing and calibration Knowledge of overall systems interactions in the image pipeline Knowledge of computer vision algorithms and applications Experience leading cross-functional teams and owning responsibility for project Experience programming with C/C++, OpenGL, Python, MATLAB, etc. languages Working knowledge across the following areas with experience: -Standard imaging interfaces and protocols in the typical consumer platform -Compact lens optics design & testing -Camera module mechanical design and tolerance analysis -Camera module electronic circuit design and signal integrity & power integrity analysis -Image sensor characterization and design -Depth sensing hardware development -Image quality evaluation methodology (test algorithm, chart, lab setup) -Camera module manufacturing process development"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MomEcUAJ/", "title": "Electrical Engineer", "location": "Redmond, WA", "description": "We are looking for an experienced Electrical Engineer who can drive the development of next generation display prototypes. This individual will work in a cross-functional team consisting of other electrical engineers, mechanical engineers, optical engineers, and research scientists. The successful candidate will have experience working with displays, analog and digital design skills, and experience leading teams. RESPONSIBILITIES Collaborate with cross-functional team members Partition EE work-loads among team members Drive EE stand-up meetings Drive all electrical engineering activities to completion, including: design, design reviews, manufacturing, assembly, test, characterization, and final system integration Create architectural diagrams and documents Hold design reviews and provide input to team members regarding EE best-practices Create full system prototypes for next generation display technologies Define scalable processes to take research-level prototypes and ramp them for production MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree in Electrical Engineering, Computer Engineering, or equivalent 5+ years of industry experience designing consumer products Experience scaling designs from low-volume to high-volume Experience designing embedded systems for production Experience with communication interfaces, such as MIPI, USB, I2C, and SPI Experience in schematic and board layout using Altium, Cadence, or equivalent Experience with PCB layout principles, including high speed signal integrity (multi-Gigabit), power layout, de-sense, DFM, etc. Experience with display systems Experience creating system and device specifications PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Masters or PhD Degree Experience with circuit simulations & modeling (e.g. SPICE, MATLAB) Experience designing custom ASICs Familiarity with silicon bring-up and characterization processes"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mp1zHUAR/", "title": "Hardware Systems Electrical Engineer FRL", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": "We are looking for an Electrical Engineer with experience in analog circuits and power to join our Brain-Computer Interface (BCI) team in Menlo Park, CA. In this role, you would work closely with researchers as part of a multi-disciplinary engineering team (e.g. mechanical, electrical, optical, and software) to design, build, test, and maintain novel wearable neural interface technologies. Our research is focused on developing functional brain-computer interface (BCI) technologies for use in consumer electronic products. Our team collaborates extensively with small companies and academic institutions, and publishes in peer-reviewed journals.  RESPONSIBILITIES Design and integrate electrical systems, including architecture, component selection, PCB schematic and layout, bring-up, characterization, and integration Integrate electronics with optical, mechanical, and software components, as part of a multi-disciplinary team Characterize, debug, and test systems using bench-top laboratory equipment and scripting Drive electrical engineering activities to completion, leveraging the internal team and external vendors Work closely with researchers to understand their goals and elicit electrical system requirements Take prototypes to increasing levels of fidelity, ranging from proof-of-concept demonstrations to integrated systems MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelors in Electrical or Computer Engineering or equivalent experience 3+ years of industry experience in consumer product system design Schematic and board layout experience using Altium, Cadence, or equivalent Lab and debugging experience for board and system bring-up and characterization using bench-top laboratory equipment Knowledge of PCB layout principles, including signal integrity, power layout, desense, DFM, etc. Experience integrating electrical systems that include components such as communication interfaces (e.g., MIPI, USB, I2C, SPI, PCIe, etc.), optoelectronics, cameras, sensors, FPGAs, microcontrollers, microprocessors, amplifiers, wireless, ADCs, DACs, DC-DC converters, and power sequencing PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Exposure to a start-up environment or a research environment RTL coding skills using Verilog or VHDL Programming skills (e.g., scripting, low-level software, DSP programming) Exposure to medical imaging or scientific instrumentation system development Experience collaborating with JDM/CM/ODM Experience designing products for mass production consumer hardware Circuit simulations experience using SPICE Masters or PhD"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LJs3tUAD/", "title": "Electrical Engineer (Hardware and FPGA)", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": "We are looking for an Electrical Engineer with experience in hardware systems and FPGAs to join our Brain-Computer Interface (BCI) team in Menlo Park, CA. In this role, you would work closely with researchers as part of a multi-disciplinary engineering team (e.g. mechanical, electrical, optical, and software) to design, build, test, and maintain novel wearable neural interface technologies. Our research is focused on developing functional brain-computer interface (BCI) technologies for use in consumer electronic products. Our team collaborates extensively with small companies and academic institutions, and publishes in peer-reviewed journals.  RESPONSIBILITIES Design and integrate electrical and computational systems, including architecture, component selection, PCB schematic and layout, bring-up, characterization, and integration FPGA programming using Verilog or VHDL Drive electrical engineering activities to completion, leveraging the internal team and external vendors Work closely with researchers to understand their goals and elicit electrical system requirements Integrate electronics with optical, mechanical, and software components, as part of a multi-disciplinary team Characterize and test opto-electro-mechanical systems using bench-top laboratory equipment and scripting Take prototypes to increasing levels of fidelity, ranging from rapid prototypes to mass production ready designs MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelors in Electrical or Computer Engineering or equivalent 4+ years of industry experience in consumer product design Experience integrating electrical systems that include communication interfaces (e.g., MIPI, USB, I2C, SPI, etc.), FPGAs, camera modules, microcontrollers, microprocessors, and power sequencing Experience in schematic and board layout using Altium, Cadence, or equivalent Experience with RTL coding using Verilog or VHDL Experience with lab and debugging for board and system bring-up and characterization using bench-top laboratory equipment Experience with PCB layout principles, including high speed signal integrity (multi-Gigabit), power layout, desense, DFM, etc. Experience with computer systems architecture and embedded systems Experience with programming and scripting PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience in one or more of the following: analog, transceivers, ADCs, DACs, power, low-level software, DSP programming, sensor technologies, low-power design, optoelectronics Experience in circuit simulations using SPICE Experience collaborating with JDM/CM/ODM Experience designing products for mass production consumer hardware Experience with medical imaging or scientific instrumentation system development Masters or PhD Degree"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MovEaUAJ/", "title": "Silicon Process and Foundry Engineer", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": "Facebook Reality Labs is the world leader in the design of virtual and augmented reality systems. Come work alongside expert engineers and research scientists to create the technology that makes VR and AR pervasive and universal. Join the adventure of a lifetime as we make science fiction real and change the world. \n \nWe are seeking a world class Silicon Process and Foundry Engineer to join our Silicon Team. The successful candidate will be a key part of our efforts to architect, design and implement several challenging pieces of digital, mixed signal and analog integrated circuits to support a game-changing new platform with very tight electrical, thermal and mechanical constraints. The ideal candidate will also have a substantial hands-on experience with silicon packaging pushing the state of the art to accommodate advanced new applications. \n \nThis is a full-time position based in Redmond, WA or Menlo Park, CA. RESPONSIBILITIES Work with the different Silicon and cross-functional teams understanding the top down system and silicon requirements and lead the analysis and decision process for technology node adoption for the different ASICs Own the AR silicon team foundry and semiconductor fabs/providers interface Be able to effectively work with and influence foundries world-wide to define the most optimized technology nodes and corresponding PDKs that most closely match our required deliverable Lead the analysis of design tradeoffs including performance, thermal, manufacturability, testability and cost Collaborate with industry, academia and research institutes to stay on top of new technology advances and push the state of the art to benefit our products Support the analysis and development of the advanced packaging technology required to support our silicon and system roadmaps Be able to communicate clearly across multiple groups and external vendors MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS PhD or M.S. degree in Electrical Engineering, Material or Computer Science or equivalent experience 10+ years of experience with silicon products, foundries, design, reliability, packaging for a variety of different applications such as Analog, RF (3-5G, Wi-Fi, millimeter waves) or Digital SOCs Knowledge of system & silicon architectures and overall silicon development process Knowledge of factors and parameters affecting system and silicon performance such as thermal dissipation, signal and power integrity, coupling, mechanical stability and failure analysis Experience doing trade-off analysis driving to concrete proposals Experience with advance technologies, such as 2.5D and 3D packaging, TSVs, wafer/chip to wafer bond, flex, board and glass bonding, etc."}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MojOwUAJ/", "title": "Manager, Developer Program, India", "location": "Gurgaon, India", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  \nFacebook is looking for a strategic and results-driven Program Manager who is passionate about the way Facebook Inc. can work with businesses, startups, and developers to build a variety of Programs and Partnerships to better serve their needs. As a part of the Developer Program team, you will engage with some of India's most influential startups, and work closely with VCs, Accelerators/Incubators, Trade Associations as well as our world-class product and engineering teams. In addition to those teams, you will work cross-functionally with the Policy, Legal, Marketing and the Operations teams to develop new programs, scale existing programs and make the Indian Start-up community more successful. This role is based in Gurgaon.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Define, develop and lead large programs in a fast-paced, rapidly changing environment with an ability to work to tight deadlines. Help drive and execute the program strategy for the startup ecosystem in India by gathering aggregated feedback from startups and developers. Maintain direct and active relationships with startups and developers on our platform, including onboarding and contract work, proactively resolving business, technical, and policy issues and serving as an internal advocate. Work cross-functionally with product, engineering, business development, partnerships, policy, legal, marketing, and PR to launch programs and partnerships. Set, track, analyze, communicate, and execute against key program performance metrics. Produce qualitative and quantitative analysis of program performance. Represent Facebook in external meetings with senior executives from other companies. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 8+ years of experience in working with startups, entrepreneurs, and developers. Thorough understanding of the Indian startup ecosystem, strong relations with stakeholders, passion for building impact programs. Exceptional collaboration and relationship-building skills \u2014 with the ability to develop strong working relationships at all levels of management, both inside and outside Facebook. Displaying the highest personal integrity and ethics Willingness and ability to travel 25-50% of the time"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MokD0UAJ/", "title": "Lead of Security & Privacy (FRL)", "location": "Redmond, WA", "description": "Are you  interested in new technologies?  Do you have a passion for Security and Privacy?   Can you envision a future and want to create it?  \n \nAt Facebook  Reality Labs (FRL), we\u2019re developing the future of augmented and virtual reality.  As Lead of Security & Privacy (FRL), your job will be to lead a team that helps us figure out what we need to do to ensure that we are developing products that our users will love and trust. You will be a critical member of a  multi-disciplinary team contributing to our efforts to ensure that we are creating secure end user environments that support new and revolutionary experiences leveraging audio, haptics, human perception, input, computer vision,  optics, display technology, and whatever else we dream up to create the ultimate AR and VR experiences. You will work closely with internal Facebook  teams, academic institutions, external partners, and vendors to help: define policy, requirements, and deliverables, translate complex and rigorous standards into easily implemented processes and tasks, align and track project progress against roadmaps and schedules, coordinate across internal teams, and manage partner relationships. To be successful, you will be  eliminating barriers to your team\u2019s success, clearly communicating the work needed  to all stakeholders, and ensuring the big picture stays in focus while delving  into the details on specific issues. Ideal team members are able to lead small to medium sized teams, work exceptionally well across organizations, distill complex ideas into easily consumable concepts, are adaptable and  resilient, eager to attack unfamiliar problems with curiosity and tenacity,  and able to use a light touch to find ways to help the team and broader organization be more  efficient. RESPONSIBILITIES Build the security and privacy Technical Program Manager teams for FRL Build durable and scalable security and privacy assurance programs across the business Attract industry leading privacy and security talent to the business Help shape and distill the business models for FRL product with regard to security and privacy across hardware, software, and cloud services Translate product and business goals into security requirements Manage security and privacy individual contributors Work with physical security team to ensure manufacturing security Executive leadership influencing on resourcing and organizational planning MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelors in Computer Science or related field Cross-discipline technical leadership experience Experience in building consumer device focused security and integrity engineering programs Experience in building privacy, security and integrity processes Experience building a team Experience managing a team Experience articulating security & privacy strategy for business units Experience translating security and privacy strategy into engineering designs and requirements Experience building and supporting others' careers Track record of executive communication experience at the V- and C-Suite of companies Knowledge with core security concepts, including: -User and code authentication and authorization systems -Core cryptography concepts -Secure coding practices -Application security concepts -Knowledge in network and web security protocols such as TLS, IPSec etc. Knowledge of device and hardware security concepts, including: - Secure boot -Sub-OS security isolation mechanisms -Operating system security concepts -Hardware supported memory management and encryption Track record of shipping industry leading consumer device security solutions 7+ years of industry experience architecting and  implementing security features and solutions 5+ years of industry experience as a security and privacy team leader Knowledge of security focused design and architecture experience Experience articulating and advocating for pragmatic, business appropriate security solutions Experience learning and contributing to security engineering solutions across the device and services technology stack Working knowledge of industry security and privacy standards (including NIST, ISO27001, GDPR etc.) PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS 7+ years of industry security experience Masters or PhD in Computer science or related field Technical security conference presentations or other indicators of industry grade security expertise 3+ years of industry grade code development experience Operating system, Sub-OS security design and architecture experience Secure manufacturing systems experience Experience authoring and managing key management systems Familiarity with embedded systems and silicon level security considerations Working knowledge of C/C++"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MonYkUAJ/", "title": "Copywriter, Digital Experience", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Guild\u2014Facebook's internal B2B creative agency\u2014helps to form meaningful connections between businesses and people. \n \nWe're looking for an agile Copywriter to join our family of artists, writers, filmmakers, strategists, analysts, producers and builders.\n \nThe ideal candidate has collaborated with all types of creative partners to concept and create innovative, effective and on-brand writing across channels and platforms, produced copy that both inspires and educates, developed narrative concepts for sizable marketing campaigns that come to life both online and off, has a track record of taking complex product stories and bringing them to life in clear, concise ways, and has managed projects and provided editorial direction to other creative teams. RESPONSIBILITIES You'll craft copy for facebook.com/business (http://facebook.com/business), our flagship business marketing site\u2014a project that requires a lot of strategic planning, cross-functional coordination and hands-on writing. You'll contribute to copy standards and ensure our digital writing maintains a human and approachable voice and tone. You'll write copy for campaigns on Facebook and Instagram and help create scripts for film. You'll partner with a highly cross-functional team of marketers, product owners and business leaders, all working together to bring our ideas to life. To be effective in this role, you\u2019ll need to understand and articulate Facebook\u2019s unique ability to help businesses connect with people and achieve their goals. You'll proactively find new opportunities to inspire advertisers to use Facebook's ever-growing family of apps and services. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 3+ years experience in a copywriting, brand or business writing role Bachelor's degree Writing samples or portfolio link (applications submitted without writing samples or portfolio link will not be considered) Experience writing copy for ad campaigns and websites Experience overseeing ideas from inception to launch Experience receiving feedback and coming up with solutions that retain the integrity of the ideas Experience self-initiating projects Knowledge of Facebook Business products (Ads Manager, Business Manager, Facebook Pages, Instagram Ads, etc.)"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MoyozUAB/", "title": "Strategic Partner Manager, Platform Partnerships, Australia", "location": "Sydney, Australia", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking an experienced Strategic Partner professional who is passionate about the way Facebook Inc. can work with businesses, startups, and developers to build a variety of valuable product experiences for people and is obsessed with technology, social media and business strategy in Australia. Platform Partnerships at Facebook is responsible for establishing and managing strategic relationships with our key product partners. You will work with some of the world's largest and most exciting companies and startups as well as with our world-class Facebook, Messenger and Instagram product and engineering teams. In addition to those teams, you will work cross-functionally with the Policy, Legal, Marketing, PR and the Operations teams to optimize new capabilities, improve user experience, and make our partners successful. This position is located in our Sydney, Australia office.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Help drive product strategy through strategic partnerships with businesses, developers, and leading consumer product organizations Define market requirements, produce qualitative and quantitative analysis of product performance, aggregate feedback, explore new strategic opportunities, inform the product roadmap with enhanced or new functionality, and ensure product and industry impact in region Maintain direct and active relationships with partners, including proactively resolving business, technical, and policy issues and serving as an internal advocate Track, analyze and communicate key quantitative metrics and business trends as they relate to partner relationships Represent Facebook in external meetings with executives from other companies, maintain direct and active relationships with partners, including proactively resolving business, technical, and policy issues and serving as an internal advocate Work cross-functionally with product, engineering, business development, partnerships, policy, legal, marketing, and PR to launch products and partnerships MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 8+ years of relevant work experience with product, partnership, or technical experience in consumer technology or mobile-focused companies Ability to define, develop and lead projects in a fast-paced, rapidly changing environment Collaboration and relationship-building skills \u2014 with the ability to develop working relationships at all levels of management, both inside and outside Facebook Organizational and analytical skills that have been used for requirements gathering, resource organization, and schedule development Willingness and ability to travel ~25% of the time Displaying the highest personal integrity and ethics"}
