uct performance, aggregate feedback, explore new strategic opportunities, inform the product roadmap with enhanced or new functionality, and ensure product and industry impact in region Maintain direct and active relationships with partners, including proactively resolving business, technical, and policy issues and serving as an internal advocate Track, analyze and communicate key quantitative metrics and business trends as they relate to partner relationships Represent Facebook in external meetings with C-level executives from other companies, maintain direct and active relationships with partners, including proactively resolving business, technical, and policy issues and serving as an internal advocate Work cross-functionally with product, engineering, business development, partnerships, policy, legal, marketing, and PR to launch products and partnerships MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 8+ years of relevant work experience with product, partnership, or technical experience in consumer technology or mobile-focused companies. Thorough understanding of Facebook Developer Products, and their strategic & competitive positions Ability to define, develop and lead projects in a fast-paced, rapidly changing environment Collaboration and relationship-building skills \u2014 with the ability to develop working relationships at all levels of management, both inside and outside Facebook Organizational and analytical skills that have been used for requirements gathering, resource organization, and schedule development Willingness and ability to travel ~25% of the time Displaying the highest personal integrity and ethics"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000Mp7LlUAJ/", "title": "Sales Operations Analyst", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is seeking a detail-oriented, driven and analytical Sales Operations Analyst who will serve as a member of Facebook\u2019s core Sales Operations team. \n \nThe role partners deeply with Small & Medium Business (SMB) sales organization with a focus on scaled regional and global programs.  The ideal candidate will be passionate about Facebook, interested in advertising, intellectually curious, a fast learner, and able to move fast while keeping focused on high impact projects. This is a full-time position and is located in our APAC HQ in Singapore. \n \nThe objective of this role is to drive strategic business decisions in close partnership with SMB Sales leadership by using clear frameworks, deploying excellent communication tactics, and producing deep analyses that will be the foundation upon which the recommendations are built.  The mission of the team is to maximize business performance by being the objective, trusted partner to the sales organization \u2013 through strategic planning, cross-functional collaboration and operational excellence. \n RESPONSIBILITIES Operating cadence / Rhythm of business - Partner with sales teams with planning and operational requests e.g. annual planning, monthly and quarterly business reviews Business partnership with Sales Leaders and key XFN partners \u2013 Support sales leadership and partner with key XFN stakeholders on operational and strategic issues to optimize resources (opex and headcount) to drive revenue growth in focused markets Business insights - Manage data pipelines and dashboards. Provide insights through revenue and product analysis. Identify key levers for driving revenue growth Strategic projects and initiatives - Translate global initiatives to regional level and help drive corporate alignment. Develop projects at regional level that have potential to scale at a global level. Drive operational excellence in the Sales organization through process improvements MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Bachelor's degree from a recognized institution >4+ years work experience in a consulting firm, investment banking or private equity firm or a similar role in a tech company Knowledge of online ad business would be a plus Demonstrated problem solving ability with experience providing practical business insights from large, complex data sets Strong communications and presentation skills especially with stakeholder management Strong project management and influencing skills, ability to lead and influence stakeholders at all levels of an organization Ability to work independently and cross functionally (sales, finance, product marketing, business intelligence/IT, ads integrity) and manage multiple concurrent projects Advanced SQL and Excel skills PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Strong knowledge Tableau, R or Python will be preferred"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MonH2UAJ/", "title": "Unit Systems Design Engineer", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook's Connectivity Team is looking for strong technical leaders to design, implement and deploy future novel communication technologies.  RESPONSIBILITIES Develop <6 GHz and mmWave communication devices using off-the-shelf integrated and discrete components. Evaluate impairments, interfaces, timing, and manufacturability of the unit. Unit integration, debugging and bring up in the lab & field and a transition to volume manufacturing. Work closely with hardware industry vendors and partners to identify, develop, test, and deploy the right technology. MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS BS in Electrical Engineering, Physics or a similar technical discipline with a minimum of 6 years of experience MS in Electrical Engineering, Physics, or a similar technical discipline with a minimum of 4 years of experience PhD in Electrical Engineering, Physics, or a similar technical discipline with a minimum of 2 years of experience Knowledge of one or more of the following areas: Antenna/RF/Transceiver design, Wireless Communication, Signal Processing and Analog/Digital Circuit Design (including processor, FPGA, memory, interconnects, power/signal integrity etc.) Hands-on experience with Modeling and Simulation of impairments along with experience debugging and resolving functional and performance failures Experience making trade-offs in unit design to achieve performance that meets specifications under cost and size constraints Knowledge of thermal, mechanical, and SW requirements and issues related to product design Experience working cross-functionally with RF, Digital, FGPA, ME and Embedded Software Engineers PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Experience with production issues and techniques (REL, DFM, DFT, OPS, Procurement) Energy and drive to work in a startup environment, and be a team player Detail oriented and diligent, balanced with rapid execution in a fast-paced environment"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000LJlttUAD/", "title": "Art Director, Interactive Design", "location": "Menlo Park, CA", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  The Guild, the internal creative and digital agency within Global Business Marketing, is hiring an Art Director to join the Brand Surfaces team. \n \nAs a member of the Brand Surfaces team, the Art Director designs content, interfaces, and other interactive platforms for Facebook Business, under the direction of the Creative Lead. This position requires a proven track record of graphic design and art direction for the web, particularly for the marketing of major brands; a strong knowledge of interactive creative development processes; and experience developing creative solutions. This individual must tell the rapidly evolving Facebook story to the market in the most compelling and aesthetically surprising ways possible, building on their natural leadership abilities and design shop/advertising agency background. The Art Director also works alongside a highly cross-functional team of designers, copywriters, marketers, product leaders, and business leaders, all working together to bring our ideas to life.\n \n RESPONSIBILITIES Deliver the art direction and design of an interactive project, from concept through to development Ability to solve complex multi-platform user experience challenges with simple yet progressive design solutions Art direct designers, as well as photographers and illustrators as necessary Help mentor and lead the design practice Collaborate with creative partners to concept and create innovative marketing ideas that can live across channels and platforms Solve problems conceptually in collaboration with the broader interactive team, including writers, UX designers, and developers Present the work effectively and clearly articulating the proposed design solutions Communicate efficiently with other team members to develop collaboration and trust Ensure Facebook branding is maintained across all business initiatives MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS 8+ years of design experience Portfolio link on resume Portfolio should feature creative development on marketing interactive experiences as well as digital products Experience overseeing ideas from inception to launch Experience taking feedback and input and coming up with solutions that keep the integrity of the ideas Experience in Photoshop, InDesign, Illustrator, PowerPoint and Keynote Experience articulating design decisions Experience self-initiating projects Experience with user-experience design and content strategy Experience using design principles to driving results in an online environment Bachelor's degree PREFFERED QUALIFICATIONS Passionate about pixel-perfect design solutions and strong attention to detail Hands-on experience using Facebook Business products (Ads Manager, Business Manager, Facebook Pages, Instagram Ads, etc.)"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MokVEUAZ/", "title": "Program Manager, Community Partnerships, APAC", "location": "Singapore", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  For the past decade, Facebook has focused on connecting friends and families. With that foundation, our next focus will be developing the social infrastructure for community \u2013 for supporting us, for keeping us safe, for informing us, for civic engagement, and for inclusion of all. We are at the beginning of this journey and are looking for someone who is interested in shaping our strategies through work with external partners. \n\nFacebook is building an experienced programs team that is passionate about the way Facebook can break the barriers community leaders face - funding, support, belief, and tools.  You should be obsessed with technology, social media and business strategy to build a variety of valuable program experiences for people to become part of such communities. \n\nYou will work with some of the world\u2019s best organization and as well as community leaders as well as our world class product and engineering teams. In addition to those teams, you will work cross-functionally with the Policy, Legal, Marketing, PR and the Operations teams to optimize new capabilities, improve user experience, and make our partners successful. A qualified candidate will have a strong passion and curiosity for innovative social products and their potential for transforming communities. This position is located in our Singapore office.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Drive program strategy through through strategic partnerships with community leaders - both people and organizations Define market requirements, produce qualitative and quantitative analysis of program performance, explore new strategic opportunities, inform the future roadmap with enhanced or new program, and ensure program and industry impact Maintain direct and active relationships with partners, including proactively resolving business, technical, and policy issues and serving as an internal advocate Work cross-functionally with product, engineering, business development, partnerships, policy, legal, marketing, and PR to launch products and partnerships -- to develop, implement and deliver value-add initiatives for community leaders Manage multiple complex project deliverables for multiple internal and external stakeholders. Provide guidance to community leaders in defining, analyzing, and measuring of their community management problems. Represent Facebook in external meetings with senior executives from other companies,  including proactively resolving technical and policy issues and serving as an internal advocate MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS Experience building communities and a zeal for the power of people coming together Significant experience in leadership development programs, grant giving, and program design 10-15 years of relevant work experience with programs, product, partnership, or technical experience in consumer technology companies, preferably mobile focused Understanding of Facebook Platform and how its products could be leveraged to build community Leadership building experience creating a culture of innovation, accountability, and a commitment to achieving results Proven track record of organizational, creative, and strategic-thought leadership Ability to define, develop and lead large programs in a fast-paced, rapidly changing environment Exceptional collaboration and relationship-building skills \u2014 with the ability to develop strong working relationships at all levels of management, both inside and outside Facebook A strong passion for innovation and collaboration with startups and early stage entrepreneurs and developers. Displaying the highest personal integrity and ethics Willingness and ability to travel 20% of the time"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MochEUAR/", "title": "Policy Programs Manager for Economic Impact and Digital Literacy, Africa", "location": "London, United Kingdom", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is looking for a Policy Programs Manager to support the Policy Programs Lead for Africa and the wider team in building partnerships that demonstrate the value of Facebook's platform to create positive economic impact across Africa. As part of Facebook\u2019s Africa Public Policy organization, the Policy Programs team is responsible for designing, developing and launching  regional programs that leverage the extraordinary reach of Facebook to promote positive social, economic, and cultural outcomes. \n \nWe are looking for a candidate who can build high impact programs across Africa. You should have a clear understanding of the policy challenges Facebook faces across the region related to economic impact, ambitious and creative ideas about how to address them, and the ability to fearlessly execute. You must have the ability to rally colleagues from across the company to scale, run & measure programs and investments. You should be highly organised and impact oriented and thrive in a fast-paced work environment. \n \nThis position is full time and location can be in Johannesburg, London or w/in region.\n RESPONSIBILITIES Identify, monitor, and analyze policy issues affecting Facebook and related to economic impact in key markets across Africa Identify, create and implement proactive strategies to address risk and create opportunities related to economic impact Work in partnership with the wider Africa Public Policy team on the strategy for building relationships with policy makers, civil society and academics Build & manage meaningful partnerships with key economic impact policy influencers and organizations across the region Represent Facebook in meetings with key stakeholders Collaborate and ensure consistency in policy programs across the region Coordinate internal and external cross functional groups Work closely with the regional public policy team in either East or Francophone Africa to develop programmatic strategies that meet the policy needs of the region MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS At least 5 + years working with an entity focused on digital skills development, entrepreneurship and/or education Impeccable integrity, passion for human rights and social impact, sound judgment, creativity and the demonstrated ability to think critically and challenge received wisdom At least 5 + years experience designing and implementing programs in/across Africa Ability to create and implement multiple projects and campaigns simultaneously Ability to work autonomously in a fast-paced, high-growth environment Ability to think, plan, and execute resourcefully and creatively Passion for technology and its power to address issues related to entrepreneurship and economic impact Ability to travel frequently and extensively across the region Passion for Facebook and its mission to make the world more open and connected Superior written and oral communications skills Fluency in English and at least one other additional language preferably   Swahili, Amarhic or French"}
{"url": "https://www.facebook.com/careers/jobs/a0I1H00000MolDeUAJ/", "title": "Policy Programs Manager for Social Impact and Human Rights, Africa", "location": "London, United Kingdom", "description": " Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities \u2014 we're just getting started.  Facebook is looking for a Policy Programs Manager to support the Policy Programs Lead for Africa and the wider team in building partnerships that demonstrate the value of Facebook's platform to advance human rights and social good. As part of Facebook\u2019s Africa Public Policy organization, the Policy Programs team is responsible for designing, developing and launching  regional programs that leverage the extraordinary reach of Facebook to promote social, economic, and cultural impact. \n \nWe are looking for candidates who can build partnerships with civil society and social impact stakeholders and deliver high impact programs across Africa. You should have a clear understanding of the policy challenges Facebook faces across the region related to human rights and social impact, ambitious and creative ideas about how to address them, and the ability to fearlessly execute. You must have the ability to rally colleagues from across the company to scale, run & measure programs and investments. You should be highly organised and impact oriented and thrive in a fast-paced work environment. \n \nThis position is full time and location can be in Johannesburg, London or w/in region. RESPONSIBILITIES Identify, monitor, and analyze policy issues affecting Facebook and related to human rights and social impact in key markets across Africa Identify, create and implement proactive strategies to address risk and create opportunities related to human rights and social impact Work in partnership with the wider Africa Public Policy team on the strategy for building relationships with policy makers, civil society and academics Build & manage meaningful partnerships with key social impact and human rights organizations across the region Represent Facebook in meetings with key stakeholders Collaborate and ensure consistency in policy programs across the region Coordinate internal and external cross functional groups.\nWork closely with the regional public policy team in either East or Francophone Africa to develop programmatic strategies that meet the policy needs of the region MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS At least 5 + years working with civil society and political systems/institutions in Africa, particularly those related to human rights, free expression, social justice, women's rights, health access, LGBTQIA rights, peace building Impeccable integrity, passion for human rights and social impact, sound judgment, creativity and the demonstrated ability to think critically and challenge received wisdom At least 5 + years experience designing and implementing programs in/across Africa Ability to create and implement multiple projects and campaigns simultaneously Ability to work autonomously in a fast-paced, high-growth environment Ability to think, plan, and execute resourcefully and creatively Passion for technology and its power to address issues related to social impact and human rights, as well as a deep understanding of the ways that technology and social media platforms Experience working with health access institutions a plus Ability to travel frequently and extensively across the region Passion for Facebook and its mission to make the world more open and connected Superior written and oral communications skills Fluency in English and at least one other additional language required (French or a regional language)"}
